50class ObjCCommonTypesHelper {
51protected:
52 llvm::LLVMContext &VMContext;
53
54private:
55 // The types of these functions don't really matter because we
56 // should always bitcast before calling them.
57
58 /// id objc_msgSend (id, SEL, ...)
59 ///
60 /// The default messenger, used for sends whose ABI is unchanged from
61 /// the all-integer/pointer case.
62 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendFn() const {
63 // Add the non-lazy-bind attribute, since objc_msgSend is likely to
64 // be called a lot.
65 llvm::Type *params[] = { ObjectPtrTy, SelectorPtrTy };
66 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
67 llvm::FunctionType::get(ObjectPtrTy, params, true), "objc_msgSend",
68 llvm::AttributeList::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(),
69 llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
70 llvm::Attribute::NonLazyBind));
71 }
72
73 /// void objc_msgSend_stret (id, SEL, ...)
74 ///
75 /// The messenger used when the return value is an aggregate returned
76 /// by indirect reference in the first argument, and therefore the
77 /// self and selector parameters are shifted over by one.
78 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendStretFn() const {
79 llvm::Type *params[] = { ObjectPtrTy, SelectorPtrTy };
80 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy,
81 params, true),
82 "objc_msgSend_stret");
83 }
84
85 /// [double | long double] objc_msgSend_fpret(id self, SEL op, ...)
86 ///
87 /// The messenger used when the return value is returned on the x87
88 /// floating-point stack; without a special entrypoint, the nil case
89 /// would be unbalanced.
90 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendFpretFn() const {
91 llvm::Type *params[] = { ObjectPtrTy, SelectorPtrTy };
92 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.DoubleTy,
93 params, true),
94 "objc_msgSend_fpret");
95 }
96
97 /// _Complex long double objc_msgSend_fp2ret(id self, SEL op, ...)
98 ///
99 /// The messenger used when the return value is returned in two values on the
100 /// x87 floating point stack; without a special entrypoint, the nil case
101 /// would be unbalanced. Only used on 64-bit X86.
102 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendFp2retFn() const {
103 llvm::Type *params[] = { ObjectPtrTy, SelectorPtrTy };
104 llvm::Type *longDoubleType = llvm::Type::getX86_FP80Ty(VMContext);
105 llvm::Type *resultType =
106 llvm::StructType::get(longDoubleType, longDoubleType);
107
108 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType::get(resultType,
109 params, true),
110 "objc_msgSend_fp2ret");
111 }
112
113 /// id objc_msgSendSuper(struct objc_super *super, SEL op, ...)
114 ///
115 /// The messenger used for super calls, which have different dispatch
116 /// semantics. The class passed is the superclass of the current
117 /// class.
118 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendSuperFn() const {
119 llvm::Type *params[] = { SuperPtrTy, SelectorPtrTy };
120 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType::get(ObjectPtrTy,
121 params, true),
122 "objc_msgSendSuper");
123 }
124
125 /// id objc_msgSendSuper2(struct objc_super *super, SEL op, ...)
126 ///
127 /// A slightly different messenger used for super calls. The class
128 /// passed is the current class.
129 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendSuperFn2() const {
130 llvm::Type *params[] = { SuperPtrTy, SelectorPtrTy };
131 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType::get(ObjectPtrTy,
132 params, true),
133 "objc_msgSendSuper2");
134 }
135
136 /// void objc_msgSendSuper_stret(void *stretAddr, struct objc_super *super,
137 /// SEL op, ...)
138 ///
139 /// The messenger used for super calls which return an aggregate indirectly.
140 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendSuperStretFn() const {
141 llvm::Type *params[] = { Int8PtrTy, SuperPtrTy, SelectorPtrTy };
142 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
143 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, params, true),
144 "objc_msgSendSuper_stret");
145 }
146
147 /// void objc_msgSendSuper2_stret(void * stretAddr, struct objc_super *super,
148 /// SEL op, ...)
149 ///
150 /// objc_msgSendSuper_stret with the super2 semantics.
151 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendSuperStretFn2() const {
152 llvm::Type *params[] = { Int8PtrTy, SuperPtrTy, SelectorPtrTy };
153 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
154 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, params, true),
155 "objc_msgSendSuper2_stret");
156 }
157
158 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendSuperFpretFn() const {
159 // There is no objc_msgSendSuper_fpret? How can that work?
160 return getMessageSendSuperFn();
161 }
162
163 llvm::FunctionCallee getMessageSendSuperFpretFn2() const {
164 // There is no objc_msgSendSuper_fpret? How can that work?
165 return getMessageSendSuperFn2();
166 }

169 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM;

171public:
172 llvm::IntegerType *ShortTy, *IntTy, *LongTy;
173 llvm::PointerType *Int8PtrTy, *Int8PtrPtrTy;
174 llvm::Type *IvarOffsetVarTy;

176 /// ObjectPtrTy - LLVM type for object handles (typeof(id))
177 llvm::PointerType *ObjectPtrTy;
178
179 /// PtrObjectPtrTy - LLVM type for id *
180 llvm::PointerType *PtrObjectPtrTy;
181
182 /// SelectorPtrTy - LLVM type for selector handles (typeof(SEL))
183 llvm::PointerType *SelectorPtrTy;
184
185private:
186 /// ProtocolPtrTy - LLVM type for external protocol handles
187 /// (typeof(Protocol))
188 llvm::Type *ExternalProtocolPtrTy;
189
190public:
191 llvm::Type *getExternalProtocolPtrTy() {
192 if (!ExternalProtocolPtrTy) {
193 // FIXME: It would be nice to unify this with the opaque type, so that the
194 // IR comes out a bit cleaner.
195 CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
196 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
197 llvm::Type *T = Types.ConvertType(Ctx.getObjCProtoType());
198 ExternalProtocolPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(T, DefaultAS);
199 }
200
201 return ExternalProtocolPtrTy;
202 }

210 llvm::StructType *SuperTy;
211 /// SuperPtrTy - LLVM type for struct objc_super *.
212 llvm::PointerType *SuperPtrTy;

215 /// in GCC parlance).

219 /// (_prop_list_t in GCC parlance).

222 llvm::PointerType *PropertyListPtrTy;

225 llvm::StructType *MethodTy;

228 llvm::Type *CacheTy;
229 /// CachePtrTy - LLVM type for struct objc_cache *.

232 llvm::FunctionCallee getGetPropertyFn() {
233 CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
234 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
235 // id objc_getProperty (id, SEL, ptrdiff_t, bool)
236 CanQualType IdType = Ctx.getCanonicalParamType(Ctx.getObjCIdType());
237 CanQualType SelType = Ctx.getCanonicalParamType(Ctx.getObjCSelType());
238 CanQualType Params[] = {
239 IdType, SelType,
240 Ctx.getPointerDiffType()->getCanonicalTypeUnqualified(), Ctx.BoolTy};
241 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
242 Types.GetFunctionType(
243 Types.arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(IdType, Params));
244 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "objc_getProperty");
245 }
246
247 llvm::FunctionCallee getSetPropertyFn() {
248 CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
249 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
250 // void objc_setProperty (id, SEL, ptrdiff_t, id, bool, bool)
251 CanQualType IdType = Ctx.getCanonicalParamType(Ctx.getObjCIdType());
252 CanQualType SelType = Ctx.getCanonicalParamType(Ctx.getObjCSelType());
253 CanQualType Params[] = {
254 IdType,
255 SelType,
256 Ctx.getPointerDiffType()->getCanonicalTypeUnqualified(),
257 IdType,
258 Ctx.BoolTy,
259 Ctx.BoolTy};
260 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
261 Types.GetFunctionType(
262 Types.arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(Ctx.VoidTy, Params));
263 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "objc_setProperty");
264 }
265
266 llvm::FunctionCallee getOptimizedSetPropertyFn(bool atomic, bool copy) {
267 CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
268 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
269 // void objc_setProperty_atomic(id self, SEL _cmd,
270 // id newValue, ptrdiff_t offset);
271 // void objc_setProperty_nonatomic(id self, SEL _cmd,
272 // id newValue, ptrdiff_t offset);
273 // void objc_setProperty_atomic_copy(id self, SEL _cmd,
274 // id newValue, ptrdiff_t offset);
275 // void objc_setProperty_nonatomic_copy(id self, SEL _cmd,
276 // id newValue, ptrdiff_t offset);
277
278 SmallVector<CanQualType,4> Params;
279 CanQualType IdType = Ctx.getCanonicalParamType(Ctx.getObjCIdType());
280 CanQualType SelType = Ctx.getCanonicalParamType(Ctx.getObjCSelType());
281 Params.push_back(IdType);
282 Params.push_back(SelType);
283 Params.push_back(IdType);
284 Params.push_back(Ctx.getPointerDiffType()->getCanonicalTypeUnqualified());
285 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
286 Types.GetFunctionType(
287 Types.arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(Ctx.VoidTy, Params));
288 const char *name;
289 if (atomic && copy)
290 name = "objc_setProperty_atomic_copy";
291 else if (atomic && !copy)
292 name = "objc_setProperty_atomic";
293 else if (!atomic && copy)
294 name = "objc_setProperty_nonatomic_copy";
295 else
296 name = "objc_setProperty_nonatomic";
297
298 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, name);
299 }
300
301 llvm::FunctionCallee getCopyStructFn() {
302 CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
303 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
304 // void objc_copyStruct (void *, const void *, size_t, bool, bool)
305 SmallVector<CanQualType,5> Params;
306 Params.push_back(Ctx.VoidPtrTy);
307 Params.push_back(Ctx.VoidPtrTy);
308 Params.push_back(Ctx.getSizeType());
309 Params.push_back(Ctx.BoolTy);
310 Params.push_back(Ctx.BoolTy);
311 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
312 Types.GetFunctionType(
313 Types.arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(Ctx.VoidTy, Params));
314 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "objc_copyStruct");
315 }

317 /// This routine declares and returns address of:
318 /// void objc_copyCppObjectAtomic(
319 /// void *dest, const void *src,
320 /// void (*copyHelper) (void *dest, const void *source));
321 llvm::FunctionCallee getCppAtomicObjectFunction() {
322 CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
323 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
324 /// void objc_copyCppObjectAtomic(void *dest, const void *src, void *helper);
325 SmallVector<CanQualType,3> Params;
326 Params.push_back(Ctx.VoidPtrTy);
327 Params.push_back(Ctx.VoidPtrTy);
328 Params.push_back(Ctx.VoidPtrTy);
329 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
330 Types.GetFunctionType(
331 Types.arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(Ctx.VoidTy, Params));
332 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "objc_copyCppObjectAtomic");
333 }

335 llvm::FunctionCallee getEnumerationMutationFn() {
336 CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
337 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
338 // void objc_enumerationMutation (id)
339 SmallVector<CanQualType,1> Params;
340 Params.push_back(Ctx.getCanonicalParamType(Ctx.getObjCIdType()));
341 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
342 Types.GetFunctionType(
343 Types.arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(Ctx.VoidTy, Params));
344 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "objc_enumerationMutation");
345 }

347 llvm::FunctionCallee getLookUpClassFn() {
348 CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
349 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
350 // Class objc_lookUpClass (const char *)
351 SmallVector<CanQualType,1> Params;
352 Params.push_back(
353 Ctx.getCanonicalType(Ctx.getPointerType(Ctx.CharTy.withConst())));
354 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
355 Types.GetFunctionType(Types.arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(
356 Ctx.getCanonicalType(Ctx.getObjCClassType()),
357 Params));
358 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "objc_lookUpClass");
359 }

473 return IsSuper ? getMessageSendSuperStretFn2() : getMessageSendStretFn();
474 }

477 return IsSuper ? getMessageSendSuperFpretFn() : getMessageSendFpretFn();
478 }
479

481 return IsSuper ? getMessageSendSuperFpretFn2() : getMessageSendFpretFn();
482 }
483

485 return IsSuper ? getMessageSendSuperFn() : getMessageSendFp2retFn();
486 }
487
488 llvm::FunctionCallee getSendFp2RetFn2(bool IsSuper) const {
489 return IsSuper ? getMessageSendSuperFn2() : getMessageSendFp2retFn();

495/// ObjCTypesHelper - Helper class that encapsulates lazy
496/// construction of varies types used during ObjC generation.
497class ObjCTypesHelper : public ObjCCommonTypesHelper {
498public:
499 /// SymtabTy - LLVM type for struct objc_symtab.
500 llvm::StructType *SymtabTy;
501 /// SymtabPtrTy - LLVM type for struct objc_symtab *.

503 /// ModuleTy - LLVM type for struct objc_module.
504 llvm::StructType *ModuleTy;
505
506 /// ProtocolTy - LLVM type for struct objc_protocol.

508 /// ProtocolPtrTy - LLVM type for struct objc_protocol *.
509 llvm::PointerType *ProtocolPtrTy;
510 /// ProtocolExtensionTy - LLVM type for struct
511 /// objc_protocol_extension.
512 llvm::StructType *ProtocolExtensionTy;
513 /// ProtocolExtensionTy - LLVM type for struct
514 /// objc_protocol_extension *.
515 llvm::PointerType *ProtocolExtensionPtrTy;
516 /// MethodDescriptionTy - LLVM type for struct
517 /// objc_method_description.
518 llvm::StructType *MethodDescriptionTy;
519 /// MethodDescriptionListTy - LLVM type for struct
520 /// objc_method_description_list.
521 llvm::StructType *MethodDescriptionListTy;
522 /// MethodDescriptionListPtrTy - LLVM type for struct
523 /// objc_method_description_list *.
524 llvm::PointerType *MethodDescriptionListPtrTy;

526 llvm::StructType *ProtocolListTy;

533 /// ClassPtrTy - LLVM type for struct objc_class *.

580 /// ExceptionMatchFn - LLVM objc_exception_match function.
581 llvm::FunctionCallee getExceptionMatchFn() {

730 /// Class objc_loadClassref (void *)
731 ///
732 /// Loads from a classref. For Objective-C stub classes, this invokes the
733 /// initialization callback stored inside the stub. For all other classes
734 /// this simply dereferences the pointer.
735 llvm::FunctionCallee getLoadClassrefFn() const {
736 // Add the non-lazy-bind attribute, since objc_loadClassref is likely to
737 // be called a lot.
738 //
739 // Also it is safe to make it readnone, since we never load or store the
740 // classref except by calling this function.
741 llvm::Type *params[] = { Int8PtrPtrTy };
742 llvm::FunctionCallee F = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
743 llvm::FunctionType::get(ClassnfABIPtrTy, params, false),
744 "objc_loadClassref",
745 llvm::AttributeList::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(),
746 llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
747 {llvm::Attribute::NonLazyBind,
748 llvm::Attribute::ReadNone,
749 llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind}));
750 if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
751 cast<llvm::Function>(F.getCallee())->setLinkage(
752 llvm::Function::ExternalWeakLinkage);
753
754 return F;
755 }

780 /// opcode for captured block variables layout 'instructions'.
781 /// In the following descriptions, 'I' is the value of the immediate field.
782 /// (field following the opcode).
783 ///
784 enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE {
785 /// An operator which affects how the following layout should be
786 /// interpreted.
787 /// I == 0: Halt interpretation and treat everything else as
788 /// a non-pointer. Note that this instruction is equal
789 /// to '\0'.
790 /// I != 0: Currently unused.
791 BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPERATOR = 0,
792
793 /// The next I+1 bytes do not contain a value of object pointer type.
794 /// Note that this can leave the stream unaligned, meaning that
795 /// subsequent word-size instructions do not begin at a multiple of
796 /// the pointer size.
797 BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_BYTES = 1,
798
799 /// The next I+1 words do not contain a value of object pointer type.
800 /// This is simply an optimized version of BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYTES for
801 /// when the required skip quantity is a multiple of the pointer size.
802 BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_WORDS = 2,
803
804 /// The next I+1 words are __strong pointers to Objective-C
805 /// objects or blocks.
806 BLOCK_LAYOUT_STRONG = 3,
807
808 /// The next I+1 words are pointers to __block variables.
809 BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF = 4,
810
811 /// The next I+1 words are __weak pointers to Objective-C
812 /// objects or blocks.
813 BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK = 5,
814
815 /// The next I+1 words are __unsafe_unretained pointers to
816 /// Objective-C objects or blocks.
817 BLOCK_LAYOUT_UNRETAINED = 6
818
819 /// The next I+1 words are block or object pointers with some
820 /// as-yet-unspecified ownership semantics. If we add more
821 /// flavors of ownership semantics, values will be taken from
822 /// this range.
823 ///
824 /// This is included so that older tools can at least continue
825 /// processing the layout past such things.
826 //BLOCK_LAYOUT_OWNERSHIP_UNKNOWN = 7..10,
827
828 /// All other opcodes are reserved. Halt interpretation and
829 /// treat everything else as opaque.
830 };
831
832 class RUN_SKIP {
833 public:
834 enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE opcode;
835 CharUnits block_var_bytepos;
836 CharUnits block_var_size;
837 RUN_SKIP(enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE Opcode = BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPERATOR,
838 CharUnits BytePos = CharUnits::Zero(),
839 CharUnits Size = CharUnits::Zero())
840 : opcode(Opcode), block_var_bytepos(BytePos), block_var_size(Size) {}
841
842 // Allow sorting based on byte pos.
843 bool operator<(const RUN_SKIP &b) const {
844 return block_var_bytepos < b.block_var_bytepos;
845 }
846 };

1132enum class MethodListType {
1133 CategoryInstanceMethods,
1134 CategoryClassMethods,
1135 InstanceMethods,
1136 ClassMethods,
1137 ProtocolInstanceMethods,
1138 ProtocolClassMethods,
1139 OptionalProtocolInstanceMethods,
1140 OptionalProtocolClassMethods,
1141};
1142
1143/// A convenience class for splitting the methods of a protocol into
1144/// the four interesting groups.
1145class ProtocolMethodLists {
1146public:
1147 enum Kind {
1148 RequiredInstanceMethods,
1149 RequiredClassMethods,
1150 OptionalInstanceMethods,
1151 OptionalClassMethods
1152 };
1153 enum {
1154 NumProtocolMethodLists = 4
1155 };
1156
1157 static MethodListType getMethodListKind(Kind kind) {
1158 switch (kind) {
1159 case RequiredInstanceMethods:
1160 return MethodListType::ProtocolInstanceMethods;
1161 case RequiredClassMethods:
1162 return MethodListType::ProtocolClassMethods;
1163 case OptionalInstanceMethods:
1164 return MethodListType::OptionalProtocolInstanceMethods;
1165 case OptionalClassMethods:
1166 return MethodListType::OptionalProtocolClassMethods;
1167 }
1168 llvm_unreachable("bad kind");
1169 }
1170
1171 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl *, 4> Methods[NumProtocolMethodLists];
1172
1173 static ProtocolMethodLists get(const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
1174 ProtocolMethodLists result;
1175
1176 for (auto MD : PD->methods()) {
1177 size_t index = (2 * size_t(MD->isOptional()))
1178 + (size_t(MD->isClassMethod()));
1179 result.Methods[index].push_back(MD);
1180 }
1181
1182 return result;
1183 }
1184
1185 template <class Self>
1186 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 8> emitExtendedTypesArray(Self *self) const {
1187 // In both ABIs, the method types list is parallel with the
1188 // concatenation of the methods arrays in the following order:
1189 // instance methods
1190 // class methods
1191 // optional instance methods
1192 // optional class methods
1193 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 8> result;
1194
1195 // Methods is already in the correct order for both ABIs.
1196 for (auto &list : Methods) {
1197 for (auto MD : list) {
1198 result.push_back(self->GetMethodVarType(MD, true));
1199 }
1200 }
1201
1202 return result;
1203 }
1204
1205 template <class Self>
1206 llvm::Constant *emitMethodList(Self *self, const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD,
1207 Kind kind) const {
1208 return self->emitMethodList(PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
1209 getMethodListKind(kind), Methods[kind]);
1210 }
1211};
1212
1213} // end anonymous namespace

1570 bool IsIvarOffsetKnownIdempotent(const CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1571 const ObjCIvarDecl *IV) {
1572 // Annotate the load as an invariant load iff inside an instance method
1573 // and ivar belongs to instance method's class and one of its super class.
1574 // This check is needed because the ivar offset is a lazily
1575 // initialised value that may depend on objc_msgSend to perform a fixup on
1576 // the first message dispatch.
1577 //
1578 // An additional opportunity to mark the load as invariant arises when the
1579 // base of the ivar access is a parameter to an Objective C method.
1580 // However, because the parameters are not available in the current
1581 // interface, we cannot perform this check.
1582 if (const ObjCMethodDecl *MD =
1583 dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMethodDecl>(CGF.CurFuncDecl))
1584 if (MD->isInstanceMethod())
1585 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = MD->getClassInterface())
1586 return IV->getContainingInterface()->isSuperClassOf(ID);
1587 return false;
1588 }
1589
1590 bool isClassLayoutKnownStatically(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
1591 // NSObject is a fixed size. If we can see the @implementation of a class
1592 // which inherits from NSObject then we know that all it's offsets also must
1593 // be fixed. FIXME: Can we do this if see a chain of super classes with
1594 // implementations leading to NSObject?
1595 return ID->getImplementation() && ID->getSuperClass() &&
1596 ID->getSuperClass()->getName() == "NSObject";
1597 }

1708/// A helper class for performing the null-initialization of a return
1709/// value.
1710struct NullReturnState {
1711 llvm::BasicBlock *NullBB;
1712 NullReturnState() : NullBB(nullptr) {}
1713
1714 /// Perform a null-check of the given receiver.
1715 void init(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *receiver) {
1716 // Make blocks for the null-receiver and call edges.
1717 NullBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("msgSend.null-receiver");
1718 llvm::BasicBlock *callBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("msgSend.call");
1719
1720 // Check for a null receiver and, if there is one, jump to the
1721 // null-receiver block. There's no point in trying to avoid it:
1722 // we're always going to put *something* there, because otherwise
1723 // we shouldn't have done this null-check in the first place.
1724 llvm::Value *isNull = CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(receiver);
1725 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(isNull, NullBB, callBB);
1726
1727 // Otherwise, start performing the call.
1728 CGF.EmitBlock(callBB);
1729 }
1730
1731 /// Complete the null-return operation. It is valid to call this
1732 /// regardless of whether 'init' has been called.
1733 RValue complete(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1734 ReturnValueSlot returnSlot,
1735 RValue result,
1736 QualType resultType,
1737 const CallArgList &CallArgs,
1738 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
1739 // If we never had to do a null-check, just use the raw result.
1740 if (!NullBB) return result;
1741
1742 // The continuation block. This will be left null if we don't have an
1743 // IP, which can happen if the method we're calling is marked noreturn.
1744 llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = nullptr;
1745
1746 // Finish the call path.
1747 llvm::BasicBlock *callBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
1748 if (callBB) {
1749 contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("msgSend.cont");
1750 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(contBB);
1751 }
1752
1753 // Okay, start emitting the null-receiver block.
1754 CGF.EmitBlock(NullBB);
1755
1756 // Release any consumed arguments we've got.
1757 if (Method) {
1758 CallArgList::const_iterator I = CallArgs.begin();
1759 for (ObjCMethodDecl::param_const_iterator i = Method->param_begin(),
1760 e = Method->param_end(); i != e; ++i, ++I) {
1761 const ParmVarDecl *ParamDecl = (*i);
1762 if (ParamDecl->hasAttr<NSConsumedAttr>()) {
1763 RValue RV = I->getRValue(CGF);
1764 assert(RV.isScalar() &&
1765 "NullReturnState::complete - arg not on object");
1766 CGF.EmitARCRelease(RV.getScalarVal(), ARCImpreciseLifetime);
1767 }
1768 }
1769 }
1770
1771 // The phi code below assumes that we haven't needed any control flow yet.
1772 assert(CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock() == NullBB);
1773
1774 // If we've got a void return, just jump to the continuation block.
1775 if (result.isScalar() && resultType->isVoidType()) {
1776 // No jumps required if the message-send was noreturn.
1777 if (contBB) CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
1778 return result;
1779 }
1780
1781 // If we've got a scalar return, build a phi.
1782 if (result.isScalar()) {
1783 // Derive the null-initialization value.
1784 llvm::Constant *null = CGF.CGM.EmitNullConstant(resultType);
1785
1786 // If no join is necessary, just flow out.
1787 if (!contBB) return RValue::get(null);
1788
1789 // Otherwise, build a phi.
1790 CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
1791 llvm::PHINode *phi = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(null->getType(), 2);
1792 phi->addIncoming(result.getScalarVal(), callBB);
1793 phi->addIncoming(null, NullBB);
1794 return RValue::get(phi);
1795 }
1796
1797 // If we've got an aggregate return, null the buffer out.
1798 // FIXME: maybe we should be doing things differently for all the
1799 // cases where the ABI has us returning (1) non-agg values in
1800 // memory or (2) agg values in registers.
1801 if (result.isAggregate()) {
1802 assert(result.isAggregate() && "null init of non-aggregate result?");
1803 if (!returnSlot.isUnused())
1804 CGF.EmitNullInitialization(result.getAggregateAddress(), resultType);
1805 if (contBB) CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
1806 return result;
1807 }
1808
1809 // Complex types.
1810 CGF.EmitBlock(contBB);
1811 CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy callResult = result.getComplexVal();
1812
1813 // Find the scalar type and its zero value.
1814 llvm::Type *scalarTy = callResult.first->getType();
1815 llvm::Constant *scalarZero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(scalarTy);
1816
1817 // Build phis for both coordinates.
1818 llvm::PHINode *real = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(scalarTy, 2);
1819 real->addIncoming(callResult.first, callBB);
1820 real->addIncoming(scalarZero, NullBB);
1821 llvm::PHINode *imag = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(scalarTy, 2);
1822 imag->addIncoming(callResult.second, callBB);
1823 imag->addIncoming(scalarZero, NullBB);
1824 return RValue::getComplex(real, imag);
1825 }
1826};
1827
1828} // end anonymous namespace

1954llvm::Constant *CGObjCMac::getNSConstantStringClassRef() {
1955 if (llvm::Value *V = ConstantStringClassRef)
1956 return cast<llvm::Constant>(V);
1957
1958 auto &StringClass = CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCConstantStringClass;
1959 std::string str =
1960 StringClass.empty() ? "_NSConstantStringClassReference"
1961 : "_" + StringClass + "ClassReference";
1962
1963 llvm::Type *PTy = llvm::ArrayType::get(CGM.IntTy, 0);
1964 auto GV = CGM.CreateRuntimeVariable(PTy, str);
1965 auto V = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, CGM.IntTy->getPointerTo(
1966 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()));
1967 ConstantStringClassRef = V;
1968 return V;
1969}
1970
1971llvm::Constant *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::getNSConstantStringClassRef() {
1972 if (llvm::Value *V = ConstantStringClassRef)
1973 return cast<llvm::Constant>(V);
1974
1975 auto &StringClass = CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCConstantStringClass;
1976 std::string str =
1977 StringClass.empty() ? "OBJC_CLASS_$_NSConstantString"
1978 : "OBJC_CLASS_$_" + StringClass;
1979 llvm::Constant *GV = GetClassGlobal(str, NotForDefinition);
1980
1981 // Make sure the result is of the correct type.
1982 auto V = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, CGM.IntTy->getPointerTo(
1983 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()));
1984
1985 ConstantStringClassRef = V;
1986 return V;
1987}
1988
1989ConstantAddress
1990CGObjCCommonMac::GenerateConstantNSString(const StringLiteral *Literal) {
1991 unsigned StringLength = 0;
1992 llvm::StringMapEntry<llvm::GlobalVariable *> &Entry =
1993 GetConstantStringEntry(NSConstantStringMap, Literal, StringLength);
1994
1995 if (auto *C = Entry.second)
1996 return ConstantAddress(C, CharUnits::fromQuantity(C->getAlignment()));
1997
1998 // If we don't already have it, get _NSConstantStringClassReference.
1999 llvm::Constant *Class = getNSConstantStringClassRef();
2000
2001 // If we don't already have it, construct the type for a constant NSString.
2002 if (!NSConstantStringType) {
2003 NSConstantStringType =
2004 llvm::StructType::create({
2005 CGM.Int32Ty->getPointerTo(CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()),
2006 CGM.Int8PtrTy,
2007 CGM.IntTy
2008 }, "struct.__builtin_NSString");
2009 }
2010
2011 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
2012 auto Fields = Builder.beginStruct(NSConstantStringType);
2013
2014 // Class pointer.
2015 Fields.add(Class);
2016
2017 // String pointer.
2018 llvm::Constant *C =
2019 llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(VMContext, Entry.first());
2020
2021 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage;
2022 bool isConstant = !CGM.getLangOpts().WritableStrings;
2023
2024 auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), C->getType(), isConstant,
2025 Linkage, C, ".str");
2026 GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
2027 // Don't enforce the target's minimum global alignment, since the only use
2028 // of the string is via this class initializer.
2029 GV->setAlignment(1);
2030 Fields.addBitCast(GV, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
2031
2032 // String length.
2033 Fields.addInt(CGM.IntTy, StringLength);
2034
2035 // The struct.
2036 CharUnits Alignment = CGM.getPointerAlign();
2037 GV = Fields.finishAndCreateGlobal("_unnamed_nsstring_", Alignment,
2038 /*constant*/ true,
2039 llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage);
2040 const char *NSStringSection = "__OBJC,__cstring_object,regular,no_dead_strip";
2041 const char *NSStringNonFragileABISection =
2042 "__DATA,__objc_stringobj,regular,no_dead_strip";
2043 // FIXME. Fix section.
2044 GV->setSection(CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.isNonFragile()
2045 ? NSStringNonFragileABISection
2046 : NSStringSection);
2047 Entry.second = GV;
2048
2049 return ConstantAddress(GV, Alignment);
2050}

2056/// Generates a message send where the super is the receiver. This is
2057/// a message send to self with special delivery semantics indicating
2058/// which class's method should be called.
2059CodeGen::RValue
2060CGObjCMac::GenerateMessageSendSuper(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2061 ReturnValueSlot Return,
2062 QualType ResultType,
2063 Selector Sel,
2064 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class,
2065 bool isCategoryImpl,
2066 llvm::Value *Receiver,
2067 bool IsClassMessage,
2068 const CodeGen::CallArgList &CallArgs,
2069 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
2070 // Create and init a super structure; this is a (receiver, class)
2071 // pair we will pass to objc_msgSendSuper.
2072 Address ObjCSuper =
2073 CGF.CreateTempAlloca(ObjCTypes.SuperTy, CGF.getPointerAlign(),
2074 "objc_super");
2075 llvm::Value *ReceiverAsObject =
2076 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Receiver, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
2077 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(ReceiverAsObject,
2078 CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCSuper, 0));
2079
2080 // If this is a class message the metaclass is passed as the target.
2081 llvm::Value *Target;
2082 if (IsClassMessage) {
2083 if (isCategoryImpl) {
2084 // Message sent to 'super' in a class method defined in a category
2085 // implementation requires an odd treatment.
2086 // If we are in a class method, we must retrieve the
2087 // _metaclass_ for the current class, pointed at by
2088 // the class's "isa" pointer. The following assumes that
2089 // isa" is the first ivar in a class (which it must be).
2090 Target = EmitClassRef(CGF, Class->getSuperClass());
2091 Target = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCTypes.ClassTy, Target, 0);
2092 Target = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Target, CGF.getPointerAlign());
2093 } else {
2094 llvm::Constant *MetaClassPtr = EmitMetaClassRef(Class);
2095 llvm::Value *SuperPtr =
2096 CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCTypes.ClassTy, MetaClassPtr, 1);
2097 llvm::Value *Super =
2098 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(SuperPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign());
2099 Target = Super;
2100 }
2101 } else if (isCategoryImpl)
2102 Target = EmitClassRef(CGF, Class->getSuperClass());
2103 else {
2104 llvm::Value *ClassPtr = EmitSuperClassRef(Class);
2105 ClassPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCTypes.ClassTy, ClassPtr, 1);
2106 Target = CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(ClassPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign());
2107 }
2108 // FIXME: We shouldn't need to do this cast, rectify the ASTContext and
2109 // ObjCTypes types.
2110 llvm::Type *ClassTy =
2111 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getObjCClassType());
2112 Target = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Target, ClassTy);
2113 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Target, CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCSuper, 1));
2114 return EmitMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType,
2115 EmitSelector(CGF, Sel),
2116 ObjCSuper.getPointer(), ObjCTypes.SuperPtrCTy,
2117 true, CallArgs, Method, Class, ObjCTypes);
2118}

2120/// Generate code for a message send expression.
2121CodeGen::RValue CGObjCMac::GenerateMessageSend(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2122 ReturnValueSlot Return,
2123 QualType ResultType,
2124 Selector Sel,
2125 llvm::Value *Receiver,
2126 const CallArgList &CallArgs,
2127 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class,
2128 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
2129 return EmitMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType,
2130 EmitSelector(CGF, Sel),
2131 Receiver, CGF.getContext().getObjCIdType(),
2132 false, CallArgs, Method, Class, ObjCTypes);
2133}
2134
2135static bool isWeakLinkedClass(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
2136 do {
2137 if (ID->isWeakImported())
2138 return true;
2139 } while ((ID = ID->getSuperClass()));
2140
2141 return false;
2142}
2143
2144CodeGen::RValue
2145CGObjCCommonMac::EmitMessageSend(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2146 ReturnValueSlot Return,
2147 QualType ResultType,
2148 llvm::Value *Sel,
2149 llvm::Value *Arg0,
2150 QualType Arg0Ty,
2151 bool IsSuper,
2152 const CallArgList &CallArgs,
2153 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method,
2154 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ClassReceiver,
2155 const ObjCCommonTypesHelper &ObjCTypes) {
2156 CallArgList ActualArgs;
2157 if (!IsSuper)
2158 Arg0 = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg0, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
2159 ActualArgs.add(RValue::get(Arg0), Arg0Ty);
2160 ActualArgs.add(RValue::get(Sel), CGF.getContext().getObjCSelType());
2161 ActualArgs.addFrom(CallArgs);
2162
2163 // If we're calling a method, use the formal signature.
2164 MessageSendInfo MSI = getMessageSendInfo(Method, ResultType, ActualArgs);
2165
2166 if (Method)
2167 assert(CGM.getContext().getCanonicalType(Method->getReturnType()) ==
2168 CGM.getContext().getCanonicalType(ResultType) &&
2169 "Result type mismatch!");
2170
2171 bool ReceiverCanBeNull = true;
2172
2173 // Super dispatch assumes that self is non-null; even the messenger
2174 // doesn't have a null check internally.
2175 if (IsSuper) {
2176 ReceiverCanBeNull = false;
2177
2178 // If this is a direct dispatch of a class method, check whether the class,
2179 // or anything in its hierarchy, was weak-linked.
2180 } else if (ClassReceiver && Method && Method->isClassMethod()) {
2181 ReceiverCanBeNull = isWeakLinkedClass(ClassReceiver);
2182
2183 // If we're emitting a method, and self is const (meaning just ARC, for now),
2184 // and the receiver is a load of self, then self is a valid object.
2185 } else if (auto CurMethod =
2186 dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMethodDecl>(CGF.CurCodeDecl)) {
2187 auto Self = CurMethod->getSelfDecl();
2188 if (Self->getType().isConstQualified()) {
2189 if (auto LI = dyn_cast<llvm::LoadInst>(Arg0->stripPointerCasts())) {
2190 llvm::Value *SelfAddr = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(Self).getPointer();
2191 if (SelfAddr == LI->getPointerOperand()) {
2192 ReceiverCanBeNull = false;
2193 }
2194 }
2195 }
2196 }
2197
2198 bool RequiresNullCheck = false;
2199
2200 llvm::FunctionCallee Fn = nullptr;
2201 if (CGM.ReturnSlotInterferesWithArgs(MSI.CallInfo)) {
2202 if (ReceiverCanBeNull) RequiresNullCheck = true;
2203 Fn = (ObjCABI == 2) ? ObjCTypes.getSendStretFn2(IsSuper)
2204 : ObjCTypes.getSendStretFn(IsSuper);
2205 } else if (CGM.ReturnTypeUsesFPRet(ResultType)) {
2206 Fn = (ObjCABI == 2) ? ObjCTypes.getSendFpretFn2(IsSuper)
2207 : ObjCTypes.getSendFpretFn(IsSuper);
2208 } else if (CGM.ReturnTypeUsesFP2Ret(ResultType)) {
2209 Fn = (ObjCABI == 2) ? ObjCTypes.getSendFp2RetFn2(IsSuper)
2210 : ObjCTypes.getSendFp2retFn(IsSuper);
2211 } else {
2212 // arm64 uses objc_msgSend for stret methods and yet null receiver check
2213 // must be made for it.
2214 if (ReceiverCanBeNull && CGM.ReturnTypeUsesSRet(MSI.CallInfo))
2215 RequiresNullCheck = true;
2216 Fn = (ObjCABI == 2) ? ObjCTypes.getSendFn2(IsSuper)
2217 : ObjCTypes.getSendFn(IsSuper);
2218 }
2219
2220 // Cast function to proper signature
2221 llvm::Constant *BitcastFn = cast<llvm::Constant>(
2222 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Fn.getCallee(), MSI.MessengerType));
2223
2224 // We don't need to emit a null check to zero out an indirect result if the
2225 // result is ignored.
2226 if (Return.isUnused())
2227 RequiresNullCheck = false;
2228
2229 // Emit a null-check if there's a consumed argument other than the receiver.
2230 if (!RequiresNullCheck && CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount && Method) {
2231 for (const auto *ParamDecl : Method->parameters()) {
2232 if (ParamDecl->hasAttr<NSConsumedAttr>()) {
2233 RequiresNullCheck = true;
2234 break;
2235 }
2236 }
2237 }
2238
2239 NullReturnState nullReturn;
2240 if (RequiresNullCheck) {
2241 nullReturn.init(CGF, Arg0);
2242 }
2243
2244 llvm::CallBase *CallSite;
2245 CGCallee Callee = CGCallee::forDirect(BitcastFn);
2246 RValue rvalue = CGF.EmitCall(MSI.CallInfo, Callee, Return, ActualArgs,
2247 &CallSite);
2248
2249 // Mark the call as noreturn if the method is marked noreturn and the
2250 // receiver cannot be null.
2251 if (Method && Method->hasAttr<NoReturnAttr>() && !ReceiverCanBeNull) {
2252 CallSite->setDoesNotReturn();
2253 }
2254
2255 return nullReturn.complete(CGF, Return, rvalue, ResultType, CallArgs,
2256 RequiresNullCheck ? Method : nullptr);
2257}
2258
2259static Qualifiers::GC GetGCAttrTypeForType(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType FQT,
2260 bool pointee = false) {
2261 // Note that GC qualification applies recursively to C pointer types
2262 // that aren't otherwise decorated. This is weird, but it's probably
2263 // an intentional workaround to the unreliable placement of GC qualifiers.
2264 if (FQT.isObjCGCStrong())
2265 return Qualifiers::Strong;
2266
2267 if (FQT.isObjCGCWeak())
2268 return Qualifiers::Weak;
2269
2270 if (auto ownership = FQT.getObjCLifetime()) {
2271 // Ownership does not apply recursively to C pointer types.
2272 if (pointee) return Qualifiers::GCNone;
2273 switch (ownership) {
2274 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak: return Qualifiers::Weak;
2275 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong: return Qualifiers::Strong;
2276 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone: return Qualifiers::GCNone;
2277 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing: llvm_unreachable("autoreleasing ivar?");
2278 case Qualifiers::OCL_None: llvm_unreachable("known nonzero");
2279 }
2280 llvm_unreachable("bad objc ownership");
2281 }
2282
2283 // Treat unqualified retainable pointers as strong.
2284 if (FQT->isObjCObjectPointerType() || FQT->isBlockPointerType())
2285 return Qualifiers::Strong;
2286
2287 // Walk into C pointer types, but only in GC.
2288 if (Ctx.getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC) {
2289 if (const PointerType *PT = FQT->getAs<PointerType>())
2290 return GetGCAttrTypeForType(Ctx, PT->getPointeeType(), /*pointee*/ true);
2291 }
2292
2293 return Qualifiers::GCNone;
2294}

2296namespace {
2297 struct IvarInfo {
2298 CharUnits Offset;
2299 uint64_t SizeInWords;
2300 IvarInfo(CharUnits offset, uint64_t sizeInWords)
2301 : Offset(offset), SizeInWords(sizeInWords) {}
2302
2303 // Allow sorting based on byte pos.
2304 bool operator<(const IvarInfo &other) const {
2305 return Offset < other.Offset;
2306 }
2307 };
2308
2309 /// A helper class for building GC layout strings.
2310 class IvarLayoutBuilder {
2311 CodeGenModule &CGM;
2312
2313 /// The start of the layout. Offsets will be relative to this value,
2314 /// and entries less than this value will be silently discarded.
2315 CharUnits InstanceBegin;
2316
2317 /// The end of the layout. Offsets will never exceed this value.
2318 CharUnits InstanceEnd;
2319
2320 /// Whether we're generating the strong layout or the weak layout.
2321 bool ForStrongLayout;
2322
2323 /// Whether the offsets in IvarsInfo might be out-of-order.
2324 bool IsDisordered = false;
2325
2326 llvm::SmallVector<IvarInfo, 8> IvarsInfo;
2327
2328 public:
2329 IvarLayoutBuilder(CodeGenModule &CGM, CharUnits instanceBegin,
2330 CharUnits instanceEnd, bool forStrongLayout)
2331 : CGM(CGM), InstanceBegin(instanceBegin), InstanceEnd(instanceEnd),
2332 ForStrongLayout(forStrongLayout) {
2333 }
2334
2335 void visitRecord(const RecordType *RT, CharUnits offset);
2336
2337 template <class Iterator, class GetOffsetFn>
2338 void visitAggregate(Iterator begin, Iterator end,
2339 CharUnits aggrOffset,
2340 const GetOffsetFn &getOffset);
2341
2342 void visitField(const FieldDecl *field, CharUnits offset);
2343
2344 /// Add the layout of a block implementation.
2345 void visitBlock(const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo);
2346
2347 /// Is there any information for an interesting bitmap?
2348 bool hasBitmapData() const { return !IvarsInfo.empty(); }
2349
2350 llvm::Constant *buildBitmap(CGObjCCommonMac &CGObjC,
2351 llvm::SmallVectorImpl<unsigned char> &buffer);
2352
2353 static void dump(ArrayRef<unsigned char> buffer) {
2354 const unsigned char *s = buffer.data();
2355 for (unsigned i = 0, e = buffer.size(); i < e; i++)
2356 if (!(s[i] & 0xf0))
2357 printf("0x0%x%s", s[i], s[i] != 0 ? ", " : "");
2358 else
2359 printf("0x%x%s", s[i], s[i] != 0 ? ", " : "");
2360 printf("\n");
2361 }
2362 };
2363} // end anonymous namespace
2364
2365llvm::Constant *CGObjCCommonMac::BuildGCBlockLayout(CodeGenModule &CGM,
2366 const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo) {
2367
2368 llvm::Constant *nullPtr = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
2369 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC)
2370 return nullPtr;
2371
2372 IvarLayoutBuilder builder(CGM, CharUnits::Zero(), blockInfo.BlockSize,
2373 /*for strong layout*/ true);
2374
2375 builder.visitBlock(blockInfo);
2376
2377 if (!builder.hasBitmapData())
2378 return nullPtr;
2379
2380 llvm::SmallVector<unsigned char, 32> buffer;
2381 llvm::Constant *C = builder.buildBitmap(*this, buffer);
2382 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCGCBitmapPrint && !buffer.empty()) {
2383 printf("\n block variable layout for block: ");
2384 builder.dump(buffer);
2385 }
2386
2387 return C;
2388}
2389
2390void IvarLayoutBuilder::visitBlock(const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo) {
2391 // __isa is the first field in block descriptor and must assume by runtime's
2392 // convention that it is GC'able.
2393 IvarsInfo.push_back(IvarInfo(CharUnits::Zero(), 1));
2394
2395 const BlockDecl *blockDecl = blockInfo.getBlockDecl();
2396
2397 // Ignore the optional 'this' capture: C++ objects are not assumed
2398 // to be GC'ed.
2399
2400 CharUnits lastFieldOffset;
2401
2402 // Walk the captured variables.
2403 for (const auto &CI : blockDecl->captures()) {
2404 const VarDecl *variable = CI.getVariable();
2405 QualType type = variable->getType();
2406
2407 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &capture = blockInfo.getCapture(variable);
2408
2409 // Ignore constant captures.
2410 if (capture.isConstant()) continue;
2411
2412 CharUnits fieldOffset = capture.getOffset();
2413
2414 // Block fields are not necessarily ordered; if we detect that we're
2415 // adding them out-of-order, make sure we sort later.
2416 if (fieldOffset < lastFieldOffset)
2417 IsDisordered = true;
2418 lastFieldOffset = fieldOffset;
2419
2420 // __block variables are passed by their descriptor address.
2421 if (CI.isByRef()) {
2422 IvarsInfo.push_back(IvarInfo(fieldOffset, /*size in words*/ 1));
2423 continue;
2424 }
2425
2426 assert(!type->isArrayType() && "array variable should not be caught");
2427 if (const RecordType *record = type->getAs<RecordType>()) {
2428 visitRecord(record, fieldOffset);
2429 continue;
2430 }
2431
2432 Qualifiers::GC GCAttr = GetGCAttrTypeForType(CGM.getContext(), type);
2433
2434 if (GCAttr == Qualifiers::Strong) {
2435 assert(CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(type)
2436 == CGM.getTarget().getPointerWidth(0));
2437 IvarsInfo.push_back(IvarInfo(fieldOffset, /*size in words*/ 1));
2438 }
2439 }
2440}
2441
2442/// getBlockCaptureLifetime - This routine returns life time of the captured
2443/// block variable for the purpose of block layout meta-data generation. FQT is
2444/// the type of the variable captured in the block.
2445Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime CGObjCCommonMac::getBlockCaptureLifetime(QualType FQT,
2446 bool ByrefLayout) {
2447 // If it has an ownership qualifier, we're done.
2448 if (auto lifetime = FQT.getObjCLifetime())
2449 return lifetime;
2450
2451 // If it doesn't, and this is ARC, it has no ownership.
2452 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
2453 return Qualifiers::OCL_None;
2454
2455 // In MRC, retainable pointers are owned by non-__block variables.
2456 if (FQT->isObjCObjectPointerType() || FQT->isBlockPointerType())
2457 return ByrefLayout ? Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone : Qualifiers::OCL_Strong;
2458
2459 return Qualifiers::OCL_None;
2460}
2461
2462void CGObjCCommonMac::UpdateRunSkipBlockVars(bool IsByref,
2463 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime LifeTime,
2464 CharUnits FieldOffset,
2465 CharUnits FieldSize) {
2466 // __block variables are passed by their descriptor address.
2467 if (IsByref)
2468 RunSkipBlockVars.push_back(RUN_SKIP(BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF, FieldOffset,
2469 FieldSize));
2470 else if (LifeTime == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong)
2471 RunSkipBlockVars.push_back(RUN_SKIP(BLOCK_LAYOUT_STRONG, FieldOffset,
2472 FieldSize));
2473 else if (LifeTime == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak)
2474 RunSkipBlockVars.push_back(RUN_SKIP(BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK, FieldOffset,
2475 FieldSize));
2476 else if (LifeTime == Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone)
2477 RunSkipBlockVars.push_back(RUN_SKIP(BLOCK_LAYOUT_UNRETAINED, FieldOffset,
2478 FieldSize));
2479 else
2480 RunSkipBlockVars.push_back(RUN_SKIP(BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_BYTES,
2481 FieldOffset,
2482 FieldSize));
2483}
2484
2485void CGObjCCommonMac::BuildRCRecordLayout(const llvm::StructLayout *RecLayout,
2486 const RecordDecl *RD,
2487 ArrayRef<const FieldDecl*> RecFields,
2488 CharUnits BytePos, bool &HasUnion,
2489 bool ByrefLayout) {
2490 bool IsUnion = (RD && RD->isUnion());
2491 CharUnits MaxUnionSize = CharUnits::Zero();
2492 const FieldDecl *MaxField = nullptr;
2493 const FieldDecl *LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed = nullptr;
2494 CharUnits MaxFieldOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
2495 CharUnits LastBitfieldOrUnnamedOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
2496
2497 if (RecFields.empty())
2498 return;
2499 unsigned ByteSizeInBits = CGM.getTarget().getCharWidth();
2500
2501 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RecFields.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2502 const FieldDecl *Field = RecFields[i];
2503 // Note that 'i' here is actually the field index inside RD of Field,
2504 // although this dependency is hidden.
2505 const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2506 CharUnits FieldOffset =
2507 CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(RL.getFieldOffset(i));
2508
2509 // Skip over unnamed or bitfields
2510 if (!Field->getIdentifier() || Field->isBitField()) {
2511 LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed = Field;
2512 LastBitfieldOrUnnamedOffset = FieldOffset;
2513 continue;
2514 }
2515
2516 LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed = nullptr;
2517 QualType FQT = Field->getType();
2518 if (FQT->isRecordType() || FQT->isUnionType()) {
2519 if (FQT->isUnionType())
2520 HasUnion = true;
2521
2522 BuildRCBlockVarRecordLayout(FQT->getAs<RecordType>(),
2523 BytePos + FieldOffset, HasUnion);
2524 continue;
2525 }
2526
2527 if (const ArrayType *Array = CGM.getContext().getAsArrayType(FQT)) {
2528 const ConstantArrayType *CArray =
2529 dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantArrayType>(Array);
2530 uint64_t ElCount = CArray->getSize().getZExtValue();
2531 assert(CArray && "only array with known element size is supported");
2532 FQT = CArray->getElementType();
2533 while (const ArrayType *Array = CGM.getContext().getAsArrayType(FQT)) {
2534 const ConstantArrayType *CArray =
2535 dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantArrayType>(Array);
2536 ElCount *= CArray->getSize().getZExtValue();
2537 FQT = CArray->getElementType();
2538 }
2539 if (FQT->isRecordType() && ElCount) {
2540 int OldIndex = RunSkipBlockVars.size() - 1;
2541 const RecordType *RT = FQT->getAs<RecordType>();
2542 BuildRCBlockVarRecordLayout(RT, BytePos + FieldOffset,
2543 HasUnion);
2544
2545 // Replicate layout information for each array element. Note that
2546 // one element is already done.
2547 uint64_t ElIx = 1;
2548 for (int FirstIndex = RunSkipBlockVars.size() - 1 ;ElIx < ElCount; ElIx++) {
2549 CharUnits Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(RT);
2550 for (int i = OldIndex+1; i <= FirstIndex; ++i)
2551 RunSkipBlockVars.push_back(
2552 RUN_SKIP(RunSkipBlockVars[i].opcode,
2553 RunSkipBlockVars[i].block_var_bytepos + Size*ElIx,
2554 RunSkipBlockVars[i].block_var_size));
2555 }
2556 continue;
2557 }
2558 }
2559 CharUnits FieldSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(Field->getType());
2560 if (IsUnion) {
2561 CharUnits UnionIvarSize = FieldSize;
2562 if (UnionIvarSize > MaxUnionSize) {
2563 MaxUnionSize = UnionIvarSize;
2564 MaxField = Field;
2565 MaxFieldOffset = FieldOffset;
2566 }
2567 } else {
2568 UpdateRunSkipBlockVars(false,
2569 getBlockCaptureLifetime(FQT, ByrefLayout),
2570 BytePos + FieldOffset,
2571 FieldSize);
2572 }
2573 }
2574
2575 if (LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed) {
2576 if (LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed->isBitField()) {
2577 // Last field was a bitfield. Must update the info.
2578 uint64_t BitFieldSize
2579 = LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed->getBitWidthValue(CGM.getContext());
2580 unsigned UnsSize = (BitFieldSize / ByteSizeInBits) +
2581 ((BitFieldSize % ByteSizeInBits) != 0);
2582 CharUnits Size = CharUnits::fromQuantity(UnsSize);
2583 Size += LastBitfieldOrUnnamedOffset;
2584 UpdateRunSkipBlockVars(false,
2585 getBlockCaptureLifetime(LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed->getType(),
2586 ByrefLayout),
2587 BytePos + LastBitfieldOrUnnamedOffset,
2588 Size);
2589 } else {
2590 assert(!LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed->getIdentifier() &&"Expected unnamed");
2591 // Last field was unnamed. Must update skip info.
2592 CharUnits FieldSize
2593 = CGM.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed->getType());
2594 UpdateRunSkipBlockVars(false,
2595 getBlockCaptureLifetime(LastFieldBitfieldOrUnnamed->getType(),
2596 ByrefLayout),
2597 BytePos + LastBitfieldOrUnnamedOffset,
2598 FieldSize);
2599 }
2600 }
2601
2602 if (MaxField)
2603 UpdateRunSkipBlockVars(false,
2604 getBlockCaptureLifetime(MaxField->getType(), ByrefLayout),
2605 BytePos + MaxFieldOffset,
2606 MaxUnionSize);
2607}
2608
2609void CGObjCCommonMac::BuildRCBlockVarRecordLayout(const RecordType *RT,
2610 CharUnits BytePos,
2611 bool &HasUnion,
2612 bool ByrefLayout) {
2613 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
2614 SmallVector<const FieldDecl*, 16> Fields(RD->fields());
2615 llvm::Type *Ty = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(QualType(RT, 0));
2616 const llvm::StructLayout *RecLayout =
2617 CGM.getDataLayout().getStructLayout(cast<llvm::StructType>(Ty));
2618
2619 BuildRCRecordLayout(RecLayout, RD, Fields, BytePos, HasUnion, ByrefLayout);
2620}
2621
2622/// InlineLayoutInstruction - This routine produce an inline instruction for the
2623/// block variable layout if it can. If not, it returns 0. Rules are as follow:
2624/// If ((uintptr_t) layout) < (1 << 12), the layout is inline. In the 64bit world,
2625/// an inline layout of value 0x0000000000000xyz is interpreted as follows:
2626/// x captured object pointers of BLOCK_LAYOUT_STRONG. Followed by
2627/// y captured object of BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF. Followed by
2628/// z captured object of BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK. If any of the above is missing, zero
2629/// replaces it. For example, 0x00000x00 means x BLOCK_LAYOUT_STRONG and no
2630/// BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF and no BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK objects are captured.
2631uint64_t CGObjCCommonMac::InlineLayoutInstruction(
2632 SmallVectorImpl<unsigned char> &Layout) {
2633 uint64_t Result = 0;
2634 if (Layout.size() <= 3) {
2635 unsigned size = Layout.size();
2636 unsigned strong_word_count = 0, byref_word_count=0, weak_word_count=0;
2637 unsigned char inst;
2638 enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE opcode ;
2639 switch (size) {
2640 case 3:
2641 inst = Layout[0];
2642 opcode = (enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE) (inst >> 4);
2643 if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_STRONG)
2644 strong_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2645 else
2646 return 0;
2647 inst = Layout[1];
2648 opcode = (enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE) (inst >> 4);
2649 if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF)
2650 byref_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2651 else
2652 return 0;
2653 inst = Layout[2];
2654 opcode = (enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE) (inst >> 4);
2655 if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK)
2656 weak_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2657 else
2658 return 0;
2659 break;
2660
2661 case 2:
2662 inst = Layout[0];
2663 opcode = (enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE) (inst >> 4);
2664 if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_STRONG) {
2665 strong_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2666 inst = Layout[1];
2667 opcode = (enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE) (inst >> 4);
2668 if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF)
2669 byref_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2670 else if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK)
2671 weak_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2672 else
2673 return 0;
2674 }
2675 else if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF) {
2676 byref_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2677 inst = Layout[1];
2678 opcode = (enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE) (inst >> 4);
2679 if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK)
2680 weak_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2681 else
2682 return 0;
2683 }
2684 else
2685 return 0;
2686 break;
2687
2688 case 1:
2689 inst = Layout[0];
2690 opcode = (enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE) (inst >> 4);
2691 if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_STRONG)
2692 strong_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2693 else if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF)
2694 byref_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2695 else if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK)
2696 weak_word_count = (inst & 0xF)+1;
2697 else
2698 return 0;
2699 break;
2700
2701 default:
2702 return 0;
2703 }
2704
2705 // Cannot inline when any of the word counts is 15. Because this is one less
2706 // than the actual work count (so 15 means 16 actual word counts),
2707 // and we can only display 0 thru 15 word counts.
2708 if (strong_word_count == 16 || byref_word_count == 16 || weak_word_count == 16)
2709 return 0;
2710
2711 unsigned count =
2712 (strong_word_count != 0) + (byref_word_count != 0) + (weak_word_count != 0);
2713
2714 if (size == count) {
2715 if (strong_word_count)
2716 Result = strong_word_count;
2717 Result <<= 4;
2718 if (byref_word_count)
2719 Result += byref_word_count;
2720 Result <<= 4;
2721 if (weak_word_count)
2722 Result += weak_word_count;
2723 }
2724 }
2725 return Result;
2726}
2727
2728llvm::Constant *CGObjCCommonMac::getBitmapBlockLayout(bool ComputeByrefLayout) {
2729 llvm::Constant *nullPtr = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
2730 if (RunSkipBlockVars.empty())
2731 return nullPtr;
2732 unsigned WordSizeInBits = CGM.getTarget().getPointerWidth(0);
2733 unsigned ByteSizeInBits = CGM.getTarget().getCharWidth();
2734 unsigned WordSizeInBytes = WordSizeInBits/ByteSizeInBits;
2735
2736 // Sort on byte position; captures might not be allocated in order,
2737 // and unions can do funny things.
2738 llvm::array_pod_sort(RunSkipBlockVars.begin(), RunSkipBlockVars.end());
2739 SmallVector<unsigned char, 16> Layout;
2740
2741 unsigned size = RunSkipBlockVars.size();
2742 for (unsigned i = 0; i < size; i++) {
2743 enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE opcode = RunSkipBlockVars[i].opcode;
2744 CharUnits start_byte_pos = RunSkipBlockVars[i].block_var_bytepos;
2745 CharUnits end_byte_pos = start_byte_pos;
2746 unsigned j = i+1;
2747 while (j < size) {
2748 if (opcode == RunSkipBlockVars[j].opcode) {
2749 end_byte_pos = RunSkipBlockVars[j++].block_var_bytepos;
2750 i++;
2751 }
2752 else
2753 break;
2754 }
2755 CharUnits size_in_bytes =
2756 end_byte_pos - start_byte_pos + RunSkipBlockVars[j-1].block_var_size;
2757 if (j < size) {
2758 CharUnits gap =
2759 RunSkipBlockVars[j].block_var_bytepos -
2760 RunSkipBlockVars[j-1].block_var_bytepos - RunSkipBlockVars[j-1].block_var_size;
2761 size_in_bytes += gap;
2762 }
2763 CharUnits residue_in_bytes = CharUnits::Zero();
2764 if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_BYTES) {
2765 residue_in_bytes = size_in_bytes % WordSizeInBytes;
2766 size_in_bytes -= residue_in_bytes;
2767 opcode = BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_WORDS;
2768 }
2769
2770 unsigned size_in_words = size_in_bytes.getQuantity() / WordSizeInBytes;
2771 while (size_in_words >= 16) {
2772 // Note that value in imm. is one less that the actual
2773 // value. So, 0xf means 16 words follow!
2774 unsigned char inst = (opcode << 4) | 0xf;
2775 Layout.push_back(inst);
2776 size_in_words -= 16;
2777 }
2778 if (size_in_words > 0) {
2779 // Note that value in imm. is one less that the actual
2780 // value. So, we subtract 1 away!
2781 unsigned char inst = (opcode << 4) | (size_in_words-1);
2782 Layout.push_back(inst);
2783 }
2784 if (residue_in_bytes > CharUnits::Zero()) {
2785 unsigned char inst =
2786 (BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_BYTES << 4) | (residue_in_bytes.getQuantity()-1);
2787 Layout.push_back(inst);
2788 }
2789 }
2790
2791 while (!Layout.empty()) {
2792 unsigned char inst = Layout.back();
2793 enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE opcode = (enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE) (inst >> 4);
2794 if (opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_BYTES || opcode == BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_WORDS)
2795 Layout.pop_back();
2796 else
2797 break;
2798 }
2799
2800 uint64_t Result = InlineLayoutInstruction(Layout);
2801 if (Result != 0) {
2802 // Block variable layout instruction has been inlined.
2803 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCGCBitmapPrint) {
2804 if (ComputeByrefLayout)
2805 printf("\n Inline BYREF variable layout: ");
2806 else
2807 printf("\n Inline block variable layout: ");
2808 printf("0x0%" PRIx64 "", Result);
2809 if (auto numStrong = (Result & 0xF00) >> 8)
2810 printf(", BL_STRONG:%d", (int) numStrong);
2811 if (auto numByref = (Result & 0x0F0) >> 4)
2812 printf(", BL_BYREF:%d", (int) numByref);
2813 if (auto numWeak = (Result & 0x00F) >> 0)
2814 printf(", BL_WEAK:%d", (int) numWeak);
2815 printf(", BL_OPERATOR:0\n");
2816 }
2817 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntPtrTy, Result);
2818 }
2819
2820 unsigned char inst = (BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPERATOR << 4) | 0;
2821 Layout.push_back(inst);
2822 std::string BitMap;
2823 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Layout.size(); i != e; i++)
2824 BitMap += Layout[i];
2825
2826 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCGCBitmapPrint) {
2827 if (ComputeByrefLayout)
2828 printf("\n Byref variable layout: ");
2829 else
2830 printf("\n Block variable layout: ");
2831 for (unsigned i = 0, e = BitMap.size(); i != e; i++) {
2832 unsigned char inst = BitMap[i];
2833 enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE opcode = (enum BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPCODE) (inst >> 4);
2834 unsigned delta = 1;
2835 switch (opcode) {
2836 case BLOCK_LAYOUT_OPERATOR:
2837 printf("BL_OPERATOR:");
2838 delta = 0;
2839 break;
2840 case BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_BYTES:
2841 printf("BL_NON_OBJECT_BYTES:");
2842 break;
2843 case BLOCK_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT_WORDS:
2844 printf("BL_NON_OBJECT_WORD:");
2845 break;
2846 case BLOCK_LAYOUT_STRONG:
2847 printf("BL_STRONG:");
2848 break;
2849 case BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF:
2850 printf("BL_BYREF:");
2851 break;
2852 case BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK:
2853 printf("BL_WEAK:");
2854 break;
2855 case BLOCK_LAYOUT_UNRETAINED:
2856 printf("BL_UNRETAINED:");
2857 break;
2858 }
2859 // Actual value of word count is one more that what is in the imm.
2860 // field of the instruction
2861 printf("%d", (inst & 0xf) + delta);
2862 if (i < e-1)
2863 printf(", ");
2864 else
2865 printf("\n");
2866 }
2867 }
2868
2869 auto *Entry = CreateCStringLiteral(BitMap, ObjCLabelType::ClassName,
2870 /*ForceNonFragileABI=*/true,
2871 /*NullTerminate=*/false);
2872 return getConstantGEP(VMContext, Entry, 0, 0);
2873}
2874
2875static std::string getBlockLayoutInfoString(
2876 const SmallVectorImpl<CGObjCCommonMac::RUN_SKIP> &RunSkipBlockVars,
2877 bool HasCopyDisposeHelpers) {
2878 std::string Str;
2879 for (const CGObjCCommonMac::RUN_SKIP &R : RunSkipBlockVars) {
2880 if (R.opcode == CGObjCCommonMac::BLOCK_LAYOUT_UNRETAINED) {
2881 // Copy/dispose helpers don't have any information about
2882 // __unsafe_unretained captures, so unconditionally concatenate a string.
2883 Str += "u";
2884 } else if (HasCopyDisposeHelpers) {
2885 // Information about __strong, __weak, or byref captures has already been
2886 // encoded into the names of the copy/dispose helpers. We have to add a
2887 // string here only when the copy/dispose helpers aren't generated (which
2888 // happens when the block is non-escaping).
2889 continue;
2890 } else {
2891 switch (R.opcode) {
2892 case CGObjCCommonMac::BLOCK_LAYOUT_STRONG:
2893 Str += "s";
2894 break;
2895 case CGObjCCommonMac::BLOCK_LAYOUT_BYREF:
2896 Str += "r";
2897 break;
2898 case CGObjCCommonMac::BLOCK_LAYOUT_WEAK:
2899 Str += "w";
2900 break;
2901 default:
2902 continue;
2903 }
2904 }
2905 Str += llvm::to_string(R.block_var_bytepos.getQuantity());
2906 Str += "l" + llvm::to_string(R.block_var_size.getQuantity());
2907 }
2908 return Str;
2909}
2910
2911void CGObjCCommonMac::fillRunSkipBlockVars(CodeGenModule &CGM,
2912 const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo) {
2913 assert(CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC);
2914
2915 RunSkipBlockVars.clear();
2916 bool hasUnion = false;
2917
2918 unsigned WordSizeInBits = CGM.getTarget().getPointerWidth(0);
2919 unsigned ByteSizeInBits = CGM.getTarget().getCharWidth();
2920 unsigned WordSizeInBytes = WordSizeInBits/ByteSizeInBits;
2921
2922 const BlockDecl *blockDecl = blockInfo.getBlockDecl();
2923
2924 // Calculate the basic layout of the block structure.
2925 const llvm::StructLayout *layout =
2926 CGM.getDataLayout().getStructLayout(blockInfo.StructureType);
2927
2928 // Ignore the optional 'this' capture: C++ objects are not assumed
2929 // to be GC'ed.
2930 if (blockInfo.BlockHeaderForcedGapSize != CharUnits::Zero())
2931 UpdateRunSkipBlockVars(false, Qualifiers::OCL_None,
2932 blockInfo.BlockHeaderForcedGapOffset,
2933 blockInfo.BlockHeaderForcedGapSize);
2934 // Walk the captured variables.
2935 for (const auto &CI : blockDecl->captures()) {
2936 const VarDecl *variable = CI.getVariable();
2937 QualType type = variable->getType();
2938
2939 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &capture = blockInfo.getCapture(variable);
2940
2941 // Ignore constant captures.
2942 if (capture.isConstant()) continue;
2943
2944 CharUnits fieldOffset =
2945 CharUnits::fromQuantity(layout->getElementOffset(capture.getIndex()));
2946
2947 assert(!type->isArrayType() && "array variable should not be caught");
2948 if (!CI.isByRef())
2949 if (const RecordType *record = type->getAs<RecordType>()) {
2950 BuildRCBlockVarRecordLayout(record, fieldOffset, hasUnion);
2951 continue;
2952 }
2953 CharUnits fieldSize;
2954 if (CI.isByRef())
2955 fieldSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(WordSizeInBytes);
2956 else
2957 fieldSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(type);
2958 UpdateRunSkipBlockVars(CI.isByRef(), getBlockCaptureLifetime(type, false),
2959 fieldOffset, fieldSize);
2960 }
2961}
2962
2963llvm::Constant *
2964CGObjCCommonMac::BuildRCBlockLayout(CodeGenModule &CGM,
2965 const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo) {
2966 fillRunSkipBlockVars(CGM, blockInfo);
2967 return getBitmapBlockLayout(false);
2968}
2969
2970std::string CGObjCCommonMac::getRCBlockLayoutStr(CodeGenModule &CGM,
2971 const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo) {
2972 fillRunSkipBlockVars(CGM, blockInfo);
2973 return getBlockLayoutInfoString(RunSkipBlockVars,
2974 blockInfo.needsCopyDisposeHelpers());
2975}

2977llvm::Constant *CGObjCCommonMac::BuildByrefLayout(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
2978 QualType T) {
2979 assert(CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC);
2980 assert(!T->isArrayType() && "__block array variable should not be caught");
2981 CharUnits fieldOffset;
2982 RunSkipBlockVars.clear();
2983 bool hasUnion = false;
2984 if (const RecordType *record = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
2985 BuildRCBlockVarRecordLayout(record, fieldOffset, hasUnion, true /*ByrefLayout */);
2986 llvm::Constant *Result = getBitmapBlockLayout(true);
2987 if (isa<llvm::ConstantInt>(Result))
2988 Result = llvm::ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(Result, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
2989 return Result;
2990 }
2991 llvm::Constant *nullPtr = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
2992 return nullPtr;
2993}

2999 LazySymbols.insert(&CGM.getContext().Idents.get("Protocol"));
3000

3005void CGObjCCommonMac::GenerateProtocol(const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
3006 // FIXME: We shouldn't need this, the protocol decl should contain enough
3007 // information to tell us whether this was a declaration or a definition.
3008 DefinedProtocols.insert(PD->getIdentifier());
3009
3010 // If we have generated a forward reference to this protocol, emit
3011 // it now. Otherwise do nothing, the protocol objects are lazily
3012 // emitted.
3013 if (Protocols.count(PD->getIdentifier()))
3014 GetOrEmitProtocol(PD);

3016
3017llvm::Constant *CGObjCCommonMac::GetProtocolRef(const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
3018 if (DefinedProtocols.count(PD->getIdentifier()))
3019 return GetOrEmitProtocol(PD);
3020
3021 return GetOrEmitProtocolRef(PD);
3022}
3023
3024llvm::Value *CGObjCCommonMac::EmitClassRefViaRuntime(
3025 CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3026 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
3027 ObjCCommonTypesHelper &ObjCTypes) {
3028 llvm::FunctionCallee lookUpClassFn = ObjCTypes.getLookUpClassFn();
3029
3030 llvm::Value *className =
3031 CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString())
3032 .getPointer();
3033 ASTContext &ctx = CGF.CGM.getContext();
3034 className =
3035 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(className,
3036 CGF.ConvertType(
3037 ctx.getPointerType(ctx.CharTy.withConst())));
3038 llvm::CallInst *call = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(lookUpClassFn, className);
3039 call->setDoesNotThrow();
3040 return call;
3041}

3043/*
3044// Objective-C 1.0 extensions
3045struct _objc_protocol {
3046struct _objc_protocol_extension *isa;
3047char *protocol_name;
3048struct _objc_protocol_list *protocol_list;
3049struct _objc__method_prototype_list *instance_methods;
3050struct _objc__method_prototype_list *class_methods
3051};
3052
3053See EmitProtocolExtension().
3054*/
3055llvm::Constant *CGObjCMac::GetOrEmitProtocol(const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
3056 llvm::GlobalVariable *Entry = Protocols[PD->getIdentifier()];
3057
3058 // Early exit if a defining object has already been generated.
3059 if (Entry && Entry->hasInitializer())
3060 return Entry;
3061
3062 // Use the protocol definition, if there is one.
3063 if (const ObjCProtocolDecl *Def = PD->getDefinition())
3064 PD = Def;
3065
3066 // FIXME: I don't understand why gcc generates this, or where it is
3067 // resolved. Investigate. Its also wasteful to look this up over and over.
3068 LazySymbols.insert(&CGM.getContext().Idents.get("Protocol"));
3069
3070 // Construct method lists.
3071 auto methodLists = ProtocolMethodLists::get(PD);
3072
3073 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3074 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ProtocolTy);
3075 values.add(EmitProtocolExtension(PD, methodLists));
3076 values.add(GetClassName(PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()));
3077 values.add(EmitProtocolList("OBJC_PROTOCOL_REFS_" + PD->getName(),
3078 PD->protocol_begin(), PD->protocol_end()));
3079 values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
3080 ProtocolMethodLists::RequiredInstanceMethods));
3081 values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
3082 ProtocolMethodLists::RequiredClassMethods));
3083
3084 if (Entry) {
3085 // Already created, update the initializer.
3086 assert(Entry->hasPrivateLinkage());
3087 values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(Entry);
3088 } else {
3089 Entry = values.finishAndCreateGlobal("OBJC_PROTOCOL_" + PD->getName(),
3090 CGM.getPointerAlign(),
3091 /*constant*/ false,
3092 llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage);
3093 Entry->setSection("__OBJC,__protocol,regular,no_dead_strip");
3094
3095 Protocols[PD->getIdentifier()] = Entry;
3096 }
3097 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(Entry);
3098
3099 return Entry;
3100}
3101
3102llvm::Constant *CGObjCMac::GetOrEmitProtocolRef(const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
3103 llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = Protocols[PD->getIdentifier()];
3104
3105 if (!Entry) {
3106 // We use the initializer as a marker of whether this is a forward
3107 // reference or not. At module finalization we add the empty
3108 // contents for protocols which were referenced but never defined.
3109 Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ProtocolTy,
3110 false, llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
3111 nullptr, "OBJC_PROTOCOL_" + PD->getName());
3112 Entry->setSection("__OBJC,__protocol,regular,no_dead_strip");
3113 // FIXME: Is this necessary? Why only for protocol?
3114 Entry->setAlignment(4);
3115 }
3116
3117 return Entry;
3118}

3120/*
3121 struct _objc_protocol_extension {
3122 uint32_t size;
3123 struct objc_method_description_list *optional_instance_methods;
3124 struct objc_method_description_list *optional_class_methods;
3125 struct objc_property_list *instance_properties;
3126 const char ** extendedMethodTypes;
3127 struct objc_property_list *class_properties;
3128 };
3129*/
3130llvm::Constant *
3131CGObjCMac::EmitProtocolExtension(const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD,
3132 const ProtocolMethodLists &methodLists) {
3133 auto optInstanceMethods =
3134 methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
3135 ProtocolMethodLists::OptionalInstanceMethods);
3136 auto optClassMethods =
3137 methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
3138 ProtocolMethodLists::OptionalClassMethods);
3139
3140 auto extendedMethodTypes =
3141 EmitProtocolMethodTypes("OBJC_PROTOCOL_METHOD_TYPES_" + PD->getName(),
3142 methodLists.emitExtendedTypesArray(this),
3143 ObjCTypes);
3144
3145 auto instanceProperties =
3146 EmitPropertyList("OBJC_$_PROP_PROTO_LIST_" + PD->getName(), nullptr, PD,
3147 ObjCTypes, false);
3148 auto classProperties =
3149 EmitPropertyList("OBJC_$_CLASS_PROP_PROTO_LIST_" + PD->getName(), nullptr,
3150 PD, ObjCTypes, true);
3151
3152 // Return null if no extension bits are used.
3153 if (optInstanceMethods->isNullValue() &&
3154 optClassMethods->isNullValue() &&
3155 extendedMethodTypes->isNullValue() &&
3156 instanceProperties->isNullValue() &&
3157 classProperties->isNullValue()) {
3158 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.ProtocolExtensionPtrTy);
3159 }
3160
3161 uint64_t size =
3162 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.ProtocolExtensionTy);
3163
3164 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3165 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ProtocolExtensionTy);
3166 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, size);
3167 values.add(optInstanceMethods);
3168 values.add(optClassMethods);
3169 values.add(instanceProperties);
3170 values.add(extendedMethodTypes);
3171 values.add(classProperties);
3172
3173 // No special section, but goes in llvm.used
3174 return CreateMetadataVar("_OBJC_PROTOCOLEXT_" + PD->getName(), values,
3175 StringRef(), CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3176}

3178/*
3179 struct objc_protocol_list {
3180 struct objc_protocol_list *next;
3181 long count;
3182 Protocol *list[];
3183 };
3184*/
3185llvm::Constant *
3186CGObjCMac::EmitProtocolList(Twine name,
3187 ObjCProtocolDecl::protocol_iterator begin,
3188 ObjCProtocolDecl::protocol_iterator end) {
3189 // Just return null for empty protocol lists
3190 if (begin == end)
3191 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListPtrTy);
3192
3193 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3194 auto values = builder.beginStruct();
3195
3196 // This field is only used by the runtime.
3197 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListPtrTy);
3198
3199 // Reserve a slot for the count.
3200 auto countSlot = values.addPlaceholder();
3201
3202 auto refsArray = values.beginArray(ObjCTypes.ProtocolPtrTy);
3203 for (; begin != end; ++begin) {
3204 refsArray.add(GetProtocolRef(*begin));
3205 }
3206 auto count = refsArray.size();
3207
3208 // This list is null terminated.
3209 refsArray.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolPtrTy);
3210
3211 refsArray.finishAndAddTo(values);
3212 values.fillPlaceholderWithInt(countSlot, ObjCTypes.LongTy, count);
3213
3214 StringRef section;
3215 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
3216 section = "__OBJC,__cat_cls_meth,regular,no_dead_strip";
3217
3218 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
3219 CreateMetadataVar(name, values, section, CGM.getPointerAlign(), false);
3220 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.ProtocolListPtrTy);
3221}
3222
3223static void
3224PushProtocolProperties(llvm::SmallPtrSet<const IdentifierInfo*,16> &PropertySet,
3225 SmallVectorImpl<const ObjCPropertyDecl *> &Properties,
3226 const ObjCProtocolDecl *Proto,
3227 bool IsClassProperty) {
3228 for (const auto *P : Proto->protocols())
3229 PushProtocolProperties(PropertySet, Properties, P, IsClassProperty);
3230
3231 for (const auto *PD : Proto->properties()) {
3232 if (IsClassProperty != PD->isClassProperty())
3233 continue;
3234 if (!PropertySet.insert(PD->getIdentifier()).second)
3235 continue;
3236 Properties.push_back(PD);
3237 }
3238}
3239
3240/*
3241 struct _objc_property {
3242 const char * const name;
3243 const char * const attributes;
3244 };
3245
3246 struct _objc_property_list {
3247 uint32_t entsize; // sizeof (struct _objc_property)
3248 uint32_t prop_count;
3249 struct _objc_property[prop_count];
3250 };
3251*/
3252llvm::Constant *CGObjCCommonMac::EmitPropertyList(Twine Name,
3253 const Decl *Container,
3254 const ObjCContainerDecl *OCD,
3255 const ObjCCommonTypesHelper &ObjCTypes,
3256 bool IsClassProperty) {
3257 if (IsClassProperty) {
3258 // Make this entry NULL for OS X with deployment target < 10.11, for iOS
3259 // with deployment target < 9.0.
3260 const llvm::Triple &Triple = CGM.getTarget().getTriple();
3261 if ((Triple.isMacOSX() && Triple.isMacOSXVersionLT(10, 11)) ||
3262 (Triple.isiOS() && Triple.isOSVersionLT(9)))
3263 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.PropertyListPtrTy);
3264 }
3265
3266 SmallVector<const ObjCPropertyDecl *, 16> Properties;
3267 llvm::SmallPtrSet<const IdentifierInfo*, 16> PropertySet;
3268
3269 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(OCD))
3270 for (const ObjCCategoryDecl *ClassExt : OID->known_extensions())
3271 for (auto *PD : ClassExt->properties()) {
3272 if (IsClassProperty != PD->isClassProperty())
3273 continue;
3274 PropertySet.insert(PD->getIdentifier());
3275 Properties.push_back(PD);
3276 }
3277
3278 for (const auto *PD : OCD->properties()) {
3279 if (IsClassProperty != PD->isClassProperty())
3280 continue;
3281 // Don't emit duplicate metadata for properties that were already in a
3282 // class extension.
3283 if (!PropertySet.insert(PD->getIdentifier()).second)
3284 continue;
3285 Properties.push_back(PD);
3286 }
3287
3288 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(OCD)) {
3289 for (const auto *P : OID->all_referenced_protocols())
3290 PushProtocolProperties(PropertySet, Properties, P, IsClassProperty);
3291 }
3292 else if (const ObjCCategoryDecl *CD = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(OCD)) {
3293 for (const auto *P : CD->protocols())
3294 PushProtocolProperties(PropertySet, Properties, P, IsClassProperty);
3295 }
3296
3297 // Return null for empty list.
3298 if (Properties.empty())
3299 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.PropertyListPtrTy);
3300
3301 unsigned propertySize =
3302 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.PropertyTy);
3303
3304 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3305 auto values = builder.beginStruct();
3306 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, propertySize);
3307 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Properties.size());
3308 auto propertiesArray = values.beginArray(ObjCTypes.PropertyTy);
3309 for (auto PD : Properties) {
3310 auto property = propertiesArray.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.PropertyTy);
3311 property.add(GetPropertyName(PD->getIdentifier()));
3312 property.add(GetPropertyTypeString(PD, Container));
3313 property.finishAndAddTo(propertiesArray);
3314 }
3315 propertiesArray.finishAndAddTo(values);
3316
3317 StringRef Section;
3318 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
3319 Section = (ObjCABI == 2) ? "__DATA, __objc_const"
3320 : "__OBJC,__property,regular,no_dead_strip";
3321
3322 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
3323 CreateMetadataVar(Name, values, Section, CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3324 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.PropertyListPtrTy);
3325}
3326
3327llvm::Constant *
3328CGObjCCommonMac::EmitProtocolMethodTypes(Twine Name,
3329 ArrayRef<llvm::Constant*> MethodTypes,
3330 const ObjCCommonTypesHelper &ObjCTypes) {
3331 // Return null for empty list.
3332 if (MethodTypes.empty())
3333 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrPtrTy);
3334
3335 llvm::ArrayType *AT = llvm::ArrayType::get(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy,
3336 MethodTypes.size());
3337 llvm::Constant *Init = llvm::ConstantArray::get(AT, MethodTypes);
3338
3339 StringRef Section;
3340 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO() && ObjCABI == 2)
3341 Section = "__DATA, __objc_const";
3342
3343 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
3344 CreateMetadataVar(Name, Init, Section, CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3345 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrPtrTy);
3346}
