3348/*
3349 struct _objc_category {
3350 char *category_name;
3351 char *class_name;
3352 struct _objc_method_list *instance_methods;
3353 struct _objc_method_list *class_methods;
3354 struct _objc_protocol_list *protocols;
3355 uint32_t size; // <rdar://4585769>
3356 struct _objc_property_list *instance_properties;
3357 struct _objc_property_list *class_properties;
3358 };
3359*/
3360void CGObjCMac::GenerateCategory(const ObjCCategoryImplDecl *OCD) {
3361 unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.CategoryTy);
3362
3363 // FIXME: This is poor design, the OCD should have a pointer to the category
3364 // decl. Additionally, note that Category can be null for the @implementation
3365 // w/o an @interface case. Sema should just create one for us as it does for
3366 // @implementation so everyone else can live life under a clear blue sky.
3367 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Interface = OCD->getClassInterface();
3368 const ObjCCategoryDecl *Category =
3369 Interface->FindCategoryDeclaration(OCD->getIdentifier());
3370
3371 SmallString<256> ExtName;
3372 llvm::raw_svector_ostream(ExtName) << Interface->getName() << '_'
3373 << OCD->getName();
3374
3375 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
3376 auto Values = Builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.CategoryTy);
3377
3378 enum {
3379 InstanceMethods,
3380 ClassMethods,
3381 NumMethodLists
3382 };
3383 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl *, 16> Methods[NumMethodLists];
3384 for (const auto *MD : OCD->methods()) {
3385 Methods[unsigned(MD->isClassMethod())].push_back(MD);
3386 }
3387
3388 Values.add(GetClassName(OCD->getName()));
3389 Values.add(GetClassName(Interface->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()));
3390 LazySymbols.insert(Interface->getIdentifier());
3391
3392 Values.add(emitMethodList(ExtName, MethodListType::CategoryInstanceMethods,
3393 Methods[InstanceMethods]));
3394 Values.add(emitMethodList(ExtName, MethodListType::CategoryClassMethods,
3395 Methods[ClassMethods]));
3396 if (Category) {
3397 Values.add(
3398 EmitProtocolList("OBJC_CATEGORY_PROTOCOLS_" + ExtName.str(),
3399 Category->protocol_begin(), Category->protocol_end()));
3400 } else {
3401 Values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListPtrTy);
3402 }
3403 Values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Size);
3404
3405 // If there is no category @interface then there can be no properties.
3406 if (Category) {
3407 Values.add(EmitPropertyList("_OBJC_$_PROP_LIST_" + ExtName.str(),
3408 OCD, Category, ObjCTypes, false));
3409 Values.add(EmitPropertyList("_OBJC_$_CLASS_PROP_LIST_" + ExtName.str(),
3410 OCD, Category, ObjCTypes, true));
3411 } else {
3412 Values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.PropertyListPtrTy);
3413 Values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.PropertyListPtrTy);
3414 }
3415
3416 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
3417 CreateMetadataVar("OBJC_CATEGORY_" + ExtName.str(), Values,
3418 "__OBJC,__category,regular,no_dead_strip",
3419 CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3420 DefinedCategories.push_back(GV);
3421 DefinedCategoryNames.insert(llvm::CachedHashString(ExtName));
3422 // method definition entries must be clear for next implementation.
3423 MethodDefinitions.clear();
3424}
3425
3426enum FragileClassFlags {
3427 /// Apparently: is not a meta-class.
3428 FragileABI_Class_Factory = 0x00001,
3429
3430 /// Is a meta-class.
3431 FragileABI_Class_Meta = 0x00002,
3432
3433 /// Has a non-trivial constructor or destructor.
3434 FragileABI_Class_HasCXXStructors = 0x02000,
3435
3436 /// Has hidden visibility.
3437 FragileABI_Class_Hidden = 0x20000,
3438
3439 /// Class implementation was compiled under ARC.
3440 FragileABI_Class_CompiledByARC = 0x04000000,
3441
3442 /// Class implementation was compiled under MRC and has MRC weak ivars.
3443 /// Exclusive with CompiledByARC.
3444 FragileABI_Class_HasMRCWeakIvars = 0x08000000,
3445};
3446
3447enum NonFragileClassFlags {
3448 /// Is a meta-class.
3449 NonFragileABI_Class_Meta = 0x00001,
3450
3451 /// Is a root class.
3452 NonFragileABI_Class_Root = 0x00002,
3453
3454 /// Has a non-trivial constructor or destructor.
3455 NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXStructors = 0x00004,
3456
3457 /// Has hidden visibility.
3458 NonFragileABI_Class_Hidden = 0x00010,
3459
3460 /// Has the exception attribute.
3461 NonFragileABI_Class_Exception = 0x00020,
3462
3463 /// (Obsolete) ARC-specific: this class has a .release_ivars method
3464 NonFragileABI_Class_HasIvarReleaser = 0x00040,
3465
3466 /// Class implementation was compiled under ARC.
3467 NonFragileABI_Class_CompiledByARC = 0x00080,
3468
3469 /// Class has non-trivial destructors, but zero-initialization is okay.
3470 NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXDestructorOnly = 0x00100,
3471
3472 /// Class implementation was compiled under MRC and has MRC weak ivars.
3473 /// Exclusive with CompiledByARC.
3474 NonFragileABI_Class_HasMRCWeakIvars = 0x00200,
3475};
3476
3477static bool hasWeakMember(QualType type) {
3478 if (type.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak) {
3479 return true;
3480 }
3481
3482 if (auto recType = type->getAs<RecordType>()) {
3483 for (auto field : recType->getDecl()->fields()) {
3484 if (hasWeakMember(field->getType()))
3485 return true;
3486 }
3487 }
3488
3489 return false;
3490}
3491
3492/// For compatibility, we only want to set the "HasMRCWeakIvars" flag
3493/// (and actually fill in a layout string) if we really do have any
3494/// __weak ivars.
3495static bool hasMRCWeakIvars(CodeGenModule &CGM,
3496 const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID) {
3497 if (!CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCWeak) return false;
3498 assert(CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC);
3499
3500 for (const ObjCIvarDecl *ivar =
3501 ID->getClassInterface()->all_declared_ivar_begin();
3502 ivar; ivar = ivar->getNextIvar()) {
3503 if (hasWeakMember(ivar->getType()))
3504 return true;
3505 }
3506
3507 return false;
3508}

3510/*
3511 struct _objc_class {
3512 Class isa;
3513 Class super_class;
3514 const char *name;
3515 long version;
3516 long info;
3517 long instance_size;
3518 struct _objc_ivar_list *ivars;
3519 struct _objc_method_list *methods;
3520 struct _objc_cache *cache;
3521 struct _objc_protocol_list *protocols;
3522 // Objective-C 1.0 extensions (<rdr://4585769>)
3523 const char *ivar_layout;
3524 struct _objc_class_ext *ext;
3525 };
3526
3527 See EmitClassExtension();
3528*/
3529void CGObjCMac::GenerateClass(const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID) {
3530 IdentifierInfo *RuntimeName =
3531 &CGM.getContext().Idents.get(ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString());
3532 DefinedSymbols.insert(RuntimeName);
3533
3534 std::string ClassName = ID->getNameAsString();
3535 // FIXME: Gross
3536 ObjCInterfaceDecl *Interface =
3537 const_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl*>(ID->getClassInterface());
3538 llvm::Constant *Protocols =
3539 EmitProtocolList("OBJC_CLASS_PROTOCOLS_" + ID->getName(),
3540 Interface->all_referenced_protocol_begin(),
3541 Interface->all_referenced_protocol_end());
3542 unsigned Flags = FragileABI_Class_Factory;
3543 if (ID->hasNonZeroConstructors() || ID->hasDestructors())
3544 Flags |= FragileABI_Class_HasCXXStructors;
3545
3546 bool hasMRCWeak = false;
3547
3548 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
3549 Flags |= FragileABI_Class_CompiledByARC;
3550 else if ((hasMRCWeak = hasMRCWeakIvars(CGM, ID)))
3551 Flags |= FragileABI_Class_HasMRCWeakIvars;
3552
3553 CharUnits Size =
3554 CGM.getContext().getASTObjCImplementationLayout(ID).getSize();
3555
3556 // FIXME: Set CXX-structors flag.
3557 if (ID->getClassInterface()->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility)
3558 Flags |= FragileABI_Class_Hidden;
3559
3560 enum {
3561 InstanceMethods,
3562 ClassMethods,
3563 NumMethodLists
3564 };
3565 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl *, 16> Methods[NumMethodLists];
3566 for (const auto *MD : ID->methods()) {
3567 Methods[unsigned(MD->isClassMethod())].push_back(MD);
3568 }
3569
3570 for (const auto *PID : ID->property_impls()) {
3571 if (PID->getPropertyImplementation() == ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Synthesize) {
3572 ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = PID->getPropertyDecl();
3573
3574 if (ObjCMethodDecl *MD = PD->getGetterMethodDecl())
3575 if (GetMethodDefinition(MD))
3576 Methods[InstanceMethods].push_back(MD);
3577 if (ObjCMethodDecl *MD = PD->getSetterMethodDecl())
3578 if (GetMethodDefinition(MD))
3579 Methods[InstanceMethods].push_back(MD);
3580 }
3581 }
3582
3583 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3584 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ClassTy);
3585 values.add(EmitMetaClass(ID, Protocols, Methods[ClassMethods]));
3586 if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super = Interface->getSuperClass()) {
3587 // Record a reference to the super class.
3588 LazySymbols.insert(Super->getIdentifier());
3589
3590 values.addBitCast(GetClassName(Super->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()),
3591 ObjCTypes.ClassPtrTy);
3592 } else {
3593 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ClassPtrTy);
3594 }
3595 values.add(GetClassName(ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()));
3596 // Version is always 0.
3597 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.LongTy, 0);
3598 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.LongTy, Flags);
3599 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.LongTy, Size.getQuantity());
3600 values.add(EmitIvarList(ID, false));
3601 values.add(emitMethodList(ID->getName(), MethodListType::InstanceMethods,
3602 Methods[InstanceMethods]));
3603 // cache is always NULL.
3604 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.CachePtrTy);
3605 values.add(Protocols);
3606 values.add(BuildStrongIvarLayout(ID, CharUnits::Zero(), Size));
3607 values.add(EmitClassExtension(ID, Size, hasMRCWeak,
3608 /*isMetaclass*/ false));
3609
3610 std::string Name("OBJC_CLASS_");
3611 Name += ClassName;
3612 const char *Section = "__OBJC,__class,regular,no_dead_strip";
3613 // Check for a forward reference.
3614 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(Name, true);
3615 if (GV) {
3616 assert(GV->getType()->getElementType() == ObjCTypes.ClassTy &&
3617 "Forward metaclass reference has incorrect type.");
3618 values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(GV);
3619 GV->setSection(Section);
3620 GV->setAlignment(CGM.getPointerAlign().getQuantity());
3621 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
3622 } else
3623 GV = CreateMetadataVar(Name, values, Section, CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3624 DefinedClasses.push_back(GV);
3625 ImplementedClasses.push_back(Interface);
3626 // method definition entries must be clear for next implementation.
3627 MethodDefinitions.clear();
3628}
3629
3630llvm::Constant *CGObjCMac::EmitMetaClass(const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID,
3631 llvm::Constant *Protocols,
3632 ArrayRef<const ObjCMethodDecl*> Methods) {
3633 unsigned Flags = FragileABI_Class_Meta;
3634 unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.ClassTy);
3635
3636 if (ID->getClassInterface()->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility)
3637 Flags |= FragileABI_Class_Hidden;
3638
3639 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3640 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ClassTy);
3641 // The isa for the metaclass is the root of the hierarchy.
3642 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Root = ID->getClassInterface();
3643 while (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super = Root->getSuperClass())
3644 Root = Super;
3645 values.addBitCast(GetClassName(Root->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()),
3646 ObjCTypes.ClassPtrTy);
3647 // The super class for the metaclass is emitted as the name of the
3648 // super class. The runtime fixes this up to point to the
3649 // *metaclass* for the super class.
3650 if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super = ID->getClassInterface()->getSuperClass()) {
3651 values.addBitCast(GetClassName(Super->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()),
3652 ObjCTypes.ClassPtrTy);
3653 } else {
3654 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ClassPtrTy);
3655 }
3656 values.add(GetClassName(ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()));
3657 // Version is always 0.
3658 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.LongTy, 0);
3659 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.LongTy, Flags);
3660 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.LongTy, Size);
3661 values.add(EmitIvarList(ID, true));
3662 values.add(emitMethodList(ID->getName(), MethodListType::ClassMethods,
3663 Methods));
3664 // cache is always NULL.
3665 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.CachePtrTy);
3666 values.add(Protocols);
3667 // ivar_layout for metaclass is always NULL.
3668 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
3669 // The class extension is used to store class properties for metaclasses.
3670 values.add(EmitClassExtension(ID, CharUnits::Zero(), false/*hasMRCWeak*/,
3671 /*isMetaclass*/true));
3672
3673 std::string Name("OBJC_METACLASS_");
3674 Name += ID->getName();
3675
3676 // Check for a forward reference.
3677 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(Name, true);
3678 if (GV) {
3679 assert(GV->getType()->getElementType() == ObjCTypes.ClassTy &&
3680 "Forward metaclass reference has incorrect type.");
3681 values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(GV);
3682 } else {
3683 GV = values.finishAndCreateGlobal(Name, CGM.getPointerAlign(),
3684 /*constant*/ false,
3685 llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage);
3686 }
3687 GV->setSection("__OBJC,__meta_class,regular,no_dead_strip");
3688 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
3689
3690 return GV;
3691}
3692
3693llvm::Constant *CGObjCMac::EmitMetaClassRef(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
3694 std::string Name = "OBJC_METACLASS_" + ID->getNameAsString();
3695
3696 // FIXME: Should we look these up somewhere other than the module. Its a bit
3697 // silly since we only generate these while processing an implementation, so
3698 // exactly one pointer would work if know when we entered/exitted an
3699 // implementation block.
3700
3701 // Check for an existing forward reference.
3702 // Previously, metaclass with internal linkage may have been defined.
3703 // pass 'true' as 2nd argument so it is returned.
3704 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(Name, true);
3705 if (!GV)
3706 GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ClassTy, false,
3707 llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, nullptr,
3708 Name);
3709
3710 assert(GV->getType()->getElementType() == ObjCTypes.ClassTy &&
3711 "Forward metaclass reference has incorrect type.");
3712 return GV;
3713}
3714
3715llvm::Value *CGObjCMac::EmitSuperClassRef(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
3716 std::string Name = "OBJC_CLASS_" + ID->getNameAsString();
3717 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(Name, true);
3718
3719 if (!GV)
3720 GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ClassTy, false,
3721 llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, nullptr,
3722 Name);
3723
3724 assert(GV->getType()->getElementType() == ObjCTypes.ClassTy &&
3725 "Forward class metadata reference has incorrect type.");
3726 return GV;
3727}
3728
3729/*
3730 Emit a "class extension", which in this specific context means extra
3731 data that doesn't fit in the normal fragile-ABI class structure, and
3732 has nothing to do with the language concept of a class extension.
3733
3734 struct objc_class_ext {
3735 uint32_t size;
3736 const char *weak_ivar_layout;
3737 struct _objc_property_list *properties;
3738 };
3739*/
3740llvm::Constant *
3741CGObjCMac::EmitClassExtension(const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID,
3742 CharUnits InstanceSize, bool hasMRCWeakIvars,
3743 bool isMetaclass) {
3744 // Weak ivar layout.
3745 llvm::Constant *layout;
3746 if (isMetaclass) {
3747 layout = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
3748 } else {
3749 layout = BuildWeakIvarLayout(ID, CharUnits::Zero(), InstanceSize,
3750 hasMRCWeakIvars);
3751 }
3752
3753 // Properties.
3754 llvm::Constant *propertyList =
3755 EmitPropertyList((isMetaclass ? Twine("_OBJC_$_CLASS_PROP_LIST_")
3756 : Twine("_OBJC_$_PROP_LIST_"))
3757 + ID->getName(),
3758 ID, ID->getClassInterface(), ObjCTypes, isMetaclass);
3759
3760 // Return null if no extension bits are used.
3761 if (layout->isNullValue() && propertyList->isNullValue()) {
3762 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.ClassExtensionPtrTy);
3763 }
3764
3765 uint64_t size =
3766 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.ClassExtensionTy);
3767
3768 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3769 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ClassExtensionTy);
3770 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, size);
3771 values.add(layout);
3772 values.add(propertyList);
3773
3774 return CreateMetadataVar("OBJC_CLASSEXT_" + ID->getName(), values,
3775 "__OBJC,__class_ext,regular,no_dead_strip",
3776 CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3777}
3778
3779/*
3780 struct objc_ivar {
3781 char *ivar_name;
3782 char *ivar_type;
3783 int ivar_offset;
3784 };
3785
3786 struct objc_ivar_list {
3787 int ivar_count;
3788 struct objc_ivar list[count];
3789 };
3790*/
3791llvm::Constant *CGObjCMac::EmitIvarList(const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID,
3792 bool ForClass) {
3793 // When emitting the root class GCC emits ivar entries for the
3794 // actual class structure. It is not clear if we need to follow this
3795 // behavior; for now lets try and get away with not doing it. If so,
3796 // the cleanest solution would be to make up an ObjCInterfaceDecl
3797 // for the class.
3798 if (ForClass)
3799 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.IvarListPtrTy);
3800
3801 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID = ID->getClassInterface();
3802
3803 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3804 auto ivarList = builder.beginStruct();
3805 auto countSlot = ivarList.addPlaceholder();
3806 auto ivars = ivarList.beginArray(ObjCTypes.IvarTy);
3807
3808 for (const ObjCIvarDecl *IVD = OID->all_declared_ivar_begin();
3809 IVD; IVD = IVD->getNextIvar()) {
3810 // Ignore unnamed bit-fields.
3811 if (!IVD->getDeclName())
3812 continue;
3813
3814 auto ivar = ivars.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.IvarTy);
3815 ivar.add(GetMethodVarName(IVD->getIdentifier()));
3816 ivar.add(GetMethodVarType(IVD));
3817 ivar.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, OID, IVD));
3818 ivar.finishAndAddTo(ivars);
3819 }
3820
3821 // Return null for empty list.
3822 auto count = ivars.size();
3823 if (count == 0) {
3824 ivars.abandon();
3825 ivarList.abandon();
3826 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.IvarListPtrTy);
3827 }
3828
3829 ivars.finishAndAddTo(ivarList);
3830 ivarList.fillPlaceholderWithInt(countSlot, ObjCTypes.IntTy, count);
3831
3832 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV;
3833 if (ForClass)
3834 GV =
3835 CreateMetadataVar("OBJC_CLASS_VARIABLES_" + ID->getName(), ivarList,
3836 "__OBJC,__class_vars,regular,no_dead_strip",
3837 CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3838 else
3839 GV = CreateMetadataVar("OBJC_INSTANCE_VARIABLES_" + ID->getName(), ivarList,
3840 "__OBJC,__instance_vars,regular,no_dead_strip",
3841 CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3842 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.IvarListPtrTy);
3843}

3845/// Build a struct objc_method_description constant for the given method.
3846///
3847/// struct objc_method_description {
3848/// SEL method_name;
3849/// char *method_types;
3850/// };
3851void CGObjCMac::emitMethodDescriptionConstant(ConstantArrayBuilder &builder,
3852 const ObjCMethodDecl *MD) {
3853 auto description = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.MethodDescriptionTy);
3854 description.addBitCast(GetMethodVarName(MD->getSelector()),
3855 ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy);
3856 description.add(GetMethodVarType(MD));
3857 description.finishAndAddTo(builder);
3858}
3859
3860/// Build a struct objc_method constant for the given method.
3861///
3862/// struct objc_method {
3863/// SEL method_name;
3864/// char *method_types;
3865/// void *method;
3866/// };
3867void CGObjCMac::emitMethodConstant(ConstantArrayBuilder &builder,
3868 const ObjCMethodDecl *MD) {
3869 llvm::Function *fn = GetMethodDefinition(MD);
3870 assert(fn && "no definition registered for method");
3871
3872 auto method = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.MethodTy);
3873 method.addBitCast(GetMethodVarName(MD->getSelector()),
3874 ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy);
3875 method.add(GetMethodVarType(MD));
3876 method.addBitCast(fn, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
3877 method.finishAndAddTo(builder);
3878}
3879
3880/// Build a struct objc_method_list or struct objc_method_description_list,
3881/// as appropriate.
3882///
3883/// struct objc_method_list {
3884/// struct objc_method_list *obsolete;
3885/// int count;
3886/// struct objc_method methods_list[count];
3887/// };
3888///
3889/// struct objc_method_description_list {
3890/// int count;
3891/// struct objc_method_description list[count];
3892/// };
3893llvm::Constant *CGObjCMac::emitMethodList(Twine name, MethodListType MLT,
3894 ArrayRef<const ObjCMethodDecl *> methods) {
3895 StringRef prefix;
3896 StringRef section;
3897 bool forProtocol = false;
3898 switch (MLT) {
3899 case MethodListType::CategoryInstanceMethods:
3900 prefix = "OBJC_CATEGORY_INSTANCE_METHODS_";
3901 section = "__OBJC,__cat_inst_meth,regular,no_dead_strip";
3902 forProtocol = false;
3903 break;
3904 case MethodListType::CategoryClassMethods:
3905 prefix = "OBJC_CATEGORY_CLASS_METHODS_";
3906 section = "__OBJC,__cat_cls_meth,regular,no_dead_strip";
3907 forProtocol = false;
3908 break;
3909 case MethodListType::InstanceMethods:
3910 prefix = "OBJC_INSTANCE_METHODS_";
3911 section = "__OBJC,__inst_meth,regular,no_dead_strip";
3912 forProtocol = false;
3913 break;
3914 case MethodListType::ClassMethods:
3915 prefix = "OBJC_CLASS_METHODS_";
3916 section = "__OBJC,__cls_meth,regular,no_dead_strip";
3917 forProtocol = false;
3918 break;
3919 case MethodListType::ProtocolInstanceMethods:
3920 prefix = "OBJC_PROTOCOL_INSTANCE_METHODS_";
3921 section = "__OBJC,__cat_inst_meth,regular,no_dead_strip";
3922 forProtocol = true;
3923 break;
3924 case MethodListType::ProtocolClassMethods:
3925 prefix = "OBJC_PROTOCOL_CLASS_METHODS_";
3926 section = "__OBJC,__cat_cls_meth,regular,no_dead_strip";
3927 forProtocol = true;
3928 break;
3929 case MethodListType::OptionalProtocolInstanceMethods:
3930 prefix = "OBJC_PROTOCOL_INSTANCE_METHODS_OPT_";
3931 section = "__OBJC,__cat_inst_meth,regular,no_dead_strip";
3932 forProtocol = true;
3933 break;
3934 case MethodListType::OptionalProtocolClassMethods:
3935 prefix = "OBJC_PROTOCOL_CLASS_METHODS_OPT_";
3936 section = "__OBJC,__cat_cls_meth,regular,no_dead_strip";
3937 forProtocol = true;
3938 break;
3939 }
3940
3941 // Return null for empty list.
3942 if (methods.empty())
3943 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(forProtocol
3944 ? ObjCTypes.MethodDescriptionListPtrTy
3945 : ObjCTypes.MethodListPtrTy);
3946
3947 // For protocols, this is an objc_method_description_list, which has
3948 // a slightly different structure.
3949 if (forProtocol) {
3950 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3951 auto values = builder.beginStruct();
3952 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, methods.size());
3953 auto methodArray = values.beginArray(ObjCTypes.MethodDescriptionTy);
3954 for (auto MD : methods) {
3955 emitMethodDescriptionConstant(methodArray, MD);
3956 }
3957 methodArray.finishAndAddTo(values);
3958
3959 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CreateMetadataVar(prefix + name, values, section,
3960 CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3961 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV,
3962 ObjCTypes.MethodDescriptionListPtrTy);
3963 }
3964
3965 // Otherwise, it's an objc_method_list.
3966 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
3967 auto values = builder.beginStruct();
3968 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
3969 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, methods.size());
3970 auto methodArray = values.beginArray(ObjCTypes.MethodTy);
3971 for (auto MD : methods) {
3972 emitMethodConstant(methodArray, MD);
3973 }
3974 methodArray.finishAndAddTo(values);
3975
3976 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CreateMetadataVar(prefix + name, values, section,
3977 CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
3978 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.MethodListPtrTy);
3979}

3981llvm::Function *CGObjCCommonMac::GenerateMethod(const ObjCMethodDecl *OMD,
3982 const ObjCContainerDecl *CD) {
3983 SmallString<256> Name;
3984 GetNameForMethod(OMD, CD, Name);
3985
3986 CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
3987 llvm::FunctionType *MethodTy =
3988 Types.GetFunctionType(Types.arrangeObjCMethodDeclaration(OMD));
3989 llvm::Function *Method =
3990 llvm::Function::Create(MethodTy,
3991 llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
3992 Name.str(),
3993 &CGM.getModule());
3994 MethodDefinitions.insert(std::make_pair(OMD, Method));
3995
3996 return Method;
3997}

4002 CharUnits Align,

4005 getLinkageTypeForObjCMetadata(CGM, Section);

4008 if (!Section.empty())

4018 CharUnits Align,
4019 bool AddToUsed) {

4033llvm::GlobalVariable *
4034CGObjCCommonMac::CreateCStringLiteral(StringRef Name, ObjCLabelType Type,
4035 bool ForceNonFragileABI,
4036 bool NullTerminate) {
4037 StringRef Label;
4038 switch (Type) {
4039 case ObjCLabelType::ClassName: Label = "OBJC_CLASS_NAME_"; break;
4040 case ObjCLabelType::MethodVarName: Label = "OBJC_METH_VAR_NAME_"; break;
4041 case ObjCLabelType::MethodVarType: Label = "OBJC_METH_VAR_TYPE_"; break;
4042 case ObjCLabelType::PropertyName: Label = "OBJC_PROP_NAME_ATTR_"; break;
4043 }
4044
4045 bool NonFragile = ForceNonFragileABI || isNonFragileABI();
4046
4047 StringRef Section;
4048 switch (Type) {
4049 case ObjCLabelType::ClassName:
4050 Section = NonFragile ? "__TEXT,__objc_classname,cstring_literals"
4051 : "__TEXT,__cstring,cstring_literals";
4052 break;
4053 case ObjCLabelType::MethodVarName:
4054 Section = NonFragile ? "__TEXT,__objc_methname,cstring_literals"
4055 : "__TEXT,__cstring,cstring_literals";
4056 break;
4057 case ObjCLabelType::MethodVarType:
4058 Section = NonFragile ? "__TEXT,__objc_methtype,cstring_literals"
4059 : "__TEXT,__cstring,cstring_literals";
4060 break;
4061 case ObjCLabelType::PropertyName:
4062 Section = "__TEXT,__cstring,cstring_literals";
4063 break;
4064 }
4065
4066 llvm::Constant *Value =
4067 llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(VMContext, Name, NullTerminate);
4068 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
4069 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Value->getType(),
4070 /*isConstant=*/true,
4071 llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, Value, Label);
4072 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
4073 GV->setSection(Section);
4074 GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
4075 GV->setAlignment(CharUnits::One().getQuantity());
4076 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
4077
4078 return GV;
4079}

4129namespace {
4130 struct PerformFragileFinally final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
4131 const Stmt &S;
4132 Address SyncArgSlot;
4133 Address CallTryExitVar;
4134 Address ExceptionData;
4135 ObjCTypesHelper &ObjCTypes;
4136 PerformFragileFinally(const Stmt *S,
4137 Address SyncArgSlot,
4138 Address CallTryExitVar,
4139 Address ExceptionData,
4140 ObjCTypesHelper *ObjCTypes)
4141 : S(*S), SyncArgSlot(SyncArgSlot), CallTryExitVar(CallTryExitVar),
4142 ExceptionData(ExceptionData), ObjCTypes(*ObjCTypes) {}
4143
4144 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
4145 // Check whether we need to call objc_exception_try_exit.
4146 // In optimized code, this branch will always be folded.
4147 llvm::BasicBlock *FinallyCallExit =
4148 CGF.createBasicBlock("finally.call_exit");
4149 llvm::BasicBlock *FinallyNoCallExit =
4150 CGF.createBasicBlock("finally.no_call_exit");
4151 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(CallTryExitVar),
4152 FinallyCallExit, FinallyNoCallExit);
4153
4154 CGF.EmitBlock(FinallyCallExit);
4155 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getExceptionTryExitFn(),
4156 ExceptionData.getPointer());
4157
4158 CGF.EmitBlock(FinallyNoCallExit);
4159
4160 if (isa<ObjCAtTryStmt>(S)) {
4161 if (const ObjCAtFinallyStmt* FinallyStmt =
4162 cast<ObjCAtTryStmt>(S).getFinallyStmt()) {
4163 // Don't try to do the @finally if this is an EH cleanup.
4164 if (flags.isForEHCleanup()) return;
4165
4166 // Save the current cleanup destination in case there's
4167 // control flow inside the finally statement.
4168 llvm::Value *CurCleanupDest =
4169 CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(CGF.getNormalCleanupDestSlot());
4170
4171 CGF.EmitStmt(FinallyStmt->getFinallyBody());
4172
4173 if (CGF.HaveInsertPoint()) {
4174 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CurCleanupDest,
4175 CGF.getNormalCleanupDestSlot());
4176 } else {
4177 // Currently, the end of the cleanup must always exist.
4178 CGF.EnsureInsertPoint();
4179 }
4180 }
4181 } else {
4182 // Emit objc_sync_exit(expr); as finally's sole statement for
4183 // @synchronized.
4184 llvm::Value *SyncArg = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(SyncArgSlot);
4185 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getSyncExitFn(), SyncArg);
4186 }
4187 }
4188 };
4189
4190 class FragileHazards {
4191 CodeGenFunction &CGF;
4192 SmallVector<llvm::Value*, 20> Locals;
4193 llvm::DenseSet<llvm::BasicBlock*> BlocksBeforeTry;
4194
4195 llvm::InlineAsm *ReadHazard;
4196 llvm::InlineAsm *WriteHazard;
4197
4198 llvm::FunctionType *GetAsmFnType();
4199
4200 void collectLocals();
4201 void emitReadHazard(CGBuilderTy &Builder);
4202
4203 public:
4204 FragileHazards(CodeGenFunction &CGF);
4205
4206 void emitWriteHazard();
4207 void emitHazardsInNewBlocks();
4208 };
4209} // end anonymous namespace
4210
4211/// Create the fragile-ABI read and write hazards based on the current
4212/// state of the function, which is presumed to be immediately prior
4213/// to a @try block. These hazards are used to maintain correct
4214/// semantics in the face of optimization and the fragile ABI's
4215/// cavalier use of setjmp/longjmp.
4216FragileHazards::FragileHazards(CodeGenFunction &CGF) : CGF(CGF) {
4217 collectLocals();
4218
4219 if (Locals.empty()) return;
4220
4221 // Collect all the blocks in the function.
4222 for (llvm::Function::iterator
4223 I = CGF.CurFn->begin(), E = CGF.CurFn->end(); I != E; ++I)
4224 BlocksBeforeTry.insert(&*I);
4225
4226 llvm::FunctionType *AsmFnTy = GetAsmFnType();
4227
4228 // Create a read hazard for the allocas. This inhibits dead-store
4229 // optimizations and forces the values to memory. This hazard is
4230 // inserted before any 'throwing' calls in the protected scope to
4231 // reflect the possibility that the variables might be read from the
4232 // catch block if the call throws.
4233 {
4234 std::string Constraint;
4235 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Locals.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4236 if (I) Constraint += ',';
4237 Constraint += "*m";
4238 }
4239
4240 ReadHazard = llvm::InlineAsm::get(AsmFnTy, "", Constraint, true, false);
4241 }
4242
4243 // Create a write hazard for the allocas. This inhibits folding
4244 // loads across the hazard. This hazard is inserted at the
4245 // beginning of the catch path to reflect the possibility that the
4246 // variables might have been written within the protected scope.
4247 {
4248 std::string Constraint;
4249 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Locals.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4250 if (I) Constraint += ',';
4251 Constraint += "=*m";
4252 }
4253
4254 WriteHazard = llvm::InlineAsm::get(AsmFnTy, "", Constraint, true, false);
4255 }
4256}
4257
4258/// Emit a write hazard at the current location.
4259void FragileHazards::emitWriteHazard() {
4260 if (Locals.empty()) return;
4261
4262 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(WriteHazard, Locals);
4263}
4264
4265void FragileHazards::emitReadHazard(CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
4266 assert(!Locals.empty());
4267 llvm::CallInst *call = Builder.CreateCall(ReadHazard, Locals);
4268 call->setDoesNotThrow();
4269 call->setCallingConv(CGF.getRuntimeCC());
4270}
4271
4272/// Emit read hazards in all the protected blocks, i.e. all the blocks
4273/// which have been inserted since the beginning of the try.
4274void FragileHazards::emitHazardsInNewBlocks() {
4275 if (Locals.empty()) return;
4276
4277 CGBuilderTy Builder(CGF, CGF.getLLVMContext());
4278
4279 // Iterate through all blocks, skipping those prior to the try.
4280 for (llvm::Function::iterator
4281 FI = CGF.CurFn->begin(), FE = CGF.CurFn->end(); FI != FE; ++FI) {
4282 llvm::BasicBlock &BB = *FI;
4283 if (BlocksBeforeTry.count(&BB)) continue;
4284
4285 // Walk through all the calls in the block.
4286 for (llvm::BasicBlock::iterator
4287 BI = BB.begin(), BE = BB.end(); BI != BE; ++BI) {
4288 llvm::Instruction &I = *BI;
4289
4290 // Ignore instructions that aren't non-intrinsic calls.
4291 // These are the only calls that can possibly call longjmp.
4292 if (!isa<llvm::CallInst>(I) && !isa<llvm::InvokeInst>(I))
4293 continue;
4294 if (isa<llvm::IntrinsicInst>(I))
4295 continue;
4296
4297 // Ignore call sites marked nounwind. This may be questionable,
4298 // since 'nounwind' doesn't necessarily mean 'does not call longjmp'.
4299 if (cast<llvm::CallBase>(I).doesNotThrow())
4300 continue;
4301
4302 // Insert a read hazard before the call. This will ensure that
4303 // any writes to the locals are performed before making the
4304 // call. If the call throws, then this is sufficient to
4305 // guarantee correctness as long as it doesn't also write to any
4306 // locals.
4307 Builder.SetInsertPoint(&BB, BI);
4308 emitReadHazard(Builder);
4309 }
4310 }
4311}
4312
4313static void addIfPresent(llvm::DenseSet<llvm::Value*> &S, Address V) {
4314 if (V.isValid()) S.insert(V.getPointer());
4315}
4316
4317void FragileHazards::collectLocals() {
4318 // Compute a set of allocas to ignore.
4319 llvm::DenseSet<llvm::Value*> AllocasToIgnore;
4320 addIfPresent(AllocasToIgnore, CGF.ReturnValue);
4321 addIfPresent(AllocasToIgnore, CGF.NormalCleanupDest);
4322
4323 // Collect all the allocas currently in the function. This is
4324 // probably way too aggressive.
4325 llvm::BasicBlock &Entry = CGF.CurFn->getEntryBlock();
4326 for (llvm::BasicBlock::iterator
4327 I = Entry.begin(), E = Entry.end(); I != E; ++I)
4328 if (isa<llvm::AllocaInst>(*I) && !AllocasToIgnore.count(&*I))
4329 Locals.push_back(&*I);
4330}
4331
4332llvm::FunctionType *FragileHazards::GetAsmFnType() {
4333 SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 16> tys(Locals.size());
4334 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Locals.size(); i != e; ++i)
4335 tys[i] = Locals[i]->getType();
4336 return llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.VoidTy, tys, false);
4337}
4338
4339/*
4340
4341 Objective-C setjmp-longjmp (sjlj) Exception Handling
4342 --
4343
4344 A catch buffer is a setjmp buffer plus:
4345 - a pointer to the exception that was caught
4346 - a pointer to the previous exception data buffer
4347 - two pointers of reserved storage
4348 Therefore catch buffers form a stack, with a pointer to the top
4349 of the stack kept in thread-local storage.
4350
4351 objc_exception_try_enter pushes a catch buffer onto the EH stack.
4352 objc_exception_try_exit pops the given catch buffer, which is
4353 required to be the top of the EH stack.
4354 objc_exception_throw pops the top of the EH stack, writes the
4355 thrown exception into the appropriate field, and longjmps
4356 to the setjmp buffer. It crashes the process (with a printf
4357 and an abort()) if there are no catch buffers on the stack.
4358 objc_exception_extract just reads the exception pointer out of the
4359 catch buffer.
4360
4361 There's no reason an implementation couldn't use a light-weight
4362 setjmp here --- something like __builtin_setjmp, but API-compatible
4363 with the heavyweight setjmp. This will be more important if we ever
4364 want to implement correct ObjC/C++ exception interactions for the
4365 fragile ABI.
4366
4367 Note that for this use of setjmp/longjmp to be correct, we may need
4368 to mark some local variables volatile: if a non-volatile local
4369 variable is modified between the setjmp and the longjmp, it has
4370 indeterminate value. For the purposes of LLVM IR, it may be
4371 sufficient to make loads and stores within the @try (to variables
4372 declared outside the @try) volatile. This is necessary for
4373 optimized correctness, but is not currently being done; this is
4374 being tracked as rdar://problem/8160285
4375
4376 The basic framework for a @try-catch-finally is as follows:
4377 {
4378 objc_exception_data d;
4379 id _rethrow = null;
4380 bool _call_try_exit = true;
4381
4382 objc_exception_try_enter(&d);
4383 if (!setjmp(d.jmp_buf)) {
4384 ... try body ...
4385 } else {
4386 // exception path
4387 id _caught = objc_exception_extract(&d);
4388
4389 // enter new try scope for handlers
4390 if (!setjmp(d.jmp_buf)) {
4391 ... match exception and execute catch blocks ...
4392
4393 // fell off end, rethrow.
4394 _rethrow = _caught;
4395 ... jump-through-finally to finally_rethrow ...
4396 } else {
4397 // exception in catch block
4398 _rethrow = objc_exception_extract(&d);
4399 _call_try_exit = false;
4400 ... jump-through-finally to finally_rethrow ...
4401 }
4402 }
4403 ... jump-through-finally to finally_end ...
4404
4405 finally:
4406 if (_call_try_exit)
4407 objc_exception_try_exit(&d);
4408
4409 ... finally block ....
4410 ... dispatch to finally destination ...
4411
4412 finally_rethrow:
4413 objc_exception_throw(_rethrow);
4414
4415 finally_end:
4416 }
4417
4418 This framework differs slightly from the one gcc uses, in that gcc
4419 uses _rethrow to determine if objc_exception_try_exit should be called
4420 and if the object should be rethrown. This breaks in the face of
4421 throwing nil and introduces unnecessary branches.
4422
4423 We specialize this framework for a few particular circumstances:
4424
4425 - If there are no catch blocks, then we avoid emitting the second
4426 exception handling context.
4427
4428 - If there is a catch-all catch block (i.e. @catch(...) or @catch(id
4429 e)) we avoid emitting the code to rethrow an uncaught exception.
4430
4431 - FIXME: If there is no @finally block we can do a few more
4432 simplifications.
4433
4434 Rethrows and Jumps-Through-Finally
4435 --
4436
4437 '@throw;' is supported by pushing the currently-caught exception
4438 onto ObjCEHStack while the @catch blocks are emitted.
4439
4440 Branches through the @finally block are handled with an ordinary
4441 normal cleanup. We do not register an EH cleanup; fragile-ABI ObjC
4442 exceptions are not compatible with C++ exceptions, and this is
4443 hardly the only place where this will go wrong.
4444
4445 @synchronized(expr) { stmt; } is emitted as if it were:
4446 id synch_value = expr;
4447 objc_sync_enter(synch_value);
4448 @try { stmt; } @finally { objc_sync_exit(synch_value); }
4449*/
4450
4451void CGObjCMac::EmitTryOrSynchronizedStmt(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4452 const Stmt &S) {
4453 bool isTry = isa<ObjCAtTryStmt>(S);
4454
4455 // A destination for the fall-through edges of the catch handlers to
4456 // jump to.
4457 CodeGenFunction::JumpDest FinallyEnd =
4458 CGF.getJumpDestInCurrentScope("finally.end");
4459
4460 // A destination for the rethrow edge of the catch handlers to jump
4461 // to.
4462 CodeGenFunction::JumpDest FinallyRethrow =
4463 CGF.getJumpDestInCurrentScope("finally.rethrow");
4464
4465 // For @synchronized, call objc_sync_enter(sync.expr). The
4466 // evaluation of the expression must occur before we enter the
4467 // @synchronized. We can't avoid a temp here because we need the
4468 // value to be preserved. If the backend ever does liveness
4469 // correctly after setjmp, this will be unnecessary.
4470 Address SyncArgSlot = Address::invalid();
4471 if (!isTry) {
4472 llvm::Value *SyncArg =
4473 CGF.EmitScalarExpr(cast<ObjCAtSynchronizedStmt>(S).getSynchExpr());
4474 SyncArg = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(SyncArg, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
4475 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getSyncEnterFn(), SyncArg);
4476
4477 SyncArgSlot = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(SyncArg->getType(),
4478 CGF.getPointerAlign(), "sync.arg");
4479 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(SyncArg, SyncArgSlot);
4480 }
4481
4482 // Allocate memory for the setjmp buffer. This needs to be kept
4483 // live throughout the try and catch blocks.
4484 Address ExceptionData = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(ObjCTypes.ExceptionDataTy,
4485 CGF.getPointerAlign(),
4486 "exceptiondata.ptr");
4487
4488 // Create the fragile hazards. Note that this will not capture any
4489 // of the allocas required for exception processing, but will
4490 // capture the current basic block (which extends all the way to the
4491 // setjmp call) as "before the @try".
4492 FragileHazards Hazards(CGF);
4493
4494 // Create a flag indicating whether the cleanup needs to call
4495 // objc_exception_try_exit. This is true except when
4496 // - no catches match and we're branching through the cleanup
4497 // just to rethrow the exception, or
4498 // - a catch matched and we're falling out of the catch handler.
4499 // The setjmp-safety rule here is that we should always store to this
4500 // variable in a place that dominates the branch through the cleanup
4501 // without passing through any setjmps.
4502 Address CallTryExitVar = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(CGF.Builder.getInt1Ty(),
4503 CharUnits::One(),
4504 "_call_try_exit");
4505
4506 // A slot containing the exception to rethrow. Only needed when we
4507 // have both a @catch and a @finally.
4508 Address PropagatingExnVar = Address::invalid();
4509
4510 // Push a normal cleanup to leave the try scope.
4511 CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<PerformFragileFinally>(NormalAndEHCleanup, &S,
4512 SyncArgSlot,
4513 CallTryExitVar,
4514 ExceptionData,
4515 &ObjCTypes);
4516
4517 // Enter a try block:
4518 // - Call objc_exception_try_enter to push ExceptionData on top of
4519 // the EH stack.
4520 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getExceptionTryEnterFn(),
4521 ExceptionData.getPointer());
4522
4523 // - Call setjmp on the exception data buffer.
4524 llvm::Constant *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Builder.getInt32Ty(), 0);
4525 llvm::Value *GEPIndexes[] = { Zero, Zero, Zero };
4526 llvm::Value *SetJmpBuffer = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(
4527 ObjCTypes.ExceptionDataTy, ExceptionData.getPointer(), GEPIndexes,
4528 "setjmp_buffer");
4529 llvm::CallInst *SetJmpResult = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(
4530 ObjCTypes.getSetJmpFn(), SetJmpBuffer, "setjmp_result");
4531 SetJmpResult->setCanReturnTwice();
4532
4533 // If setjmp returned 0, enter the protected block; otherwise,
4534 // branch to the handler.
4535 llvm::BasicBlock *TryBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("try");
4536 llvm::BasicBlock *TryHandler = CGF.createBasicBlock("try.handler");
4537 llvm::Value *DidCatch =
4538 CGF.Builder.CreateIsNotNull(SetJmpResult, "did_catch_exception");
4539 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(DidCatch, TryHandler, TryBlock);
4540
4541 // Emit the protected block.
4542 CGF.EmitBlock(TryBlock);
4543 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CGF.Builder.getTrue(), CallTryExitVar);
4544 CGF.EmitStmt(isTry ? cast<ObjCAtTryStmt>(S).getTryBody()
4545 : cast<ObjCAtSynchronizedStmt>(S).getSynchBody());
4546
4547 CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint TryFallthroughIP = CGF.Builder.saveAndClearIP();
4548
4549 // Emit the exception handler block.
4550 CGF.EmitBlock(TryHandler);
4551
4552 // Don't optimize loads of the in-scope locals across this point.
4553 Hazards.emitWriteHazard();
4554
4555 // For a @synchronized (or a @try with no catches), just branch
4556 // through the cleanup to the rethrow block.
4557 if (!isTry || !cast<ObjCAtTryStmt>(S).getNumCatchStmts()) {
4558 // Tell the cleanup not to re-pop the exit.
4559 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CGF.Builder.getFalse(), CallTryExitVar);
4560 CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(FinallyRethrow);
4561
4562 // Otherwise, we have to match against the caught exceptions.
4563 } else {
4564 // Retrieve the exception object. We may emit multiple blocks but
4565 // nothing can cross this so the value is already in SSA form.
4566 llvm::CallInst *Caught =
4567 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getExceptionExtractFn(),
4568 ExceptionData.getPointer(), "caught");
4569
4570 // Push the exception to rethrow onto the EH value stack for the
4571 // benefit of any @throws in the handlers.
4572 CGF.ObjCEHValueStack.push_back(Caught);
4573
4574 const ObjCAtTryStmt* AtTryStmt = cast<ObjCAtTryStmt>(&S);
4575
4576 bool HasFinally = (AtTryStmt->getFinallyStmt() != nullptr);
4577
4578 llvm::BasicBlock *CatchBlock = nullptr;
4579 llvm::BasicBlock *CatchHandler = nullptr;
4580 if (HasFinally) {
4581 // Save the currently-propagating exception before
4582 // objc_exception_try_enter clears the exception slot.
4583 PropagatingExnVar = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(Caught->getType(),
4584 CGF.getPointerAlign(),
4585 "propagating_exception");
4586 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Caught, PropagatingExnVar);
4587
4588 // Enter a new exception try block (in case a @catch block
4589 // throws an exception).
4590 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getExceptionTryEnterFn(),
4591 ExceptionData.getPointer());
4592
4593 llvm::CallInst *SetJmpResult =
4594 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getSetJmpFn(),
4595 SetJmpBuffer, "setjmp.result");
4596 SetJmpResult->setCanReturnTwice();
4597
4598 llvm::Value *Threw =
4599 CGF.Builder.CreateIsNotNull(SetJmpResult, "did_catch_exception");
4600
4601 CatchBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("catch");
4602 CatchHandler = CGF.createBasicBlock("catch_for_catch");
4603 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Threw, CatchHandler, CatchBlock);
4604
4605 CGF.EmitBlock(CatchBlock);
4606 }
4607
4608 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CGF.Builder.getInt1(HasFinally), CallTryExitVar);
4609
4610 // Handle catch list. As a special case we check if everything is
4611 // matched and avoid generating code for falling off the end if
4612 // so.
4613 bool AllMatched = false;
4614 for (unsigned I = 0, N = AtTryStmt->getNumCatchStmts(); I != N; ++I) {
4615 const ObjCAtCatchStmt *CatchStmt = AtTryStmt->getCatchStmt(I);
4616
4617 const VarDecl *CatchParam = CatchStmt->getCatchParamDecl();
4618 const ObjCObjectPointerType *OPT = nullptr;
4619
4620 // catch(...) always matches.
4621 if (!CatchParam) {
4622 AllMatched = true;
4623 } else {
4624 OPT = CatchParam->getType()->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
4625
4626 // catch(id e) always matches under this ABI, since only
4627 // ObjC exceptions end up here in the first place.
4628 // FIXME: For the time being we also match id<X>; this should
4629 // be rejected by Sema instead.
4630 if (OPT && (OPT->isObjCIdType() || OPT->isObjCQualifiedIdType()))
4631 AllMatched = true;
4632 }
4633
4634 // If this is a catch-all, we don't need to test anything.
4635 if (AllMatched) {
4636 CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope CatchVarCleanups(CGF);
4637
4638 if (CatchParam) {
4639 CGF.EmitAutoVarDecl(*CatchParam);
4640 assert(CGF.HaveInsertPoint() && "DeclStmt destroyed insert point?");
4641
4642 // These types work out because ConvertType(id) == i8*.
4643 EmitInitOfCatchParam(CGF, Caught, CatchParam);
4644 }
4645
4646 CGF.EmitStmt(CatchStmt->getCatchBody());
4647
4648 // The scope of the catch variable ends right here.
4649 CatchVarCleanups.ForceCleanup();
4650
4651 CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(FinallyEnd);
4652 break;
4653 }
4654
4655 assert(OPT && "Unexpected non-object pointer type in @catch");
4656 const ObjCObjectType *ObjTy = OPT->getObjectType();
4657
4658 // FIXME: @catch (Class c) ?
4659 ObjCInterfaceDecl *IDecl = ObjTy->getInterface();
4660 assert(IDecl && "Catch parameter must have Objective-C type!");
4661
4662 // Check if the @catch block matches the exception object.
4663 llvm::Value *Class = EmitClassRef(CGF, IDecl);
4664
4665 llvm::Value *matchArgs[] = { Class, Caught };
4666 llvm::CallInst *Match =
4667 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getExceptionMatchFn(),
4668 matchArgs, "match");
4669
4670 llvm::BasicBlock *MatchedBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("match");
4671 llvm::BasicBlock *NextCatchBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("catch.next");
4672
4673 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(CGF.Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Match, "matched"),
4674 MatchedBlock, NextCatchBlock);
4675
4676 // Emit the @catch block.
4677 CGF.EmitBlock(MatchedBlock);
4678
4679 // Collect any cleanups for the catch variable. The scope lasts until
4680 // the end of the catch body.
4681 CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope CatchVarCleanups(CGF);
4682
4683 CGF.EmitAutoVarDecl(*CatchParam);
4684 assert(CGF.HaveInsertPoint() && "DeclStmt destroyed insert point?");
4685
4686 // Initialize the catch variable.
4687 llvm::Value *Tmp =
4688 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Caught,
4689 CGF.ConvertType(CatchParam->getType()));
4690 EmitInitOfCatchParam(CGF, Tmp, CatchParam);
4691
4692 CGF.EmitStmt(CatchStmt->getCatchBody());
4693
4694 // We're done with the catch variable.
4695 CatchVarCleanups.ForceCleanup();
4696
4697 CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(FinallyEnd);
4698
4699 CGF.EmitBlock(NextCatchBlock);
4700 }
4701
4702 CGF.ObjCEHValueStack.pop_back();
4703
4704 // If nothing wanted anything to do with the caught exception,
4705 // kill the extract call.
4706 if (Caught->use_empty())
4707 Caught->eraseFromParent();
4708
4709 if (!AllMatched)
4710 CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(FinallyRethrow);
4711
4712 if (HasFinally) {
4713 // Emit the exception handler for the @catch blocks.
4714 CGF.EmitBlock(CatchHandler);
4715
4716 // In theory we might now need a write hazard, but actually it's
4717 // unnecessary because there's no local-accessing code between
4718 // the try's write hazard and here.
4719 //Hazards.emitWriteHazard();
4720
4721 // Extract the new exception and save it to the
4722 // propagating-exception slot.
4723 assert(PropagatingExnVar.isValid());
4724 llvm::CallInst *NewCaught =
4725 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getExceptionExtractFn(),
4726 ExceptionData.getPointer(), "caught");
4727 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(NewCaught, PropagatingExnVar);
4728
4729 // Don't pop the catch handler; the throw already did.
4730 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CGF.Builder.getFalse(), CallTryExitVar);
4731 CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(FinallyRethrow);
4732 }
4733 }
4734
4735 // Insert read hazards as required in the new blocks.
4736 Hazards.emitHazardsInNewBlocks();
4737
4738 // Pop the cleanup.
4739 CGF.Builder.restoreIP(TryFallthroughIP);
4740 if (CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
4741 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CGF.Builder.getTrue(), CallTryExitVar);
4742 CGF.PopCleanupBlock();
4743 CGF.EmitBlock(FinallyEnd.getBlock(), true);
4744
4745 // Emit the rethrow block.
4746 CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint SavedIP = CGF.Builder.saveAndClearIP();
4747 CGF.EmitBlock(FinallyRethrow.getBlock(), true);
4748 if (CGF.HaveInsertPoint()) {
4749 // If we have a propagating-exception variable, check it.
4750 llvm::Value *PropagatingExn;
4751 if (PropagatingExnVar.isValid()) {
4752 PropagatingExn = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(PropagatingExnVar);
4753
4754 // Otherwise, just look in the buffer for the exception to throw.
4755 } else {
4756 llvm::CallInst *Caught =
4757 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getExceptionExtractFn(),
4758 ExceptionData.getPointer());
4759 PropagatingExn = Caught;
4760 }
4761
4762 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getExceptionThrowFn(),
4763 PropagatingExn);
4764 CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4765 }
4766
4767 CGF.Builder.restoreIP(SavedIP);
4768}
4769
4770void CGObjCMac::EmitThrowStmt(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4771 const ObjCAtThrowStmt &S,
4772 bool ClearInsertionPoint) {
4773 llvm::Value *ExceptionAsObject;
4774
4775 if (const Expr *ThrowExpr = S.getThrowExpr()) {
4776 llvm::Value *Exception = CGF.EmitObjCThrowOperand(ThrowExpr);
4777 ExceptionAsObject =
4778 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Exception, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
4779 } else {
4780 assert((!CGF.ObjCEHValueStack.empty() && CGF.ObjCEHValueStack.back()) &&
4781 "Unexpected rethrow outside @catch block.");
4782 ExceptionAsObject = CGF.ObjCEHValueStack.back();
4783 }
4784
4785 CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getExceptionThrowFn(), ExceptionAsObject)
4786 ->setDoesNotReturn();
4787 CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4788
4789 // Clear the insertion point to indicate we are in unreachable code.
4790 if (ClearInsertionPoint)
4791 CGF.Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
4792}
4793
4794/// EmitObjCWeakRead - Code gen for loading value of a __weak
4795/// object: objc_read_weak (id *src)
4796///
4797llvm::Value * CGObjCMac::EmitObjCWeakRead(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4798 Address AddrWeakObj) {
4799 llvm::Type* DestTy = AddrWeakObj.getElementType();
4800 AddrWeakObj = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(AddrWeakObj,
4801 ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
4802 llvm::Value *read_weak =
4803 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcReadWeakFn(),
4804 AddrWeakObj.getPointer(), "weakread");
4805 read_weak = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(read_weak, DestTy);
4806 return read_weak;
4807}
4808
4809/// EmitObjCWeakAssign - Code gen for assigning to a __weak object.
4810/// objc_assign_weak (id src, id *dst)
4811///
4812void CGObjCMac::EmitObjCWeakAssign(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4813 llvm::Value *src, Address dst) {
4814 llvm::Type * SrcTy = src->getType();
4815 if (!isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) {
4816 unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
4817 assert(Size <= 8 && "does not support size > 8");
4818 src = (Size == 4) ? CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, CGM.Int32Ty)
4819 : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, CGM.Int64Ty);
4820 src = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(src, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
4821 }
4822 src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
4823 dst = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(dst, ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
4824 llvm::Value *args[] = { src, dst.getPointer() };
4825 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignWeakFn(),
4826 args, "weakassign");
4827}
4828
4829/// EmitObjCGlobalAssign - Code gen for assigning to a __strong object.
4830/// objc_assign_global (id src, id *dst)
4831///
4832void CGObjCMac::EmitObjCGlobalAssign(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4833 llvm::Value *src, Address dst,
4834 bool threadlocal) {
4835 llvm::Type * SrcTy = src->getType();
4836 if (!isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) {
4837 unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
4838 assert(Size <= 8 && "does not support size > 8");
4839 src = (Size == 4) ? CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, CGM.Int32Ty)
4840 : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, CGM.Int64Ty);
4841 src = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(src, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
4842 }
4843 src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
4844 dst = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(dst, ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
4845 llvm::Value *args[] = { src, dst.getPointer() };
4846 if (!threadlocal)
4847 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignGlobalFn(),
4848 args, "globalassign");
4849 else
4850 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignThreadLocalFn(),
4851 args, "threadlocalassign");
4852}

4858 llvm::Value *src, Address dst,
4859 llvm::Value *ivarOffset) {

4861 llvm::Type * SrcTy = src->getType();
4862 if (!isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) {

4864 assert(Size <= 8 && "does not support size > 8");

4866 : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, CGM.Int64Ty);

4868 }
4869 src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
4870 dst = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(dst, ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
4871 llvm::Value *args[] = { src, dst.getPointer(), ivarOffset };
4872 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignIvarFn(), args);
4873}

4927/* *** Private Interface *** */
4928
4929std::string CGObjCCommonMac::GetSectionName(StringRef Section,
4930 StringRef MachOAttributes) {
4931 switch (CGM.getTriple().getObjectFormat()) {
4932 default:
4933 llvm_unreachable("unexpected object file format");
4934 case llvm::Triple::MachO: {
4935 if (MachOAttributes.empty())
4936 return ("__DATA," + Section).str();
4937 return ("__DATA," + Section + "," + MachOAttributes).str();
4938 }
4939 case llvm::Triple::ELF:
4940 assert(Section.substr(0, 2) == "__" &&
4941 "expected the name to begin with __");
4942 return Section.substr(2).str();
4943 case llvm::Triple::COFF:
4944 assert(Section.substr(0, 2) == "__" &&
4945 "expected the name to begin with __");
4946 return ("." + Section.substr(2) + "$B").str();
4947 }
4948}

4950/// EmitImageInfo - Emit the image info marker used to encode some module
4951/// level information.
4952///
4953/// See: <rdr://4810609&4810587&4810587>
4954/// struct IMAGE_INFO {
4955/// unsigned version;
4956/// unsigned flags;
4957/// };
4958enum ImageInfoFlags {
4959 eImageInfo_FixAndContinue = (1 << 0), // This flag is no longer set by clang.
4960 eImageInfo_GarbageCollected = (1 << 1),
4961 eImageInfo_GCOnly = (1 << 2),
4962 eImageInfo_OptimizedByDyld = (1 << 3), // This flag is set by the dyld shared cache.
4963
4964 // A flag indicating that the module has no instances of a @synthesize of a
4965 // superclass variable. <rdar://problem/6803242>
4966 eImageInfo_CorrectedSynthesize = (1 << 4), // This flag is no longer set by clang.
4967 eImageInfo_ImageIsSimulated = (1 << 5),
4968 eImageInfo_ClassProperties = (1 << 6)
4969};
4970
4971void CGObjCCommonMac::EmitImageInfo() {
4972 unsigned version = 0; // Version is unused?
4973 std::string Section =
4974 (ObjCABI == 1)
4975 ? "__OBJC,__image_info,regular"
4976 : GetSectionName("__objc_imageinfo", "regular,no_dead_strip");
4977
4978 // Generate module-level named metadata to convey this information to the
4979 // linker and code-gen.
4980 llvm::Module &Mod = CGM.getModule();
4981
4982 // Add the ObjC ABI version to the module flags.
4983 Mod.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "Objective-C Version", ObjCABI);
4984 Mod.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "Objective-C Image Info Version",
4985 version);
4986 Mod.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "Objective-C Image Info Section",
4987 llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, Section));
4988
4989 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC) {
4990 // Non-GC overrides those files which specify GC.
4991 Mod.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override,
4992 "Objective-C Garbage Collection", (uint32_t)0);
4993 } else {
4994 // Add the ObjC garbage collection value.
4995 Mod.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error,
4996 "Objective-C Garbage Collection",
4997 eImageInfo_GarbageCollected);
4998
4999 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::GCOnly) {
5000 // Add the ObjC GC Only value.
5001 Mod.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "Objective-C GC Only",
5002 eImageInfo_GCOnly);
5003
5004 // Require that GC be specified and set to eImageInfo_GarbageCollected.
5005 llvm::Metadata *Ops[2] = {
5006 llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "Objective-C Garbage Collection"),
5007 llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
5008 llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(VMContext), eImageInfo_GarbageCollected))};
5009 Mod.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Require, "Objective-C GC Only",
5010 llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, Ops));
5011 }
5012 }
5013
5014 // Indicate whether we're compiling this to run on a simulator.
5015 if (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isSimulatorEnvironment())
5016 Mod.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "Objective-C Is Simulated",
5017 eImageInfo_ImageIsSimulated);
5018
5019 // Indicate whether we are generating class properties.
5020 Mod.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "Objective-C Class Properties",
5021 eImageInfo_ClassProperties);
5022}

5024// struct objc_module {
5025// unsigned long version;
5026// unsigned long size;
5027// const char *name;
5028// Symtab symtab;
5029// };
5030
5031// FIXME: Get from somewhere
5032static const int ModuleVersion = 7;
5033
5034void CGObjCMac::EmitModuleInfo() {
5035 uint64_t Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.ModuleTy);
5036
5037 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
5038 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ModuleTy);
5039 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.LongTy, ModuleVersion);
5040 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.LongTy, Size);
5041 // This used to be the filename, now it is unused. <rdr://4327263>
5042 values.add(GetClassName(StringRef("")));
5043 values.add(EmitModuleSymbols());
5044 CreateMetadataVar("OBJC_MODULES", values,
5045 "__OBJC,__module_info,regular,no_dead_strip",
5046 CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
5047}
5048
5049llvm::Constant *CGObjCMac::EmitModuleSymbols() {
5050 unsigned NumClasses = DefinedClasses.size();
5051 unsigned NumCategories = DefinedCategories.size();
5052
5053 // Return null if no symbols were defined.
5054 if (!NumClasses && !NumCategories)
5055 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.SymtabPtrTy);
5056
5057 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
5058 auto values = builder.beginStruct();
5059 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.LongTy, 0);
5060 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy);
5061 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.ShortTy, NumClasses);
5062 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.ShortTy, NumCategories);
5063
5064 // The runtime expects exactly the list of defined classes followed
5065 // by the list of defined categories, in a single array.
5066 auto array = values.beginArray(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
5067 for (unsigned i=0; i<NumClasses; i++) {
5068 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = ImplementedClasses[i];
5069 assert(ID);
5070 if (ObjCImplementationDecl *IMP = ID->getImplementation())
5071 // We are implementing a weak imported interface. Give it external linkage
5072 if (ID->isWeakImported() && !IMP->isWeakImported())
5073 DefinedClasses[i]->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage);
5074
5075 array.addBitCast(DefinedClasses[i], ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
5076 }
5077 for (unsigned i=0; i<NumCategories; i++)
5078 array.addBitCast(DefinedCategories[i], ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
5079
5080 array.finishAndAddTo(values);
5081
5082 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CreateMetadataVar(
5083 "OBJC_SYMBOLS", values, "__OBJC,__symbols,regular,no_dead_strip",
5084 CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
5085 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.SymtabPtrTy);
5086}

5090 LazySymbols.insert(II);
5091
5092 llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = ClassReferences[II];
5093
5094 if (!Entry) {
5095 llvm::Constant *Casted =
5096 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GetClassName(II->getName()),
5097 ObjCTypes.ClassPtrTy);
5098 Entry = CreateMetadataVar(
5099 "OBJC_CLASS_REFERENCES_", Casted,
5100 "__OBJC,__cls_refs,literal_pointers,no_dead_strip",
5101 CGM.getPointerAlign(), true);
5102 }
5103
5104 return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Entry, CGF.getPointerAlign());
5105}

5161/// GetIvarLayoutName - Returns a unique constant for the given
5162/// ivar layout bitmap.

5167
5168void IvarLayoutBuilder::visitRecord(const RecordType *RT,
5169 CharUnits offset) {
5170 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
5171
5172 // If this is a union, remember that we had one, because it might mess
5173 // up the ordering of layout entries.
5174 if (RD->isUnion())
5175 IsDisordered = true;
5176
5177 const ASTRecordLayout *recLayout = nullptr;
5178 visitAggregate(RD->field_begin(), RD->field_end(), offset,
5179 [&](const FieldDecl *field) -> CharUnits {
5180 if (!recLayout)
5181 recLayout = &CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
5182 auto offsetInBits = recLayout->getFieldOffset(field->getFieldIndex());
5183 return CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(offsetInBits);
5184 });
5185}
5186
5187template <class Iterator, class GetOffsetFn>
5188void IvarLayoutBuilder::visitAggregate(Iterator begin, Iterator end,
5189 CharUnits aggregateOffset,
5190 const GetOffsetFn &getOffset) {
5191 for (; begin != end; ++begin) {
5192 auto field = *begin;
5193
5194 // Skip over bitfields.
5195 if (field->isBitField()) {
5196 continue;
5197 }
5198
5199 // Compute the offset of the field within the aggregate.
5200 CharUnits fieldOffset = aggregateOffset + getOffset(field);
5201
5202 visitField(field, fieldOffset);
5203 }
5204}
5205
5206/// Collect layout information for the given fields into IvarsInfo.
5207void IvarLayoutBuilder::visitField(const FieldDecl *field,
5208 CharUnits fieldOffset) {
5209 QualType fieldType = field->getType();
5210
5211 // Drill down into arrays.
5212 uint64_t numElts = 1;
5213 if (auto arrayType = CGM.getContext().getAsIncompleteArrayType(fieldType)) {
5214 numElts = 0;
5215 fieldType = arrayType->getElementType();
5216 }
5217 // Unlike incomplete arrays, constant arrays can be nested.
5218 while (auto arrayType = CGM.getContext().getAsConstantArrayType(fieldType)) {
5219 numElts *= arrayType->getSize().getZExtValue();
5220 fieldType = arrayType->getElementType();
5221 }
5222
5223 assert(!fieldType->isArrayType() && "ivar of non-constant array type?");
5224
5225 // If we ended up with a zero-sized array, we've done what we can do within
5226 // the limits of this layout encoding.
5227 if (numElts == 0) return;
5228
5229 // Recurse if the base element type is a record type.
5230 if (auto recType = fieldType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
5231 size_t oldEnd = IvarsInfo.size();
5232
5233 visitRecord(recType, fieldOffset);
5234
5235 // If we have an array, replicate the first entry's layout information.
5236 auto numEltEntries = IvarsInfo.size() - oldEnd;
5237 if (numElts != 1 && numEltEntries != 0) {
5238 CharUnits eltSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(recType);
5239 for (uint64_t eltIndex = 1; eltIndex != numElts; ++eltIndex) {
5240 // Copy the last numEltEntries onto the end of the array, adjusting
5241 // each for the element size.
5242 for (size_t i = 0; i != numEltEntries; ++i) {
5243 auto firstEntry = IvarsInfo[oldEnd + i];
5244 IvarsInfo.push_back(IvarInfo(firstEntry.Offset + eltIndex * eltSize,
5245 firstEntry.SizeInWords));
5246 }
5247 }
5248 }
5249
5250 return;
5251 }
5252
5253 // Classify the element type.
5254 Qualifiers::GC GCAttr = GetGCAttrTypeForType(CGM.getContext(), fieldType);
5255
5256 // If it matches what we're looking for, add an entry.
5257 if ((ForStrongLayout && GCAttr == Qualifiers::Strong)
5258 || (!ForStrongLayout && GCAttr == Qualifiers::Weak)) {
5259 assert(CGM.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(fieldType)
5260 == CGM.getPointerSize());
5261 IvarsInfo.push_back(IvarInfo(fieldOffset, numElts));
5262 }
5263}
5264
5265/// buildBitmap - This routine does the horsework of taking the offsets of
5266/// strong/weak references and creating a bitmap. The bitmap is also
5267/// returned in the given buffer, suitable for being passed to \c dump().
5268llvm::Constant *IvarLayoutBuilder::buildBitmap(CGObjCCommonMac &CGObjC,
5269 llvm::SmallVectorImpl<unsigned char> &buffer) {
5270 // The bitmap is a series of skip/scan instructions, aligned to word
5271 // boundaries. The skip is performed first.
5272 const unsigned char MaxNibble = 0xF;
5273 const unsigned char SkipMask = 0xF0, SkipShift = 4;
5274 const unsigned char ScanMask = 0x0F, ScanShift = 0;
5275
5276 assert(!IvarsInfo.empty() && "generating bitmap for no data");
5277
5278 // Sort the ivar info on byte position in case we encounterred a
5279 // union nested in the ivar list.
5280 if (IsDisordered) {
5281 // This isn't a stable sort, but our algorithm should handle it fine.
5282 llvm::array_pod_sort(IvarsInfo.begin(), IvarsInfo.end());
5283 } else {
5284 assert(std::is_sorted(IvarsInfo.begin(), IvarsInfo.end()));
5285 }
5286 assert(IvarsInfo.back().Offset < InstanceEnd);
5287
5288 assert(buffer.empty());
5289
5290 // Skip the next N words.
5291 auto skip = [&](unsigned numWords) {
5292 assert(numWords > 0);
5293
5294 // Try to merge into the previous byte. Since scans happen second, we
5295 // can't do this if it includes a scan.
5296 if (!buffer.empty() && !(buffer.back() & ScanMask)) {
5297 unsigned lastSkip = buffer.back() >> SkipShift;
5298 if (lastSkip < MaxNibble) {
5299 unsigned claimed = std::min(MaxNibble - lastSkip, numWords);
5300 numWords -= claimed;
5301 lastSkip += claimed;
5302 buffer.back() = (lastSkip << SkipShift);
5303 }
5304 }
5305
5306 while (numWords >= MaxNibble) {
5307 buffer.push_back(MaxNibble << SkipShift);
5308 numWords -= MaxNibble;
5309 }
5310 if (numWords) {
5311 buffer.push_back(numWords << SkipShift);
5312 }
5313 };
5314
5315 // Scan the next N words.
5316 auto scan = [&](unsigned numWords) {
5317 assert(numWords > 0);
5318
5319 // Try to merge into the previous byte. Since scans happen second, we can
5320 // do this even if it includes a skip.
5321 if (!buffer.empty()) {
5322 unsigned lastScan = (buffer.back() & ScanMask) >> ScanShift;
5323 if (lastScan < MaxNibble) {
5324 unsigned claimed = std::min(MaxNibble - lastScan, numWords);
5325 numWords -= claimed;
5326 lastScan += claimed;
5327 buffer.back() = (buffer.back() & SkipMask) | (lastScan << ScanShift);
5328 }
5329 }
5330
5331 while (numWords >= MaxNibble) {
5332 buffer.push_back(MaxNibble << ScanShift);
5333 numWords -= MaxNibble;
5334 }
5335 if (numWords) {
5336 buffer.push_back(numWords << ScanShift);
5337 }
5338 };
5339
5340 // One past the end of the last scan.
5341 unsigned endOfLastScanInWords = 0;
5342 const CharUnits WordSize = CGM.getPointerSize();
5343
5344 // Consider all the scan requests.
5345 for (auto &request : IvarsInfo) {
5346 CharUnits beginOfScan = request.Offset - InstanceBegin;
5347
5348 // Ignore scan requests that don't start at an even multiple of the
5349 // word size. We can't encode them.
5350 if ((beginOfScan % WordSize) != 0) continue;
5351
5352 // Ignore scan requests that start before the instance start.
5353 // This assumes that scans never span that boundary. The boundary
5354 // isn't the true start of the ivars, because in the fragile-ARC case
5355 // it's rounded up to word alignment, but the test above should leave
5356 // us ignoring that possibility.
5357 if (beginOfScan.isNegative()) {
5358 assert(request.Offset + request.SizeInWords * WordSize <= InstanceBegin);
5359 continue;
5360 }
5361
5362 unsigned beginOfScanInWords = beginOfScan / WordSize;
5363 unsigned endOfScanInWords = beginOfScanInWords + request.SizeInWords;
5364
5365 // If the scan starts some number of words after the last one ended,
5366 // skip forward.
5367 if (beginOfScanInWords > endOfLastScanInWords) {
5368 skip(beginOfScanInWords - endOfLastScanInWords);
5369
5370 // Otherwise, start scanning where the last left off.
5371 } else {
5372 beginOfScanInWords = endOfLastScanInWords;
5373
5374 // If that leaves us with nothing to scan, ignore this request.
5375 if (beginOfScanInWords >= endOfScanInWords) continue;
5376 }
5377
5378 // Scan to the end of the request.
5379 assert(beginOfScanInWords < endOfScanInWords);
5380 scan(endOfScanInWords - beginOfScanInWords);
5381 endOfLastScanInWords = endOfScanInWords;
5382 }
5383
5384 if (buffer.empty())
5385 return llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
5386
5387 // For GC layouts, emit a skip to the end of the allocation so that we
5388 // have precise information about the entire thing. This isn't useful
5389 // or necessary for the ARC-style layout strings.
5390 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC) {
5391 unsigned lastOffsetInWords =
5392 (InstanceEnd - InstanceBegin + WordSize - CharUnits::One()) / WordSize;
5393 if (lastOffsetInWords > endOfLastScanInWords) {
5394 skip(lastOffsetInWords - endOfLastScanInWords);
5395 }
5396 }
5397
5398 // Null terminate the string.
5399 buffer.push_back(0);
5400
5401 auto *Entry = CGObjC.CreateCStringLiteral(
5402 reinterpret_cast<char *>(buffer.data()), ObjCLabelType::ClassName);
5403 return getConstantGEP(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Entry, 0, 0);
5404}
5405
5406/// BuildIvarLayout - Builds ivar layout bitmap for the class
5407/// implementation for the __strong or __weak case.
5408/// The layout map displays which words in ivar list must be skipped
5409/// and which must be scanned by GC (see below). String is built of bytes.
5410/// Each byte is divided up in two nibbles (4-bit each). Left nibble is count
5411/// of words to skip and right nibble is count of words to scan. So, each
5412/// nibble represents up to 15 workds to skip or scan. Skipping the rest is
5413/// represented by a 0x00 byte which also ends the string.
5414/// 1. when ForStrongLayout is true, following ivars are scanned:
5415/// - id, Class
5416/// - object *
5417/// - __strong anything
5418///
5419/// 2. When ForStrongLayout is false, following ivars are scanned:
5420/// - __weak anything
5421///
5422llvm::Constant *
5423CGObjCCommonMac::BuildIvarLayout(const ObjCImplementationDecl *OMD,
5424 CharUnits beginOffset, CharUnits endOffset,
5425 bool ForStrongLayout, bool HasMRCWeakIvars) {
5426 // If this is MRC, and we're either building a strong layout or there
5427 // are no weak ivars, bail out early.
5428 llvm::Type *PtrTy = CGM.Int8PtrTy;
5429 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC &&
5430 !CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
5431 (ForStrongLayout || !HasMRCWeakIvars))
5432 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(PtrTy);
5433
5434 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OI = OMD->getClassInterface();
5435 SmallVector<const ObjCIvarDecl*, 32> ivars;
5436
5437 // GC layout strings include the complete object layout, possibly
5438 // inaccurately in the non-fragile ABI; the runtime knows how to fix this
5439 // up.
5440 //
5441 // ARC layout strings only include the class's ivars. In non-fragile
5442 // runtimes, that means starting at InstanceStart, rounded up to word
5443 // alignment. In fragile runtimes, there's no InstanceStart, so it means
5444 // starting at the offset of the first ivar, rounded up to word alignment.
5445 //
5446 // MRC weak layout strings follow the ARC style.
5447 CharUnits baseOffset;
5448 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC) {
5449 for (const ObjCIvarDecl *IVD = OI->all_declared_ivar_begin();
5450 IVD; IVD = IVD->getNextIvar())
5451 ivars.push_back(IVD);
5452
5453 if (isNonFragileABI()) {
5454 baseOffset = beginOffset; // InstanceStart
5455 } else if (!ivars.empty()) {
5456 baseOffset =
5457 CharUnits::fromQuantity(ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, OMD, ivars[0]));
5458 } else {
5459 baseOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
5460 }
5461
5462 baseOffset = baseOffset.alignTo(CGM.getPointerAlign());
5463 }
5464 else {
5465 CGM.getContext().DeepCollectObjCIvars(OI, true, ivars);
5466
5467 baseOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
5468 }
5469
5470 if (ivars.empty())
5471 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(PtrTy);
5472
5473 IvarLayoutBuilder builder(CGM, baseOffset, endOffset, ForStrongLayout);
5474
5475 builder.visitAggregate(ivars.begin(), ivars.end(), CharUnits::Zero(),
5476 [&](const ObjCIvarDecl *ivar) -> CharUnits {
5477 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, OMD, ivar));
5478 });
5479
5480 if (!builder.hasBitmapData())
5481 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(PtrTy);
5482
5483 llvm::SmallVector<unsigned char, 4> buffer;
5484 llvm::Constant *C = builder.buildBitmap(*this, buffer);
5485
5486 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCGCBitmapPrint && !buffer.empty()) {
5487 printf("\n%s ivar layout for class '%s': ",
5488 ForStrongLayout ? "strong" : "weak",
5489 OMD->getClassInterface()->getName().str().c_str());
5490 builder.dump(buffer);
5491 }
5492 return C;
5493}

5547void CGObjCCommonMac::GetNameForMethod(const ObjCMethodDecl *D,
5548 const ObjCContainerDecl *CD,
5549 SmallVectorImpl<char> &Name) {
5550 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Name);
5551 assert (CD && "Missing container decl in GetNameForMethod");
5552 OS << '\01' << (D->isInstanceMethod() ? '-' : '+')
5553 << '[' << CD->getName();
5554 if (const ObjCCategoryImplDecl *CID =
5555 dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(D->getDeclContext()))
5556 OS << '(' << *CID << ')';
5557 OS << ' ' << D->getSelector().getAsString() << ']';
5558}
5559
5560void CGObjCMac::FinishModule() {
5561 EmitModuleInfo();
5562
5563 // Emit the dummy bodies for any protocols which were referenced but
5564 // never defined.
5565 for (auto &entry : Protocols) {
5566 llvm::GlobalVariable *global = entry.second;
5567 if (global->hasInitializer())
5568 continue;
5569
5570 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
5571 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ProtocolTy);
5572 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolExtensionPtrTy);
5573 values.add(GetClassName(entry.first->getName()));
5574 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListPtrTy);
5575 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.MethodDescriptionListPtrTy);
5576 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.MethodDescriptionListPtrTy);
5577 values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(global);
5578 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(global);
5579 }
5580
5581 // Add assembler directives to add lazy undefined symbol references
5582 // for classes which are referenced but not defined. This is
5583 // important for correct linker interaction.
5584 //
5585 // FIXME: It would be nice if we had an LLVM construct for this.
5586 if ((!LazySymbols.empty() || !DefinedSymbols.empty()) &&
5587 CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO()) {
5588 SmallString<256> Asm;
5589 Asm += CGM.getModule().getModuleInlineAsm();
5590 if (!Asm.empty() && Asm.back() != '\n')
5591 Asm += '\n';
5592
5593 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Asm);
5594 for (const auto *Sym : DefinedSymbols)
5595 OS << "\t.objc_class_name_" << Sym->getName() << "=0\n"
5596 << "\t.globl .objc_class_name_" << Sym->getName() << "\n";
5597 for (const auto *Sym : LazySymbols)
5598 OS << "\t.lazy_reference .objc_class_name_" << Sym->getName() << "\n";
5599 for (const auto &Category : DefinedCategoryNames)
5600 OS << "\t.objc_category_name_" << Category << "=0\n"
5601 << "\t.globl .objc_category_name_" << Category << "\n";
5602
5603 CGM.getModule().setModuleInlineAsm(OS.str());
5604 }
5605}
