5959 llvm::Type *params[] = { ObjectPtrTy, SelectorPtrTy };
5960 ImpnfABITy = llvm::FunctionType::get(ObjectPtrTy, params, false)
5961 ->getPointerTo(CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
5962
5963 // struct _class_t {
5964 // struct _class_t *isa;
5965 // struct _class_t * const superclass;
5966 // void *cache;
5967 // IMP *vtable;
5968 // struct class_ro_t *ro;
5969 // }
5970
5971 ClassnfABITy = llvm::StructType::create(VMContext, "struct._class_t");
5972 ClassnfABITy->setBody(llvm::PointerType::get(ClassnfABITy, DefaultAS),
5973 llvm::PointerType::get(ClassnfABITy, DefaultAS),
5974 CachePtrTy,
5975 llvm::PointerType::get(ImpnfABITy, DefaultAS),
5976 llvm::PointerType::get(ClassRonfABITy, DefaultAS));
5977
5978 // LLVM for struct _class_t *
5979 ClassnfABIPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(ClassnfABITy, DefaultAS);
5980
5981 // struct _category_t {
5982 // const char * const name;
5983 // struct _class_t *const cls;
5984 // const struct _method_list_t * const instance_methods;
5985 // const struct _method_list_t * const class_methods;
5986 // const struct _protocol_list_t * const protocols;
5987 // const struct _prop_list_t * const properties;
5988 // const struct _prop_list_t * const class_properties;
5989 // const uint32_t size;
5990 // }
5991 CategorynfABITy = llvm::StructType::create(
5992 "struct._category_t", Int8PtrTy, ClassnfABIPtrTy, MethodListnfABIPtrTy,
5993 MethodListnfABIPtrTy, ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy, PropertyListPtrTy,
5994 PropertyListPtrTy, IntTy);
5995
5996 // New types for nonfragile abi messaging.
5997 CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
5998 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
5999
6000 // MessageRefTy - LLVM for:
6001 // struct _message_ref_t {
6002 // IMP messenger;
6003 // SEL name;
6004 // };
6005
6006 // First the clang type for struct _message_ref_t
6007 RecordDecl *RD = RecordDecl::Create(Ctx, TTK_Struct,
6008 Ctx.getTranslationUnitDecl(),
6009 SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
6010 &Ctx.Idents.get("_message_ref_t"));
6011 RD->addDecl(FieldDecl::Create(Ctx, RD, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
6012 nullptr, Ctx.VoidPtrTy, nullptr, nullptr, false,
6013 ICIS_NoInit));
6014 RD->addDecl(FieldDecl::Create(Ctx, RD, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
6015 nullptr, Ctx.getObjCSelType(), nullptr, nullptr,
6016 false, ICIS_NoInit));
6017 RD->completeDefinition();
6018
6019 MessageRefCTy = Ctx.getTagDeclType(RD);
6020 MessageRefCPtrTy = Ctx.getPointerType(MessageRefCTy);
6021 MessageRefTy = cast<llvm::StructType>(Types.ConvertType(MessageRefCTy));
6022
6023 // MessageRefPtrTy - LLVM for struct _message_ref_t*
6024 MessageRefPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(MessageRefTy, DefaultAS);
6025
6026 // SuperMessageRefTy - LLVM for:
6027 // struct _super_message_ref_t {
6028 // SUPER_IMP messenger;
6029 // SEL name;
6030 // };
6031 SuperMessageRefTy = llvm::StructType::create("struct._super_message_ref_t",
6032 ImpnfABITy, SelectorPtrTy);
6033
6034 // SuperMessageRefPtrTy - LLVM for struct _super_message_ref_t*
6035 SuperMessageRefPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(SuperMessageRefTy, DefaultAS);
6036
6037
6038 // struct objc_typeinfo {
6039 // const void** vtable; // objc_ehtype_vtable + 2
6040 // const char* name; // c++ typeinfo string
6041 // Class cls;
6042 // };
6043 EHTypeTy = llvm::StructType::create("struct._objc_typeinfo",
6044 llvm::PointerType::get(Int8PtrTy, DefaultAS),
6045 Int8PtrTy, ClassnfABIPtrTy);
6046 EHTypePtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(EHTypeTy, DefaultAS);
6047}
6048
6049llvm::Function *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::ModuleInitFunction() {
6050 FinishNonFragileABIModule();
6051
6052 return nullptr;
6053}
6054
6055void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::AddModuleClassList(
6056 ArrayRef<llvm::GlobalValue *> Container, StringRef SymbolName,
6057 StringRef SectionName) {
6058 unsigned NumClasses = Container.size();
6059
6060 if (!NumClasses)
6061 return;
6062
6063 SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 8> Symbols(NumClasses);
6064 for (unsigned i=0; i<NumClasses; i++)
6065 Symbols[i] = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Container[i],
6066 ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
6067 llvm::Constant *Init =
6068 llvm::ConstantArray::get(llvm::ArrayType::get(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy,
6069 Symbols.size()),
6070 Symbols);
6071
6072 // Section name is obtained by calling GetSectionName, which returns
6073 // sections in the __DATA segment on MachO.
6074 assert((!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO() ||
6075 SectionName.startswith("__DATA")) &&
6076 "SectionName expected to start with __DATA on MachO");
6077 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes LT =
6078 getLinkageTypeForObjCMetadata(CGM, SectionName);
6079 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
6080 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Init->getType(), false, LT, Init,
6081 SymbolName);
6082 GV->setAlignment(CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(Init->getType()));
6083 GV->setSection(SectionName);
6084 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
6085}
6086
6087void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::FinishNonFragileABIModule() {
6088 // nonfragile abi has no module definition.
6089
6090 // Build list of all implemented class addresses in array
6091 // L_OBJC_LABEL_CLASS_$.
6092
6093 for (unsigned i=0, NumClasses=ImplementedClasses.size(); i<NumClasses; i++) {
6094 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = ImplementedClasses[i];
6095 assert(ID);
6096 if (ObjCImplementationDecl *IMP = ID->getImplementation())
6097 // We are implementing a weak imported interface. Give it external linkage
6098 if (ID->isWeakImported() && !IMP->isWeakImported()) {
6099 DefinedClasses[i]->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage);
6100 DefinedMetaClasses[i]->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage);
6101 }
6102 }
6103
6104 AddModuleClassList(DefinedClasses, "OBJC_LABEL_CLASS_$",
6105 GetSectionName("__objc_classlist",
6106 "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6107
6108 AddModuleClassList(DefinedNonLazyClasses, "OBJC_LABEL_NONLAZY_CLASS_$",
6109 GetSectionName("__objc_nlclslist",
6110 "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6111
6112 // Build list of all implemented category addresses in array
6113 // L_OBJC_LABEL_CATEGORY_$.
6114 AddModuleClassList(DefinedCategories, "OBJC_LABEL_CATEGORY_$",
6115 GetSectionName("__objc_catlist",
6116 "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6117 AddModuleClassList(DefinedStubCategories, "OBJC_LABEL_STUB_CATEGORY_$",
6118 GetSectionName("__objc_catlist2",
6119 "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6120 AddModuleClassList(DefinedNonLazyCategories, "OBJC_LABEL_NONLAZY_CATEGORY_$",
6121 GetSectionName("__objc_nlcatlist",
6122 "regular,no_dead_strip"));
6123
6124 EmitImageInfo();
6125}
6126
6127/// isVTableDispatchedSelector - Returns true if SEL is not in the list of
6128/// VTableDispatchMethods; false otherwise. What this means is that
6129/// except for the 19 selectors in the list, we generate 32bit-style
6130/// message dispatch call for all the rest.
6131bool CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::isVTableDispatchedSelector(Selector Sel) {
6132 // At various points we've experimented with using vtable-based
6133 // dispatch for all methods.
6134 switch (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getObjCDispatchMethod()) {
6135 case CodeGenOptions::Legacy:
6136 return false;
6137 case CodeGenOptions::NonLegacy:
6138 return true;
6139 case CodeGenOptions::Mixed:
6140 break;
6141 }
6142
6143 // If so, see whether this selector is in the white-list of things which must
6144 // use the new dispatch convention. We lazily build a dense set for this.
6145 if (VTableDispatchMethods.empty()) {
6146 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("alloc"));
6147 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("class"));
6148 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("self"));
6149 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("isFlipped"));
6150 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("length"));
6151 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("count"));
6152
6153 // These are vtable-based if GC is disabled.
6154 // Optimistically use vtable dispatch for hybrid compiles.
6155 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::GCOnly) {
6156 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("retain"));
6157 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("release"));
6158 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("autorelease"));
6159 }
6160
6161 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("allocWithZone"));
6162 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("isKindOfClass"));
6163 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("respondsToSelector"));
6164 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("objectForKey"));
6165 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("objectAtIndex"));
6166 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("isEqualToString"));
6167 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("isEqual"));
6168
6169 // These are vtable-based if GC is enabled.
6170 // Optimistically use vtable dispatch for hybrid compiles.
6171 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC) {
6172 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetNullarySelector("hash"));
6173 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(GetUnarySelector("addObject"));
6174
6175 // "countByEnumeratingWithState:objects:count"
6176 IdentifierInfo *KeyIdents[] = {
6177 &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("countByEnumeratingWithState"),
6178 &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("objects"),
6179 &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("count")
6180 };
6181 VTableDispatchMethods.insert(
6182 CGM.getContext().Selectors.getSelector(3, KeyIdents));
6183 }
6184 }
6185
6186 return VTableDispatchMethods.count(Sel);
6187}
6188
6189/// BuildClassRoTInitializer - generate meta-data for:
6190/// struct _class_ro_t {
6191/// uint32_t const flags;
6192/// uint32_t const instanceStart;
6193/// uint32_t const instanceSize;
6194/// uint32_t const reserved; // only when building for 64bit targets
6195/// const uint8_t * const ivarLayout;
6196/// const char *const name;
6197/// const struct _method_list_t * const baseMethods;
6198/// const struct _protocol_list_t *const baseProtocols;
6199/// const struct _ivar_list_t *const ivars;
6200/// const uint8_t * const weakIvarLayout;
6201/// const struct _prop_list_t * const properties;
6202/// }
6203///
6204llvm::GlobalVariable * CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::BuildClassRoTInitializer(
6205 unsigned flags,
6206 unsigned InstanceStart,
6207 unsigned InstanceSize,
6208 const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID) {
6209 std::string ClassName = ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6210
6211 CharUnits beginInstance = CharUnits::fromQuantity(InstanceStart);
6212 CharUnits endInstance = CharUnits::fromQuantity(InstanceSize);
6213
6214 bool hasMRCWeak = false;
6215 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
6216 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_CompiledByARC;
6217 else if ((hasMRCWeak = hasMRCWeakIvars(CGM, ID)))
6218 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasMRCWeakIvars;
6219
6220 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6221 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ClassRonfABITy);
6222
6223 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, flags);
6224 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, InstanceStart);
6225 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, InstanceSize);
6226 values.add((flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta)
6227 ? GetIvarLayoutName(nullptr, ObjCTypes)
6228 : BuildStrongIvarLayout(ID, beginInstance, endInstance));
6229 values.add(GetClassName(ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()));
6230
6231 // const struct _method_list_t * const baseMethods;
6232 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl*, 16> methods;
6233 if (flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta) {
6234 for (const auto *MD : ID->class_methods())
6235 methods.push_back(MD);
6236 } else {
6237 for (const auto *MD : ID->instance_methods())
6238 methods.push_back(MD);
6239
6240 for (const auto *PID : ID->property_impls()) {
6241 if (PID->getPropertyImplementation() == ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Synthesize){
6242 ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = PID->getPropertyDecl();
6243
6244 if (auto MD = PD->getGetterMethodDecl())
6245 if (GetMethodDefinition(MD))
6246 methods.push_back(MD);
6247 if (auto MD = PD->getSetterMethodDecl())
6248 if (GetMethodDefinition(MD))
6249 methods.push_back(MD);
6250 }
6251 }
6252 }
6253
6254 values.add(emitMethodList(ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6255 (flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta)
6256 ? MethodListType::ClassMethods
6257 : MethodListType::InstanceMethods,
6258 methods));
6259
6260 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID = ID->getClassInterface();
6261 assert(OID && "CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::BuildClassRoTInitializer");
6262 values.add(EmitProtocolList("_OBJC_CLASS_PROTOCOLS_$_"
6263 + OID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6264 OID->all_referenced_protocol_begin(),
6265 OID->all_referenced_protocol_end()));
6266
6267 if (flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta) {
6268 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.IvarListnfABIPtrTy);
6269 values.add(GetIvarLayoutName(nullptr, ObjCTypes));
6270 values.add(EmitPropertyList(
6271 "_OBJC_$_CLASS_PROP_LIST_" + ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6272 ID, ID->getClassInterface(), ObjCTypes, true));
6273 } else {
6274 values.add(EmitIvarList(ID));
6275 values.add(BuildWeakIvarLayout(ID, beginInstance, endInstance, hasMRCWeak));
6276 values.add(EmitPropertyList(
6277 "_OBJC_$_PROP_LIST_" + ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6278 ID, ID->getClassInterface(), ObjCTypes, false));
6279 }
6280
6281 llvm::SmallString<64> roLabel;
6282 llvm::raw_svector_ostream(roLabel)
6283 << ((flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Meta) ? "_OBJC_METACLASS_RO_$_"
6284 : "_OBJC_CLASS_RO_$_")
6285 << ClassName;
6286
6287 return finishAndCreateGlobal(values, roLabel, CGM);
6288}
6289
6290/// Build the metaclass object for a class.
6291///
6292/// struct _class_t {
6293/// struct _class_t *isa;
6294/// struct _class_t * const superclass;
6295/// void *cache;
6296/// IMP *vtable;
6297/// struct class_ro_t *ro;
6298/// }
6299///
6300llvm::GlobalVariable *
6301CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::BuildClassObject(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *CI,
6302 bool isMetaclass,
6303 llvm::Constant *IsAGV,
6304 llvm::Constant *SuperClassGV,
6305 llvm::Constant *ClassRoGV,
6306 bool HiddenVisibility) {
6307 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6308 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy);
6309 values.add(IsAGV);
6310 if (SuperClassGV) {
6311 values.add(SuperClassGV);
6312 } else {
6313 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABIPtrTy);
6314 }
6315 values.add(ObjCEmptyCacheVar);
6316 values.add(ObjCEmptyVtableVar);
6317 values.add(ClassRoGV);
6318
6319 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
6320 cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GetClassGlobal(CI, isMetaclass, ForDefinition));
6321 values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(GV);
6322
6323 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
6324 GV->setSection("__DATA, __objc_data");
6325 GV->setAlignment(
6326 CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy));
6327 if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
6328 if (HiddenVisibility)
6329 GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
6330 return GV;
6331}
6332
6333bool CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::ImplementationIsNonLazy(
6334 const ObjCImplDecl *OD) const {
6335 return OD->getClassMethod(GetNullarySelector("load")) != nullptr ||
6336 OD->getClassInterface()->hasAttr<ObjCNonLazyClassAttr>() ||
6337 OD->hasAttr<ObjCNonLazyClassAttr>();
6338}
6339
6340void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClassSizeInfo(const ObjCImplementationDecl *OID,
6341 uint32_t &InstanceStart,
6342 uint32_t &InstanceSize) {
6343 const ASTRecordLayout &RL =
6344 CGM.getContext().getASTObjCImplementationLayout(OID);
6345
6346 // InstanceSize is really instance end.
6347 InstanceSize = RL.getDataSize().getQuantity();
6348
6349 // If there are no fields, the start is the same as the end.
6350 if (!RL.getFieldCount())
6351 InstanceStart = InstanceSize;
6352 else
6353 InstanceStart = RL.getFieldOffset(0) / CGM.getContext().getCharWidth();
6354}
6355
6356static llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes getStorage(CodeGenModule &CGM,
6357 StringRef Name) {
6358 IdentifierInfo &II = CGM.getContext().Idents.get(Name);
6359 TranslationUnitDecl *TUDecl = CGM.getContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
6360 DeclContext *DC = TranslationUnitDecl::castToDeclContext(TUDecl);
6361
6362 const VarDecl *VD = nullptr;
6363 for (const auto &Result : DC->lookup(&II))
6364 if ((VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Result)))
6365 break;
6366
6367 if (!VD)
6368 return llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass;
6369 if (VD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
6370 return llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass;
6371 if (VD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
6372 return llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass;
6373 return llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass;
6374}
6375
6376void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateClass(const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID) {
6377 if (!ObjCEmptyCacheVar) {
6378 ObjCEmptyCacheVar =
6379 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.CacheTy, false,
6380 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
6381 "_objc_empty_cache");
6382 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
6383 ObjCEmptyCacheVar->setDLLStorageClass(getStorage(CGM, "_objc_empty_cache"));
6384
6385 // Only OS X with deployment version <10.9 use the empty vtable symbol
6386 const llvm::Triple &Triple = CGM.getTarget().getTriple();
6387 if (Triple.isMacOSX() && Triple.isMacOSXVersionLT(10, 9))
6388 ObjCEmptyVtableVar =
6389 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ImpnfABITy, false,
6390 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
6391 "_objc_empty_vtable");
6392 else
6393 ObjCEmptyVtableVar =
6394 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(ObjCTypes.ImpnfABITy->getPointerTo(
6395 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()));
6396 }
6397
6398 // FIXME: Is this correct (that meta class size is never computed)?
6399 uint32_t InstanceStart =
6400 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy);
6401 uint32_t InstanceSize = InstanceStart;
6402 uint32_t flags = NonFragileABI_Class_Meta;
6403
6404 llvm::Constant *SuperClassGV, *IsAGV;
6405
6406 const auto *CI = ID->getClassInterface();
6407 assert(CI && "CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateClass - class is 0");
6408
6409 // Build the flags for the metaclass.
6410 bool classIsHidden = (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
6411 ? !CI->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()
6412 : CI->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility;
6413 if (classIsHidden)
6414 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Hidden;
6415
6416 // FIXME: why is this flag set on the metaclass?
6417 // ObjC metaclasses have no fields and don't really get constructed.
6418 if (ID->hasNonZeroConstructors() || ID->hasDestructors()) {
6419 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXStructors;
6420 if (!ID->hasNonZeroConstructors())
6421 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXDestructorOnly;
6422 }
6423
6424 if (!CI->getSuperClass()) {
6425 // class is root
6426 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Root;
6427
6428 SuperClassGV = GetClassGlobal(CI, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition);
6429 IsAGV = GetClassGlobal(CI, /*metaclass*/ true, NotForDefinition);
6430 } else {
6431 // Has a root. Current class is not a root.
6432 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Root = ID->getClassInterface();
6433 while (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super = Root->getSuperClass())
6434 Root = Super;
6435
6436 const auto *Super = CI->getSuperClass();
6437 IsAGV = GetClassGlobal(Root, /*metaclass*/ true, NotForDefinition);
6438 SuperClassGV = GetClassGlobal(Super, /*metaclass*/ true, NotForDefinition);
6439 }
6440
6441 llvm::GlobalVariable *CLASS_RO_GV =
6442 BuildClassRoTInitializer(flags, InstanceStart, InstanceSize, ID);
6443
6444 llvm::GlobalVariable *MetaTClass =
6445 BuildClassObject(CI, /*metaclass*/ true,
6446 IsAGV, SuperClassGV, CLASS_RO_GV, classIsHidden);
6447 CGM.setGVProperties(MetaTClass, CI);
6448 DefinedMetaClasses.push_back(MetaTClass);
6449
6450 // Metadata for the class
6451 flags = 0;
6452 if (classIsHidden)
6453 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Hidden;
6454
6455 if (ID->hasNonZeroConstructors() || ID->hasDestructors()) {
6456 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXStructors;
6457
6458 // Set a flag to enable a runtime optimization when a class has
6459 // fields that require destruction but which don't require
6460 // anything except zero-initialization during construction. This
6461 // is most notably true of __strong and __weak types, but you can
6462 // also imagine there being C++ types with non-trivial default
6463 // constructors that merely set all fields to null.
6464 if (!ID->hasNonZeroConstructors())
6465 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_HasCXXDestructorOnly;
6466 }
6467
6468 if (hasObjCExceptionAttribute(CGM.getContext(), CI))
6469 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Exception;
6470
6471 if (!CI->getSuperClass()) {
6472 flags |= NonFragileABI_Class_Root;
6473 SuperClassGV = nullptr;
6474 } else {
6475 // Has a root. Current class is not a root.
6476 const auto *Super = CI->getSuperClass();
6477 SuperClassGV = GetClassGlobal(Super, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition);
6478 }
6479
6480 GetClassSizeInfo(ID, InstanceStart, InstanceSize);
6481 CLASS_RO_GV =
6482 BuildClassRoTInitializer(flags, InstanceStart, InstanceSize, ID);
6483
6484 llvm::GlobalVariable *ClassMD =
6485 BuildClassObject(CI, /*metaclass*/ false,
6486 MetaTClass, SuperClassGV, CLASS_RO_GV, classIsHidden);
6487 CGM.setGVProperties(ClassMD, CI);
6488 DefinedClasses.push_back(ClassMD);
6489 ImplementedClasses.push_back(CI);
6490
6491 // Determine if this class is also "non-lazy".
6492 if (ImplementationIsNonLazy(ID))
6493 DefinedNonLazyClasses.push_back(ClassMD);
6494
6495 // Force the definition of the EHType if necessary.
6496 if (flags & NonFragileABI_Class_Exception)
6497 (void) GetInterfaceEHType(CI, ForDefinition);
6498 // Make sure method definition entries are all clear for next implementation.
6499 MethodDefinitions.clear();
6500}
6501
6502/// GenerateProtocolRef - This routine is called to generate code for
6503/// a protocol reference expression; as in:
6504/// @code
6505/// @protocol(Proto1);
6506/// @endcode
6507/// It generates a weak reference to l_OBJC_PROTOCOL_REFERENCE_$_Proto1
6508/// which will hold address of the protocol meta-data.
6509///
6510llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateProtocolRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
6511 const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
6512
6513 // This routine is called for @protocol only. So, we must build definition
6514 // of protocol's meta-data (not a reference to it!)
6515 //
6516 llvm::Constant *Init =
6517 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GetOrEmitProtocol(PD),
6518 ObjCTypes.getExternalProtocolPtrTy());
6519
6520 std::string ProtocolName("_OBJC_PROTOCOL_REFERENCE_$_");
6521 ProtocolName += PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6522
6523 CharUnits Align = CGF.getPointerAlign();
6524
6525 llvm::GlobalVariable *PTGV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(ProtocolName);
6526 if (PTGV)
6527 return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(PTGV, Align);
6528 PTGV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Init->getType(), false,
6529 llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, Init,
6530 ProtocolName);
6531 PTGV->setSection(GetSectionName("__objc_protorefs",
6532 "coalesced,no_dead_strip"));
6533 PTGV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
6534 PTGV->setAlignment(Align.getQuantity());
6535 if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
6536 PTGV->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ProtocolName));
6537 CGM.addUsedGlobal(PTGV);
6538 return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(PTGV, Align);
6539}
6540
6541/// GenerateCategory - Build metadata for a category implementation.
6542/// struct _category_t {
6543/// const char * const name;
6544/// struct _class_t *const cls;
6545/// const struct _method_list_t * const instance_methods;
6546/// const struct _method_list_t * const class_methods;
6547/// const struct _protocol_list_t * const protocols;
6548/// const struct _prop_list_t * const properties;
6549/// const struct _prop_list_t * const class_properties;
6550/// const uint32_t size;
6551/// }
6552///
6553void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateCategory(const ObjCCategoryImplDecl *OCD) {
6554 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Interface = OCD->getClassInterface();
6555 const char *Prefix = "_OBJC_$_CATEGORY_";
6556
6557 llvm::SmallString<64> ExtCatName(Prefix);
6558 ExtCatName += Interface->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6559 ExtCatName += "_$_";
6560 ExtCatName += OCD->getNameAsString();
6561
6562 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6563 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.CategorynfABITy);
6564 values.add(GetClassName(OCD->getIdentifier()->getName()));
6565 // meta-class entry symbol
6566 values.add(GetClassGlobal(Interface, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition));
6567 std::string listName =
6568 (Interface->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString() + "_$_" + OCD->getName()).str();
6569
6570 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl *, 16> instanceMethods;
6571 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl *, 8> classMethods;
6572 for (const auto *MD : OCD->methods()) {
6573 if (MD->isInstanceMethod()) {
6574 instanceMethods.push_back(MD);
6575 } else {
6576 classMethods.push_back(MD);
6577 }
6578 }
6579
6580 values.add(emitMethodList(listName, MethodListType::CategoryInstanceMethods,
6581 instanceMethods));
6582 values.add(emitMethodList(listName, MethodListType::CategoryClassMethods,
6583 classMethods));
6584
6585 const ObjCCategoryDecl *Category =
6586 Interface->FindCategoryDeclaration(OCD->getIdentifier());
6587 if (Category) {
6588 SmallString<256> ExtName;
6589 llvm::raw_svector_ostream(ExtName) << Interface->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString() << "_$_"
6590 << OCD->getName();
6591 values.add(EmitProtocolList("_OBJC_CATEGORY_PROTOCOLS_$_"
6592 + Interface->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString() + "_$_"
6593 + Category->getName(),
6594 Category->protocol_begin(),
6595 Category->protocol_end()));
6596 values.add(EmitPropertyList("_OBJC_$_PROP_LIST_" + ExtName.str(),
6597 OCD, Category, ObjCTypes, false));
6598 values.add(EmitPropertyList("_OBJC_$_CLASS_PROP_LIST_" + ExtName.str(),
6599 OCD, Category, ObjCTypes, true));
6600 } else {
6601 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy);
6602 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.PropertyListPtrTy);
6603 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.PropertyListPtrTy);
6604 }
6605
6606 unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.CategorynfABITy);
6607 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Size);
6608
6609 llvm::GlobalVariable *GCATV =
6610 finishAndCreateGlobal(values, ExtCatName.str(), CGM);
6611 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GCATV);
6612 if (Interface->hasAttr<ObjCClassStubAttr>())
6613 DefinedStubCategories.push_back(GCATV);
6614 else
6615 DefinedCategories.push_back(GCATV);
6616
6617 // Determine if this category is also "non-lazy".
6618 if (ImplementationIsNonLazy(OCD))
6619 DefinedNonLazyCategories.push_back(GCATV);
6620 // method definition entries must be clear for next implementation.
6621 MethodDefinitions.clear();
6622}
6623
6624/// emitMethodConstant - Return a struct objc_method constant. If
6625/// forProtocol is true, the implementation will be null; otherwise,
6626/// the method must have a definition registered with the runtime.
6627///
6628/// struct _objc_method {
6629/// SEL _cmd;
6630/// char *method_type;
6631/// char *_imp;
6632/// }
6633void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::emitMethodConstant(ConstantArrayBuilder &builder,
6634 const ObjCMethodDecl *MD,
6635 bool forProtocol) {
6636 auto method = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.MethodTy);
6637 method.addBitCast(GetMethodVarName(MD->getSelector()),
6638 ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy);
6639 method.add(GetMethodVarType(MD));
6640
6641 if (forProtocol) {
6642 // Protocol methods have no implementation. So, this entry is always NULL.
6643 method.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
6644 } else {
6645 llvm::Function *fn = GetMethodDefinition(MD);
6646 assert(fn && "no definition for method?");
6647 method.addBitCast(fn, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
6648 }
6649
6650 method.finishAndAddTo(builder);
6651}
6652
6653/// Build meta-data for method declarations.
6654///
6655/// struct _method_list_t {
6656/// uint32_t entsize; // sizeof(struct _objc_method)
6657/// uint32_t method_count;
6658/// struct _objc_method method_list[method_count];
6659/// }
6660///
6661llvm::Constant *
6662CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::emitMethodList(Twine name, MethodListType kind,
6663 ArrayRef<const ObjCMethodDecl *> methods) {
6664 // Return null for empty list.
6665 if (methods.empty())
6666 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.MethodListnfABIPtrTy);
6667
6668 StringRef prefix;
6669 bool forProtocol;
6670 switch (kind) {
6671 case MethodListType::CategoryInstanceMethods:
6672 prefix = "_OBJC_$_CATEGORY_INSTANCE_METHODS_";
6673 forProtocol = false;
6674 break;
6675 case MethodListType::CategoryClassMethods:
6676 prefix = "_OBJC_$_CATEGORY_CLASS_METHODS_";
6677 forProtocol = false;
6678 break;
6679 case MethodListType::InstanceMethods:
6680 prefix = "_OBJC_$_INSTANCE_METHODS_";
6681 forProtocol = false;
6682 break;
6683 case MethodListType::ClassMethods:
6684 prefix = "_OBJC_$_CLASS_METHODS_";
6685 forProtocol = false;
6686 break;
6687
6688 case MethodListType::ProtocolInstanceMethods:
6689 prefix = "_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_INSTANCE_METHODS_";
6690 forProtocol = true;
6691 break;
6692 case MethodListType::ProtocolClassMethods:
6693 prefix = "_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_CLASS_METHODS_";
6694 forProtocol = true;
6695 break;
6696 case MethodListType::OptionalProtocolInstanceMethods:
6697 prefix = "_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_INSTANCE_METHODS_OPT_";
6698 forProtocol = true;
6699 break;
6700 case MethodListType::OptionalProtocolClassMethods:
6701 prefix = "_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_CLASS_METHODS_OPT_";
6702 forProtocol = true;
6703 break;
6704 }
6705
6706 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6707 auto values = builder.beginStruct();
6708
6709 // sizeof(struct _objc_method)
6710 unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.MethodTy);
6711 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Size);
6712 // method_count
6713 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, methods.size());
6714 auto methodArray = values.beginArray(ObjCTypes.MethodTy);
6715 for (auto MD : methods) {
6716 emitMethodConstant(methodArray, MD, forProtocol);
6717 }
6718 methodArray.finishAndAddTo(values);
6719
6720 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = finishAndCreateGlobal(values, prefix + name, CGM);
6721 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
6722 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.MethodListnfABIPtrTy);
6723}
6724
6725/// ObjCIvarOffsetVariable - Returns the ivar offset variable for
6726/// the given ivar.
6727llvm::GlobalVariable *
6728CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::ObjCIvarOffsetVariable(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
6729 const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar) {
6730 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Container = Ivar->getContainingInterface();
6731 llvm::SmallString<64> Name("OBJC_IVAR_$_");
6732 Name += Container->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6733 Name += ".";
6734 Name += Ivar->getName();
6735 llvm::GlobalVariable *IvarOffsetGV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(Name);
6736 if (!IvarOffsetGV) {
6737 IvarOffsetGV =
6738 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy,
6739 false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
6740 nullptr, Name.str());
6741 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
6742 bool IsPrivateOrPackage =
6743 Ivar->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Private ||
6744 Ivar->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Package;
6745
6746 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ContainingID = Ivar->getContainingInterface();
6747
6748 if (ContainingID->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
6749 IvarOffsetGV
6750 ->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
6751 else if (ContainingID->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>() && !IsPrivateOrPackage)
6752 IvarOffsetGV
6753 ->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass);
6754 }
6755 }
6756 return IvarOffsetGV;
6757}
6758
6759llvm::Constant *
6760CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitIvarOffsetVar(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
6761 const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar,
6762 unsigned long int Offset) {
6763 llvm::GlobalVariable *IvarOffsetGV = ObjCIvarOffsetVariable(ID, Ivar);
6764 IvarOffsetGV->setInitializer(
6765 llvm::ConstantInt::get(ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy, Offset));
6766 IvarOffsetGV->setAlignment(
6767 CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy));
6768
6769 if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
6770 // FIXME: This matches gcc, but shouldn't the visibility be set on the use
6771 // as well (i.e., in ObjCIvarOffsetVariable).
6772 if (Ivar->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Private ||
6773 Ivar->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Package ||
6774 ID->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility)
6775 IvarOffsetGV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
6776 else
6777 IvarOffsetGV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility);
6778 }
6779
6780 // If ID's layout is known, then make the global constant. This serves as a
6781 // useful assertion: we'll never use this variable to calculate ivar offsets,
6782 // so if the runtime tries to patch it then we should crash.
6783 if (isClassLayoutKnownStatically(ID))
6784 IvarOffsetGV->setConstant(true);
6785
6786 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
6787 IvarOffsetGV->setSection("__DATA, __objc_ivar");
6788 return IvarOffsetGV;
6789}
6790
6791/// EmitIvarList - Emit the ivar list for the given
6792/// implementation. The return value has type
6793/// IvarListnfABIPtrTy.
6794/// struct _ivar_t {
6795/// unsigned [long] int *offset; // pointer to ivar offset location
6796/// char *name;
6797/// char *type;
6798/// uint32_t alignment;
6799/// uint32_t size;
6800/// }
6801/// struct _ivar_list_t {
6802/// uint32 entsize; // sizeof(struct _ivar_t)
6803/// uint32 count;
6804/// struct _iver_t list[count];
6805/// }
6806///
6807
6808llvm::Constant *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitIvarList(
6809 const ObjCImplementationDecl *ID) {
6810
6811 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6812 auto ivarList = builder.beginStruct();
6813 ivarList.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy,
6814 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.IvarnfABITy));
6815 auto ivarCountSlot = ivarList.addPlaceholder();
6816 auto ivars = ivarList.beginArray(ObjCTypes.IvarnfABITy);
6817
6818 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OID = ID->getClassInterface();
6819 assert(OID && "CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitIvarList - null interface");
6820
6821 // FIXME. Consolidate this with similar code in GenerateClass.
6822
6823 for (const ObjCIvarDecl *IVD = OID->all_declared_ivar_begin();
6824 IVD; IVD = IVD->getNextIvar()) {
6825 // Ignore unnamed bit-fields.
6826 if (!IVD->getDeclName())
6827 continue;
6828
6829 auto ivar = ivars.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.IvarnfABITy);
6830 ivar.add(EmitIvarOffsetVar(ID->getClassInterface(), IVD,
6831 ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, ID, IVD)));
6832 ivar.add(GetMethodVarName(IVD->getIdentifier()));
6833 ivar.add(GetMethodVarType(IVD));
6834 llvm::Type *FieldTy =
6835 CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(IVD->getType());
6836 unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(FieldTy);
6837 unsigned Align = CGM.getContext().getPreferredTypeAlign(
6838 IVD->getType().getTypePtr()) >> 3;
6839 Align = llvm::Log2_32(Align);
6840 ivar.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Align);
6841 // NOTE. Size of a bitfield does not match gcc's, because of the
6842 // way bitfields are treated special in each. But I am told that
6843 // 'size' for bitfield ivars is ignored by the runtime so it does
6844 // not matter. If it matters, there is enough info to get the
6845 // bitfield right!
6846 ivar.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Size);
6847 ivar.finishAndAddTo(ivars);
6848 }
6849 // Return null for empty list.
6850 if (ivars.empty()) {
6851 ivars.abandon();
6852 ivarList.abandon();
6853 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.IvarListnfABIPtrTy);
6854 }
6855
6856 auto ivarCount = ivars.size();
6857 ivars.finishAndAddTo(ivarList);
6858 ivarList.fillPlaceholderWithInt(ivarCountSlot, ObjCTypes.IntTy, ivarCount);
6859
6860 const char *Prefix = "_OBJC_$_INSTANCE_VARIABLES_";
6861 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = finishAndCreateGlobal(
6862 ivarList, Prefix + OID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(), CGM);
6863 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
6864 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.IvarListnfABIPtrTy);
6865}
6866
6867llvm::Constant *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetOrEmitProtocolRef(
6868 const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
6869 llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = Protocols[PD->getIdentifier()];
6870
6871 if (!Entry) {
6872 // We use the initializer as a marker of whether this is a forward
6873 // reference or not. At module finalization we add the empty
6874 // contents for protocols which were referenced but never defined.
6875 llvm::SmallString<64> Protocol;
6876 llvm::raw_svector_ostream(Protocol) << "_OBJC_PROTOCOL_$_"
6877 << PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6878
6879 Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABITy,
6880 false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
6881 nullptr, Protocol);
6882 if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
6883 Entry->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(Protocol));
6884 }
6885
6886 return Entry;
6887}
6888
6889/// GetOrEmitProtocol - Generate the protocol meta-data:
6890/// @code
6891/// struct _protocol_t {
6892/// id isa; // NULL
6893/// const char * const protocol_name;
6894/// const struct _protocol_list_t * protocol_list; // super protocols
6895/// const struct method_list_t * const instance_methods;
6896/// const struct method_list_t * const class_methods;
6897/// const struct method_list_t *optionalInstanceMethods;
6898/// const struct method_list_t *optionalClassMethods;
6899/// const struct _prop_list_t * properties;
6900/// const uint32_t size; // sizeof(struct _protocol_t)
6901/// const uint32_t flags; // = 0
6902/// const char ** extendedMethodTypes;
6903/// const char *demangledName;
6904/// const struct _prop_list_t * class_properties;
6905/// }
6906/// @endcode
6907///
6908
6909llvm::Constant *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetOrEmitProtocol(
6910 const ObjCProtocolDecl *PD) {
6911 llvm::GlobalVariable *Entry = Protocols[PD->getIdentifier()];
6912
6913 // Early exit if a defining object has already been generated.
6914 if (Entry && Entry->hasInitializer())
6915 return Entry;
6916
6917 // Use the protocol definition, if there is one.
6918 assert(PD->hasDefinition() &&
6919 "emitting protocol metadata without definition");
6920 PD = PD->getDefinition();
6921
6922 auto methodLists = ProtocolMethodLists::get(PD);
6923
6924 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
6925 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABITy);
6926
6927 // isa is NULL
6928 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
6929 values.add(GetClassName(PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()));
6930 values.add(EmitProtocolList("_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_REFS_"
6931 + PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6932 PD->protocol_begin(),
6933 PD->protocol_end()));
6934 values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
6935 ProtocolMethodLists::RequiredInstanceMethods));
6936 values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
6937 ProtocolMethodLists::RequiredClassMethods));
6938 values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
6939 ProtocolMethodLists::OptionalInstanceMethods));
6940 values.add(methodLists.emitMethodList(this, PD,
6941 ProtocolMethodLists::OptionalClassMethods));
6942 values.add(EmitPropertyList(
6943 "_OBJC_$_PROP_LIST_" + PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6944 nullptr, PD, ObjCTypes, false));
6945 uint32_t Size =
6946 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABITy);
6947 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, Size);
6948 values.addInt(ObjCTypes.IntTy, 0);
6949 values.add(EmitProtocolMethodTypes("_OBJC_$_PROTOCOL_METHOD_TYPES_"
6950 + PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6951 methodLists.emitExtendedTypesArray(this),
6952 ObjCTypes));
6953
6954 // const char *demangledName;
6955 values.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
6956
6957 values.add(EmitPropertyList(
6958 "_OBJC_$_CLASS_PROP_LIST_" + PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString(),
6959 nullptr, PD, ObjCTypes, true));
6960
6961 if (Entry) {
6962 // Already created, fix the linkage and update the initializer.
6963 Entry->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage);
6964 values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(Entry);
6965 } else {
6966 llvm::SmallString<64> symbolName;
6967 llvm::raw_svector_ostream(symbolName)
6968 << "_OBJC_PROTOCOL_$_" << PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6969
6970 Entry = values.finishAndCreateGlobal(symbolName, CGM.getPointerAlign(),
6971 /*constant*/ false,
6972 llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage);
6973 if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
6974 Entry->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(symbolName));
6975
6976 Protocols[PD->getIdentifier()] = Entry;
6977 }
6978 Entry->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
6979 CGM.addUsedGlobal(Entry);
6980
6981 // Use this protocol meta-data to build protocol list table in section
6982 // __DATA, __objc_protolist
6983 llvm::SmallString<64> ProtocolRef;
6984 llvm::raw_svector_ostream(ProtocolRef) << "_OBJC_LABEL_PROTOCOL_$_"
6985 << PD->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
6986
6987 llvm::GlobalVariable *PTGV =
6988 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABIPtrTy,
6989 false, llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, Entry,
6990 ProtocolRef);
6991 if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
6992 PTGV->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ProtocolRef));
6993 PTGV->setAlignment(
6994 CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABIPtrTy));
6995 PTGV->setSection(GetSectionName("__objc_protolist",
6996 "coalesced,no_dead_strip"));
6997 PTGV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
6998 CGM.addUsedGlobal(PTGV);
6999 return Entry;
7000}
7001
7002/// EmitProtocolList - Generate protocol list meta-data:
7003/// @code
7004/// struct _protocol_list_t {
7005/// long protocol_count; // Note, this is 32/64 bit
7006/// struct _protocol_t[protocol_count];
7007/// }
7008/// @endcode
7009///
7010llvm::Constant *
7011CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitProtocolList(Twine Name,
7012 ObjCProtocolDecl::protocol_iterator begin,
7013 ObjCProtocolDecl::protocol_iterator end) {
7014 SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 16> ProtocolRefs;
7015
7016 // Just return null for empty protocol lists
7017 if (begin == end)
7018 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ObjCTypes.ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy);
7019
7020 // FIXME: We shouldn't need to do this lookup here, should we?
7021 SmallString<256> TmpName;
7022 Name.toVector(TmpName);
7023 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
7024 CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(TmpName.str(), true);
7025 if (GV)
7026 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ObjCTypes.ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy);
7027
7028 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
7029 auto values = builder.beginStruct();
7030 auto countSlot = values.addPlaceholder();
7031
7032 // A null-terminated array of protocols.
7033 auto array = values.beginArray(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABIPtrTy);
7034 for (; begin != end; ++begin)
7035 array.add(GetProtocolRef(*begin)); // Implemented???
7036 auto count = array.size();
7037 array.addNullPointer(ObjCTypes.ProtocolnfABIPtrTy);
7038
7039 array.finishAndAddTo(values);
7040 values.fillPlaceholderWithInt(countSlot, ObjCTypes.LongTy, count);
7041
7042 GV = finishAndCreateGlobal(values, Name, CGM);
7043 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
7044 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV,
7045 ObjCTypes.ProtocolListnfABIPtrTy);
7046}
7047
7048/// EmitObjCValueForIvar - Code Gen for nonfragile ivar reference.
7049/// This code gen. amounts to generating code for:
7050/// @code
7051/// (type *)((char *)base + _OBJC_IVAR_$_.ivar;
7052/// @encode
7053///
7054LValue CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitObjCValueForIvar(
7055 CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7056 QualType ObjectTy,
7057 llvm::Value *BaseValue,
7058 const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar,
7059 unsigned CVRQualifiers) {
7060 ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = ObjectTy->getAs<ObjCObjectType>()->getInterface();
7061 llvm::Value *Offset = EmitIvarOffset(CGF, ID, Ivar);
7062 return EmitValueForIvarAtOffset(CGF, ID, BaseValue, Ivar, CVRQualifiers,
7063 Offset);
7064}
7065
7066llvm::Value *
7067CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitIvarOffset(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7068 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Interface,
7069 const ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar) {
7070 llvm::Value *IvarOffsetValue;
7071 if (isClassLayoutKnownStatically(Interface)) {
7072 IvarOffsetValue = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
7073 ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy,
7074 ComputeIvarBaseOffset(CGM, Interface->getImplementation(), Ivar));
7075 } else {
7076 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = ObjCIvarOffsetVariable(Interface, Ivar);
7077 IvarOffsetValue =
7078 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(GV, CGF.getSizeAlign(), "ivar");
7079 if (IsIvarOffsetKnownIdempotent(CGF, Ivar))
7080 cast<llvm::LoadInst>(IvarOffsetValue)
7081 ->setMetadata(CGM.getModule().getMDKindID("invariant.load"),
7082 llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, None));
7083 }
7084
7085 // This could be 32bit int or 64bit integer depending on the architecture.
7086 // Cast it to 64bit integer value, if it is a 32bit integer ivar offset value
7087 // as this is what caller always expects.
7088 if (ObjCTypes.IvarOffsetVarTy == ObjCTypes.IntTy)
7089 IvarOffsetValue = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
7090 IvarOffsetValue, ObjCTypes.LongTy, true, "ivar.conv");
7091 return IvarOffsetValue;
7092}
7093
7094static void appendSelectorForMessageRefTable(std::string &buffer,
7095 Selector selector) {
7096 if (selector.isUnarySelector()) {
7097 buffer += selector.getNameForSlot(0);
7098 return;
7099 }
7100
7101 for (unsigned i = 0, e = selector.getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i) {
7102 buffer += selector.getNameForSlot(i);
7103 buffer += '_';
7104 }
7105}
7106
7107/// Emit a "vtable" message send. We emit a weak hidden-visibility
7108/// struct, initially containing the selector pointer and a pointer to
7109/// a "fixup" variant of the appropriate objc_msgSend. To call, we
7110/// load and call the function pointer, passing the address of the
7111/// struct as the second parameter. The runtime determines whether
7112/// the selector is currently emitted using vtable dispatch; if so, it
7113/// substitutes a stub function which simply tail-calls through the
7114/// appropriate vtable slot, and if not, it substitues a stub function
7115/// which tail-calls objc_msgSend. Both stubs adjust the selector
7116/// argument to correctly point to the selector.
7117RValue
7118CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitVTableMessageSend(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7119 ReturnValueSlot returnSlot,
7120 QualType resultType,
7121 Selector selector,
7122 llvm::Value *arg0,
7123 QualType arg0Type,
7124 bool isSuper,
7125 const CallArgList &formalArgs,
7126 const ObjCMethodDecl *method) {
7127 // Compute the actual arguments.
7128 CallArgList args;
7129
7130 // First argument: the receiver / super-call structure.
7131 if (!isSuper)
7132 arg0 = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(arg0, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7133 args.add(RValue::get(arg0), arg0Type);
7134
7135 // Second argument: a pointer to the message ref structure. Leave
7136 // the actual argument value blank for now.
7137 args.add(RValue::get(nullptr), ObjCTypes.MessageRefCPtrTy);
7138
7139 args.insert(args.end(), formalArgs.begin(), formalArgs.end());
7140
7141 MessageSendInfo MSI = getMessageSendInfo(method, resultType, args);
7142
7143 NullReturnState nullReturn;
7144
7145 // Find the function to call and the mangled name for the message
7146 // ref structure. Using a different mangled name wouldn't actually
7147 // be a problem; it would just be a waste.
7148 //
7149 // The runtime currently never uses vtable dispatch for anything
7150 // except normal, non-super message-sends.
7151 // FIXME: don't use this for that.
7152 llvm::FunctionCallee fn = nullptr;
7153 std::string messageRefName("_");
7154 if (CGM.ReturnSlotInterferesWithArgs(MSI.CallInfo)) {
7155 if (isSuper) {
7156 fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendSuper2StretFixupFn();
7157 messageRefName += "objc_msgSendSuper2_stret_fixup";
7158 } else {
7159 nullReturn.init(CGF, arg0);
7160 fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendStretFixupFn();
7161 messageRefName += "objc_msgSend_stret_fixup";
7162 }
7163 } else if (!isSuper && CGM.ReturnTypeUsesFPRet(resultType)) {
7164 fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendFpretFixupFn();
7165 messageRefName += "objc_msgSend_fpret_fixup";
7166 } else {
7167 if (isSuper) {
7168 fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendSuper2FixupFn();
7169 messageRefName += "objc_msgSendSuper2_fixup";
7170 } else {
7171 fn = ObjCTypes.getMessageSendFixupFn();
7172 messageRefName += "objc_msgSend_fixup";
7173 }
7174 }
7175 assert(fn && "CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitMessageSend");
7176 messageRefName += '_';
7177
7178 // Append the selector name, except use underscores anywhere we
7179 // would have used colons.
7180 appendSelectorForMessageRefTable(messageRefName, selector);
7181
7182 llvm::GlobalVariable *messageRef
7183 = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(messageRefName);
7184 if (!messageRef) {
7185 // Build the message ref structure.
7186 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
7187 auto values = builder.beginStruct();
7188 values.add(cast<llvm::Constant>(fn.getCallee()));
7189 values.add(GetMethodVarName(selector));
7190 messageRef = values.finishAndCreateGlobal(messageRefName,
7191 CharUnits::fromQuantity(16),
7192 /*constant*/ false,
7193 llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage);
7194 messageRef->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
7195 messageRef->setSection(GetSectionName("__objc_msgrefs", "coalesced"));
7196 }
7197
7198 bool requiresnullCheck = false;
7199 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount && method)
7200 for (const auto *ParamDecl : method->parameters()) {
7201 if (ParamDecl->hasAttr<NSConsumedAttr>()) {
7202 if (!nullReturn.NullBB)
7203 nullReturn.init(CGF, arg0);
7204 requiresnullCheck = true;
7205 break;
7206 }
7207 }
7208
7209 Address mref =
7210 Address(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(messageRef, ObjCTypes.MessageRefPtrTy),
7211 CGF.getPointerAlign());
7212
7213 // Update the message ref argument.
7214 args[1].setRValue(RValue::get(mref.getPointer()));
7215
7216 // Load the function to call from the message ref table.
7217 Address calleeAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(mref, 0);
7218 llvm::Value *calleePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(calleeAddr, "msgSend_fn");
7219
7220 calleePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(calleePtr, MSI.MessengerType);
7221 CGCallee callee(CGCalleeInfo(), calleePtr);
7222
7223 RValue result = CGF.EmitCall(MSI.CallInfo, callee, returnSlot, args);
7224 return nullReturn.complete(CGF, returnSlot, result, resultType, formalArgs,
7225 requiresnullCheck ? method : nullptr);
7226}
7227
7228/// Generate code for a message send expression in the nonfragile abi.
7229CodeGen::RValue
7230CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateMessageSend(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7231 ReturnValueSlot Return,
7232 QualType ResultType,
7233 Selector Sel,
7234 llvm::Value *Receiver,
7235 const CallArgList &CallArgs,
7236 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class,
7237 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
7238 return isVTableDispatchedSelector(Sel)
7239 ? EmitVTableMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType, Sel,
7240 Receiver, CGF.getContext().getObjCIdType(),
7241 false, CallArgs, Method)
7242 : EmitMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType,
7243 EmitSelector(CGF, Sel),
7244 Receiver, CGF.getContext().getObjCIdType(),
7245 false, CallArgs, Method, Class, ObjCTypes);
7246}
7247
7248llvm::Constant *
7249CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClassGlobal(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
7250 bool metaclass,
7251 ForDefinition_t isForDefinition) {
7252 auto prefix =
7253 (metaclass ? getMetaclassSymbolPrefix() : getClassSymbolPrefix());
7254 return GetClassGlobal((prefix + ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString()).str(),
7255 isForDefinition,
7256 ID->isWeakImported(),
7257 !isForDefinition
7258 && CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()
7259 && ID->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>());
7260}
7261
7262llvm::Constant *
7263CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClassGlobal(StringRef Name,
7264 ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition,
7265 bool Weak, bool DLLImport) {
7266 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes L =
7267 Weak ? llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage
7268 : llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage;
7269
7270 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(Name);
7271 if (!GV || GV->getType() != ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy->getPointerTo()) {
7272 auto *NewGV =
7273 new llvm::GlobalVariable(ObjCTypes.ClassnfABITy, false, L, nullptr,
7274 Name, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
7275 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
7276
7277 if (DLLImport)
7278 NewGV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
7279
7280 if (GV) {
7281 GV->replaceAllUsesWith(
7282 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(NewGV, GV->getType()));
7283 GV->eraseFromParent();
7284 }
7285 GV = NewGV;
7286 CGM.getModule().getGlobalList().push_back(GV);
7287 }
7288
7289 assert(GV->getLinkage() == L);
7290 return GV;
7291}
7292
7293llvm::Constant *
7294CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClassGlobalForClassRef(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7295 llvm::Constant *ClassGV = GetClassGlobal(ID, /*metaclass*/ false,
7296 NotForDefinition);
7297
7298 if (!ID->hasAttr<ObjCClassStubAttr>())
7299 return ClassGV;
7300
7301 ClassGV = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(ClassGV, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7302
7303 // Stub classes are pointer-aligned. Classrefs pointing at stub classes
7304 // must set the least significant bit set to 1.
7305 auto *Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 1);
7306 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(CGM.Int8Ty, ClassGV, Idx);
7307}
7308
7309llvm::Value *
7310CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitLoadOfClassRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7311 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
7312 llvm::GlobalVariable *Entry) {
7313 if (ID && ID->hasAttr<ObjCClassStubAttr>()) {
7314 // Classrefs pointing at Objective-C stub classes must be loaded by calling
7315 // a special runtime function.
7316 return CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
7317 ObjCTypes.getLoadClassrefFn(), Entry, "load_classref_result");
7318 }
7319
7320 CharUnits Align = CGF.getPointerAlign();
7321 return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Entry, Align);
7322}
7323
7324llvm::Value *
7325CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitClassRefFromId(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7326 IdentifierInfo *II,
7327 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7328 llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = ClassReferences[II];
7329
7330 if (!Entry) {
7331 llvm::Constant *ClassGV;
7332 if (ID) {
7333 ClassGV = GetClassGlobalForClassRef(ID);
7334 } else {
7335 ClassGV = GetClassGlobal((getClassSymbolPrefix() + II->getName()).str(),
7336 NotForDefinition);
7337 assert(ClassGV->getType() == ObjCTypes.ClassnfABIPtrTy &&
7338 "classref was emitted with the wrong type?");
7339 }
7340
7341 std::string SectionName =
7342 GetSectionName("__objc_classrefs", "regular,no_dead_strip");
7343 Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
7344 CGM.getModule(), ClassGV->getType(), false,
7345 getLinkageTypeForObjCMetadata(CGM, SectionName), ClassGV,
7346 "OBJC_CLASSLIST_REFERENCES_$_");
7347 Entry->setAlignment(CGF.getPointerAlign().getQuantity());
7348 if (!ID || !ID->hasAttr<ObjCClassStubAttr>())
7349 Entry->setSection(SectionName);
7350
7351 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(Entry);
7352 }
7353
7354 return EmitLoadOfClassRef(CGF, ID, Entry);
7355}
7356
7357llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitClassRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7358 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7359 // If the class has the objc_runtime_visible attribute, we need to
7360 // use the Objective-C runtime to get the class.
7361 if (ID->hasAttr<ObjCRuntimeVisibleAttr>())
7362 return EmitClassRefViaRuntime(CGF, ID, ObjCTypes);
7363
7364 return EmitClassRefFromId(CGF, ID->getIdentifier(), ID);
7365}
7366
7367llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitNSAutoreleasePoolClassRef(
7368 CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
7369 IdentifierInfo *II = &CGM.getContext().Idents.get("NSAutoreleasePool");
7370 return EmitClassRefFromId(CGF, II, nullptr);
7371}
7372
7373llvm::Value *
7374CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitSuperClassRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7375 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7376 llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = SuperClassReferences[ID->getIdentifier()];
7377
7378 if (!Entry) {
7379 llvm::Constant *ClassGV = GetClassGlobalForClassRef(ID);
7380 std::string SectionName =
7381 GetSectionName("__objc_superrefs", "regular,no_dead_strip");
7382 Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
7383 CGM.getModule(), ClassGV->getType(), false,
7384 getLinkageTypeForObjCMetadata(CGM, SectionName), ClassGV,
7385 "OBJC_CLASSLIST_SUP_REFS_$_");
7386 Entry->setAlignment(CGF.getPointerAlign().getQuantity());
7387 Entry->setSection(SectionName);
7388 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(Entry);
7389 }
7390
7391 return EmitLoadOfClassRef(CGF, ID, Entry);
7392}

7394/// EmitMetaClassRef - Return a Value * of the address of _class_t
7395/// meta-data
7396///
7397llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitMetaClassRef(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7398 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
7399 bool Weak) {
7400 CharUnits Align = CGF.getPointerAlign();
7401 llvm::GlobalVariable * &Entry = MetaClassReferences[ID->getIdentifier()];
7402 if (!Entry) {
7403 auto MetaClassGV = GetClassGlobal(ID, /*metaclass*/ true, NotForDefinition);
7404 std::string SectionName =
7405 GetSectionName("__objc_superrefs", "regular,no_dead_strip");
7406 Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
7407 CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.ClassnfABIPtrTy, false,
7408 getLinkageTypeForObjCMetadata(CGM, SectionName), MetaClassGV,
7409 "OBJC_CLASSLIST_SUP_REFS_$_");
7410 Entry->setAlignment(Align.getQuantity());
7411 Entry->setSection(SectionName);
7412 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(Entry);
7413 }
7414
7415 return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Entry, Align);
7416}

7418/// GetClass - Return a reference to the class for the given interface
7419/// decl.
7420llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetClass(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7421 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID) {
7422 if (ID->isWeakImported()) {
7423 auto ClassGV = GetClassGlobal(ID, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition);
7424 (void)ClassGV;
7425 assert(!isa<llvm::GlobalVariable>(ClassGV) ||
7426 cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(ClassGV)->hasExternalWeakLinkage());
7427 }
7428
7429 return EmitClassRef(CGF, ID);
7430}
7431
7432/// Generates a message send where the super is the receiver. This is
7433/// a message send to self with special delivery semantics indicating
7434/// which class's method should be called.
7435CodeGen::RValue
7436CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GenerateMessageSendSuper(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7437 ReturnValueSlot Return,
7438 QualType ResultType,
7439 Selector Sel,
7440 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class,
7441 bool isCategoryImpl,
7442 llvm::Value *Receiver,
7443 bool IsClassMessage,
7444 const CodeGen::CallArgList &CallArgs,
7445 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method) {
7446 // ...
7447 // Create and init a super structure; this is a (receiver, class)
7448 // pair we will pass to objc_msgSendSuper.
7449 Address ObjCSuper =
7450 CGF.CreateTempAlloca(ObjCTypes.SuperTy, CGF.getPointerAlign(),
7451 "objc_super");
7452
7453 llvm::Value *ReceiverAsObject =
7454 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Receiver, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7455 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(ReceiverAsObject,
7456 CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCSuper, 0));
7457
7458 // If this is a class message the metaclass is passed as the target.
7459 llvm::Value *Target;
7460 if (IsClassMessage)
7461 Target = EmitMetaClassRef(CGF, Class, Class->isWeakImported());
7462 else
7463 Target = EmitSuperClassRef(CGF, Class);
7464
7465 // FIXME: We shouldn't need to do this cast, rectify the ASTContext and
7466 // ObjCTypes types.
7467 llvm::Type *ClassTy =
7468 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getObjCClassType());
7469 Target = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Target, ClassTy);
7470 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Target, CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(ObjCSuper, 1));
7471
7472 return (isVTableDispatchedSelector(Sel))
7473 ? EmitVTableMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType, Sel,
7474 ObjCSuper.getPointer(), ObjCTypes.SuperPtrCTy,
7475 true, CallArgs, Method)
7476 : EmitMessageSend(CGF, Return, ResultType,
7477 EmitSelector(CGF, Sel),
7478 ObjCSuper.getPointer(), ObjCTypes.SuperPtrCTy,
7479 true, CallArgs, Method, Class, ObjCTypes);
7480}
7481
7482llvm::Value *CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitSelector(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7483 Selector Sel) {
7484 Address Addr = EmitSelectorAddr(CGF, Sel);
7485
7486 llvm::LoadInst* LI = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Addr);
7487 LI->setMetadata(CGM.getModule().getMDKindID("invariant.load"),
7488 llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, None));
7489 return LI;
7490}
7491
7492Address CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitSelectorAddr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7493 Selector Sel) {
7494 llvm::GlobalVariable *&Entry = SelectorReferences[Sel];
7495
7496 CharUnits Align = CGF.getPointerAlign();
7497 if (!Entry) {
7498 llvm::Constant *Casted =
7499 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GetMethodVarName(Sel),
7500 ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy);
7501 std::string SectionName =
7502 GetSectionName("__objc_selrefs", "literal_pointers,no_dead_strip");
7503 Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
7504 CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.SelectorPtrTy, false,
7505 getLinkageTypeForObjCMetadata(CGM, SectionName), Casted,
7506 "OBJC_SELECTOR_REFERENCES_");
7507 Entry->setExternallyInitialized(true);
7508 Entry->setSection(SectionName);
7509 Entry->setAlignment(Align.getQuantity());
7510 CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(Entry);
7511 }
7512
7513 return Address(Entry, Align);
7514}

7516/// EmitObjCIvarAssign - Code gen for assigning to a __strong object.
7517/// objc_assign_ivar (id src, id *dst, ptrdiff_t)
7518///
7519void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitObjCIvarAssign(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7520 llvm::Value *src,
7521 Address dst,
7522 llvm::Value *ivarOffset) {
7523 llvm::Type * SrcTy = src->getType();
7524 if (!isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) {
7525 unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
7526 assert(Size <= 8 && "does not support size > 8");
7527 src = (Size == 4 ? CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.IntTy)
7528 : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.LongTy));
7529 src = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(src, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7530 }
7531 src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7532 dst = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(dst, ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
7533 llvm::Value *args[] = { src, dst.getPointer(), ivarOffset };
7534 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignIvarFn(), args);
7535}

7548 : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.LongTy));
7549 src = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(src, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7550 }
7551 src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);

7604/// EmitObjCGlobalAssign - Code gen for assigning to a __strong object.
7605/// objc_assign_global (id src, id *dst)
7606///
7607void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitObjCGlobalAssign(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7608 llvm::Value *src, Address dst,
7609 bool threadlocal) {
7610 llvm::Type * SrcTy = src->getType();
7611 if (!isa<llvm::PointerType>(SrcTy)) {
7612 unsigned Size = CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy);
7613 assert(Size <= 8 && "does not support size > 8");
7614 src = (Size == 4 ? CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.IntTy)
7615 : CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.LongTy));
7616 src = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(src, ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy);
7617 }
7618 src = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(src, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7619 dst = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(dst, ObjCTypes.PtrObjectPtrTy);
7620 llvm::Value *args[] = { src, dst.getPointer() };
7621 if (!threadlocal)
7622 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignGlobalFn(),
7623 args, "globalassign");
7624 else
7625 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(ObjCTypes.getGcAssignThreadLocalFn(),
7626 args, "threadlocalassign");

7635
7636llvm::Constant *
7637CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetEHType(QualType T) {
7638 // There's a particular fixed type info for 'id'.
7639 if (T->isObjCIdType() || T->isObjCQualifiedIdType()) {
7640 auto *IDEHType = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable("OBJC_EHTYPE_id");
7641 if (!IDEHType) {
7642 IDEHType =
7643 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.EHTypeTy, false,
7644 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
7645 "OBJC_EHTYPE_id");
7646 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
7647 IDEHType->setDLLStorageClass(getStorage(CGM, "OBJC_EHTYPE_id"));
7648 }
7649 return IDEHType;
7650 }
7651
7652 // All other types should be Objective-C interface pointer types.
7653 const ObjCObjectPointerType *PT = T->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
7654 assert(PT && "Invalid @catch type.");
7655
7656 const ObjCInterfaceType *IT = PT->getInterfaceType();
7657 assert(IT && "Invalid @catch type.");
7658
7659 return GetInterfaceEHType(IT->getDecl(), NotForDefinition);
7660}
7661
7662void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitTryStmt(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7663 const ObjCAtTryStmt &S) {
7664 EmitTryCatchStmt(CGF, S, ObjCTypes.getObjCBeginCatchFn(),
7665 ObjCTypes.getObjCEndCatchFn(),
7666 ObjCTypes.getExceptionRethrowFn());
7667}
7668
7669/// EmitThrowStmt - Generate code for a throw statement.
7670void CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::EmitThrowStmt(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7671 const ObjCAtThrowStmt &S,
7672 bool ClearInsertionPoint) {
7673 if (const Expr *ThrowExpr = S.getThrowExpr()) {
7674 llvm::Value *Exception = CGF.EmitObjCThrowOperand(ThrowExpr);
7675 Exception = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Exception, ObjCTypes.ObjectPtrTy);
7676 llvm::CallBase *Call =
7677 CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(ObjCTypes.getExceptionThrowFn(), Exception);
7678 Call->setDoesNotReturn();
7679 } else {
7680 llvm::CallBase *Call =
7681 CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(ObjCTypes.getExceptionRethrowFn());
7682 Call->setDoesNotReturn();
7683 }
7684
7685 CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
7686 if (ClearInsertionPoint)
7687 CGF.Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
7688}
7689
7690llvm::Constant *
7691CGObjCNonFragileABIMac::GetInterfaceEHType(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID,
7692 ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
7693 llvm::GlobalVariable * &Entry = EHTypeReferences[ID->getIdentifier()];
7694 StringRef ClassName = ID->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
7695
7696 // If we don't need a definition, return the entry if found or check
7697 // if we use an external reference.
7698 if (!IsForDefinition) {
7699 if (Entry)
7700 return Entry;
7701
7702 // If this type (or a super class) has the __objc_exception__
7703 // attribute, emit an external reference.
7704 if (hasObjCExceptionAttribute(CGM.getContext(), ID)) {
7705 std::string EHTypeName = ("OBJC_EHTYPE_$_" + ClassName).str();
7706 Entry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.EHTypeTy,
7707 false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
7708 nullptr, EHTypeName);
7709 CGM.setGVProperties(Entry, ID);
7710 return Entry;
7711 }
7712 }
7713
7714 // Otherwise we need to either make a new entry or fill in the initializer.
7715 assert((!Entry || !Entry->hasInitializer()) && "Duplicate EHType definition");
7716
7717 std::string VTableName = "objc_ehtype_vtable";
7718 auto *VTableGV = CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(VTableName);
7719 if (!VTableGV) {
7720 VTableGV =
7721 new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), ObjCTypes.Int8PtrTy, false,
7722 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
7723 VTableName);
7724 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
7725 VTableGV->setDLLStorageClass(getStorage(CGM, VTableName));
7726 }
7727
7728 llvm::Value *VTableIdx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 2);
7729 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
7730 auto values = builder.beginStruct(ObjCTypes.EHTypeTy);
7731 values.add(
7732 llvm::ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(VTableGV->getValueType(),
7733 VTableGV, VTableIdx));
7734 values.add(GetClassName(ClassName));
7735 values.add(GetClassGlobal(ID, /*metaclass*/ false, NotForDefinition));
7736
7737 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes L = IsForDefinition
7738 ? llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage
7739 : llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage;
7740 if (Entry) {
7741 values.finishAndSetAsInitializer(Entry);
7742 Entry->setAlignment(CGM.getPointerAlign().getQuantity());
7743 } else {
7744 Entry = values.finishAndCreateGlobal("OBJC_EHTYPE_$_" + ClassName,
7745 CGM.getPointerAlign(),
7746 /*constant*/ false,
7747 L);
7748 if (hasObjCExceptionAttribute(CGM.getContext(), ID))
7749 CGM.setGVProperties(Entry, ID);
7750 }
7751 assert(Entry->getLinkage() == L);
7752
7753 if (!CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
7754 if (ID->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility)
7755 Entry->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
7756
7757 if (IsForDefinition)
7758 if (CGM.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
7759 Entry->setSection("__DATA,__objc_const");
7760
7761 return Entry;
7762}
7763
7764/* *** */
7765
7766CodeGen::CGObjCRuntime *
7767CodeGen::CreateMacObjCRuntime(CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) {
7768 switch (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.getKind()) {
7769 case ObjCRuntime::FragileMacOSX:
7770 return new CGObjCMac(CGM);
7771
7772 case ObjCRuntime::MacOSX:
7773 case ObjCRuntime::iOS:
7774 case ObjCRuntime::WatchOS:
7775 return new CGObjCNonFragileABIMac(CGM);
7776
7777 case ObjCRuntime::GNUstep:
7778 case ObjCRuntime::GCC:
7779 case ObjCRuntime::ObjFW:
7780 llvm_unreachable("these runtimes are not Mac runtimes");
7781 }
7782 llvm_unreachable("bad runtime");
7783}
